title: baked chicken(makes its own gravy)
directions: Coat chicken
with
flour
and arrange in single layer, skin down, in
melted
butter
in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake, uncovered,	in
oven for 30 minutes.	Turn chicken and bake until
brown,
15 to 20 minutes longer, until tender. Remove from oven
and
reduce
temperature to 325°.
Pour off excess fat.

title: zucchini cheese casserole(this recipe is heart healthy)
directions: Saute zucchini and chopped onions in oil.
Whip cottage cheese with basil and oregano in blender.
Place alternating layers of zucchini, cottage cheese and tomato in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.
Approximate cal/serving:

title: broccoli and cheese dish
directions: Mix rice, soup, broccoli and Cheez Whiz.
Pour into greased casserole (I use flat-like casserole to bake in).
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Stir when halfway done.

title: chili chicken
directions: Boil chicken and when cool, debone.
In a skillet, melt 1 stick butter.
Add diced onion; then add jalapenos, evaporated milk and 3/4 of the Velveeta cheese.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer chips, chicken and sauce.
Repeat until all are used up.
Then add remaining Velveeta cheese that has been grated. Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: chile-cheese meat loaf
directions: In a large skillet, heat the olive oil over high heat. Add the onion, red pepper, garlic, jalapeno peppers, chili powder, salt, oregano and cumin. Cover, reduce heat to low and cook, stirring once or twice, until the vegetables are soft, about 10 minutes. Add the tomatoes and cook, covered, stirring once or twice, for 10 minutes longer. Remove from the heat and let cool to room temperature.

title: classic cornbread dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Prepare dry bread mix according to package directions.
Let cool, then crumble. Grease one 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
In a large skillet over medium heat, melt butter and saute celery and onion until soft.
In a large bowl, combine celery, onions, 3 c crumbled cornbread, eggs, chicken stock, sage salt and pepper to taste, mix well. Place into prepared dish and bake in 350 oven for 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch icebox squares
directions: Cut cake into 1-inch cubes; place in large bowl.
Combine butterscotch pudding, milk and evaporated milk in large saucepan. Cook, following label directions for pudding.
Fold hot pudding into cake until all pieces are evenly coated.
Spoon half the pudding mixture into a pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Add sliced bananas in a single layer.
Top with remaining pudding mixture, spreading evenly.
Place a layer of waxed paper directly on pudding.
Chill at least 3 hours.
To serve, peel off waxed paper.
Cut dessert into squares.
Whipped cream is optional.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix shortening, butter, brown sugar, egg yolk and vanilla. Add flour, salt and nuts.
Roll in balls, then roll in egg white and extra finely chopped nuts.
Bake 5 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven and press in center of cookie.
Return to oven and bake 8 minutes longer.
To decorate, frost and top with cherry.

title: quick pickled beets
directions: Boil vinegar, sugar and water until clear liquid.
Pour drained beets into this.
Serve hot or chilled.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: This can be used for cream pies by omitting the chocolate chips and adding bananas, coconut, pineapple, etc.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Wrap tortillas in foil.
Heat in a 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes, or until softened.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with chips.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Add peas last two minutes, drain, return to pan. Stir in tuna, sour cream, milk, soup, water chestnuts, French fried onions, salt & pepper.
Pour into ungreased casserole.
Bake uncovered for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1/2 c. French fried onions, 1/4 c. Parmesan cheese, bake until bubbly and onions brown.
6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Combine shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add fruit cocktail juice.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to batter.
Mix well.
Add fruit cocktail and mix.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Beat eggs by hand.
Add syrup, vanilla and salt.
Stir and add pecans.
Pour into unbaked crust and bake for 10 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake until firm (about 40 minutes).

title: ham loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Add to meat and mix well. Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pack in a greased loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for
1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch Tupperware pan.
Grease lightly with vegetable spray.

title: baked ziti with marinara sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook ziti.
Drain; return to pot and cover.
Melt butter in a large heavy saucepan over medium heat. Stir in cream and 6 tablespoons of the Parmesan cheese.
Add about 1/4 of the Mozzarella cheese.
Stir until the cheese melts.
Add ziti, stirring well to coat.
Stir in 6 tablespoons parsley, 1 3/4 cups marinara sauce and pepper.
Transfer mixture to a shallow baking dish and top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 10 minutes.
Top with remaining sauce, Parmesan cheese and parsley.

title: sunshine sauce(for diabetics)
directions: Combine all ingredients in small saucepan.
Heat until warmed through.
Serve over poached or broiled fillets.
One serving equals 2 tablespoons over fish.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Soak raisins in hot water to plump.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in spring-form pan or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes, then bake at 375° for 45 minutes more until edges of cheese cake brown.
Then shut off oven and let the cake stay in oven for one hour.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix
and
spread
Hellmann's mayonnaise evenly to seal. Make sure it is sealed.	Chill for 3 hours.

title: brown jug cheese soup
directions: Cook cubed potatoes, celery, onion and water for 20 minutes in covered pan.
Add mixed vegetables.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Add soup undiluted and stir until blended.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
This soup freezes well.

title: pork tenderloins and stuffing
directions: *STUFFING- Bring 1/3 c of cider and butter to a boil, remove, and stir in stuffing mix. Add the apples, onion, and celery; then set aside.

title: pot roast
directions: Place roast in a large cast iron pot.
Add a teaspoon of shortening.
Rub with garlic powder, salt and pepper on roast. Cook on medium heat on both sides until roast is dark, adding water while it cooks.
Each time you add water, also add garlic powder, salt and pepper.
When roast is brown enough, quit turning.
Add 2 cups of water to make some red eye gravy.
Cook roast for about 3 hours.
When it is about done, chop up onion and add to gravy.

title: last minute dessert
directions: Butter an 8-inch square pan.
Add a can of either apple, cherry or blueberry pie filling (not plain fruit).
Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Pour margarine and nuts on top and bake for approximately 35 minutes at 350°.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Pour all three into ice cream maker and freeze.

title: chicken souffle
directions: Cover bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch casserole dish with bread (add extra pieces, if needed).
Add layer of chicken; cover with cheese.
Add sauteed mushrooms.
Mix eggs and milk; pour over it.
Mix pimentos with both soups and spread on top.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes; let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Delicious with mixed salad and herb or garlic bread.

title: swiss enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken breasts, cool and remove meat and dice.
In oil, cook onion and garlic until soft.
Add chicken and tomato sauce. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add diced green chilies.
Mix bouillon with milk until dissolved over low heat, add mushrooms.
Dip tortillas in milk mixture to soften.
Fill with chicken mixture and roll up. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
When done, pour remaining milk and mushrooms over enchiladas.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until heated through and cheese melted.

title: applesauce raisin nut cake
directions: Mix all together. Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour Bundt or tube pan. Beat with spoon or fork until smooth.
Bake about 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes (until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean). Allow to cool before removing from pan.

title: salmon patties
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup liquid from salmon.
Add egg and flour to salmon; mix well.
Add baking powder to reserved liquid to foam good.
Mix in salmon.
Make into patties.
Fry in hot oil or shortening, browning on both sides.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add oatmeal to boiling water; let stand for 20 minutes.
Cream sugars and margarine.

Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add oatmeal; sift dry ingredients together. Add to creamed mixture, stirring just enough to blend. Add vanilla. Place in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: caramel apple coffeecake
directions: Make a paste with first 3 ingredients and spread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Add sliced apples. Roll biscuits one at a time in sugar and cinnamon.
Place on top of apples.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: brooklyn fireman's meal
directions: Bring chicken broth to boil.
Add rice.
Next mix all other ingredients together in separate bowl.
Take 9 x 13-inch baking pan and spray Pam in the pan.
Pour chicken broth and rice in bottom. Put rest of mixture on top.
Beat 3 more eggs and pour over top. Sprinkle Italian cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes. Will serve 12.

title: lois' chili
directions: Brown ground chuck and onions; sprinkle garlic, salt, pepper, cumin and peppers, then cook until brown. Add beans, chili powder and mustard; cook until boils. Add tomatoes and cook until you feel it's ready to eat.

title: strawberry pizza pie
directions: Mix margarine, flour and sugar well.
Press in pizza pan or two pie plates.
Bake at 400° for 13 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, milk and lemon juice.
Cook strawberries with cornstarch until thick.
Cool and spread on pizza.
Spread with whipped topping and chill.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Boil potatoes about 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain potatoes.
Add butter to potatoes.
Add onion, both cans of soup and 1 cup of cheese.
Mix together, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Transfer mixture to a casserole dish.
Top casserole with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peaches cream cheese cake
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium. Pour into 9-inch deep dish or 10-inch pie pan.
Place pineapple or peaches over batter.
Combine cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and reserved juice in small mixing bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spoon to within 1-inch of edge of batter.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon over cream cheese filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until crust is golden brown.
Filling will appear soft.
Store in refrigerator.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Combine crackers, dates and nuts.
Gently fold into egg whites.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serve topped with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook beef and drain.
Cook noodles according to package and drain.
In large casserole dish (9 x 13-inches), put noodles on bottom.

title: spiced pear jam with pineapple
directions: Peel and core pears.
Wash orange and lemon.
Put the fruit through a grinder, using a coarse blade (or a food processor will work well).
Save the juices.
Combine pulp, juices, pineapple sugar and spices.
Heat the mixture, stirring constantly.
Boil for about 30 minutes.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and jello; add water.
Boil on medium heat until thickens, about 15 minutes, maybe more.
Pour over berries in cooked pie shell.
Let cool.
Top with Dream Whip. Refrigerate.

title: harvest punch
directions: Combine sugar, water, cloves and cinnamon stick in small saucepan.
Simmer 5 minutes over low heat.
Strain mixture into punch bowl.
Stir in orange juice and cider.
Chill.
Garnish with clove-studded orange slices.
Serve over ice.
Makes 12 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: orange biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix margarine, orange juice, and sugar. Heat until melted. Spoon liquid mixture into a 12-cup muffin tin. Pull each biscuit into 4 parts. Put 3 parts biscuit in each muffin cup. Bake 15 minutes or until brown. Let stand a couple of minutes. Invert onto a platter letting muffin pan remain a while so all liquid runs out onto biscuits. Serve warm.

title: date and nut cookies
directions: Combine sugar, flour and baking powder.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in nuts and dates.
Spread in a well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Cut into 1 x 2-inch bars.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Yields about 5 dozen.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Make white sauce of first 5 ingredients.
Place half the potatoes in greased 2 quart casserole.
Cover with half the onions and half the sauce.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake about one hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: zucchini torte
directions: Peel and remove seed from zucchini and dice.
Salt and let set 1 1/2 hours to drain.
Saute onion in oil and add zucchini, salt, pepper, parsley and garlic powder.
Cook 2 minutes or so, then add tomatoes or sauce and cook 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat and add crumbs, cheese and slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into casserole and sprinkle a little oil on top.
Bake to light golden brown, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: deluxe strawberry salad
directions: Mix wafer crumbs and melted margarine; spread or press on bottom of 9-inch square pan.

title: korean salad
directions: Toss salad ingredients together shortly before serving.

title: crabmeat appetizer
directions: Mix and spread on 12 English muffins, baked.
Freeze.
Cut each 1/2 into 8ths after frozen.
Double bag and freeze.
Broil until brown and bubbly.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain beef; stir in soup, don't add water.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Place biscuits in greased muffin tins pressing down to cover bottom and sides. Spoon about 1/4 cup meat mixture into biscuit lined cups. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Yields 12 Pizza Cups.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and pumpkin.
Sift remaining ingredients.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Stir well.
Pour into greased and floured 12 x 8 x 1 inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Wash and drain beans; combine with other ingredients.
Serve immediately.

title: macaroni and cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bring water to a boil.
Add salt and macaroni; cook 10 minutes.
Drain.
Make a layer of macaroni in a baking dish.
Make a layer of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Beat eggs. Add milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over macaroni and cheese layers. Cut butter up in pieces and dot top.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: tuna mushroom casserole
directions: Dilute soup with 2/3 can of water.
Place 1/3 of crushed potato chips in casserole.
Cover with layers of tuna fish, mushroom soup, green pepper, onion and potato chips.
Repeat, ending with chips.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Blend well.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: joyce's oven ribs
directions: Precook ribs on a rack in an open roasting pan at 475° until ribs are crisped and lightly browned (20 to 30 minutes).
Lower oven temperature to 300°.
Baste ribs with sauce made by mixing remaining ingredients.
Pour 2 cups hot water in bottom of pan and cover roaster.
Cook ribs 2 to 3 hours, basting with sauce occasionally (for longer cooking, lower heat to 250° to 275°).

title: smokey corn chowder
directions: Cook onions in butter until tender, but not brown. Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk all at once. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Stir in sausage links (I cut them in pieces). Simmer 10 minutes.

title: quick and easy cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and dressing mix; shape into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: frozen fruit cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream together butter and sugar until fluffy. Beat in egg.
Stir in flour and cream of tartar until well combined.
Blend in pecans and fruit or citron.
Roll dough into two long rolls, about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Wrap each roll in plastic or foil and freeze.

title: white chocolate candy
directions: Place chocolate in heavy flat pan.
Place pan in a 250° oven. Turn oven off and leave chocolate for 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir into melted chocolate, Captain Crunch cereal, miniature marshmallows, Rice Krispies and salted peanuts.
Mix well and drop by teaspoons on wax paper.
Let set to dry and store in covered container. Easy and delicious!
Serves about 125 pieces.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown the meatballs slowly in 1 to 2 tablespoons oil. Add balls to sauce and simmer on low flame 3 to 4 hours.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion and green pepper until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except spaghetti and cheese.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring sauce occasionally.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package.
Serve meat sauce over hot spaghetti.
Serves 8.

title: pickled beets
directions: *Can use 1 tablespoon pickling spice for spices listed.

title: hamburger scramble
directions: Brown ground beef in frying pan; drain.
Chop onion and bell pepper; add to ground beef, then add mushroom soup, tomato sauce, salt and black pepper.
Cook for about 25 or 30 minutes, until onion and pepper are tender.
Serves about 5.

title: swiss pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Ice cake while warm.

title: ginger carrot squash bisque
directions: Combine carrot juice, chicken broth and squash.
Blend in blender until smooth.
In medium saucepan, combine blended mixture with ginger juice.
Combine cream and potato juice and add to soup mixture.
Heat just to boiling, then simmer until soup thickens, about 5 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Season with salt and white pepper to taste.
Garnish with chives or dill.
Serves 4.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Add the dry spaghetti sauce mix and tomato sauce to the browned and drained hamburger and simmer for 20 minutes. Put in 9 x 13 pan. Put the Mozzarella cheese over meat mixture. Put the crescent rolls over that. Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: country chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain and add chopped onions.
Saute until onions are tender.
Pour into a large cooker and add all the other ingredients.
Cook on medium heat for about 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon twist
directions: Roll biscuits into ropes.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Roll biscuit rolls into sugar mixture, then melted butter, then sugar mixture.
Roll twists to form circle in baking dish.
Sprinkle with nuts (optional).
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Add milk, vanilla and peanuts; mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto buttered cookie sheet or waxed paper.

title: strawberry supreme
directions: Prepare pastry shells as directed on package.
Cool on wire rack.
In a small bowl, blend softened ice cream until smooth. Fold in pie filling and whipped topping. Spoon 1/2 cup mixture into each patty shell. Serve immediately with fresh strawberries.

title: salami
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate, covered.
Mix again each
day for 2 more days. On the fourth day, mix again and form into rolls approximately 2 1/2 inches in diameter and 6 inches long.
Place on rack over a drip pan to catch grease. Bake at 150° for 10
hours.
Be
sure
oven
is not too hot or salami gets crusty on
the
outside.
The
meat turns red when cooking.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Brown beef and drain off fat.
Mix in all other ingredients. Bring to a boil, then simmer for 30 minutes, stirring often.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Buy pizza crust or make your own.
Roll out on pan.
Bake pizza crust until brown.
Then let cool, cut pizza into sections. Mix 1/2 package party dip mix with 1 pint sour cream (makes enough for 2 pizzas).
Spread pizza entirely with dip mixture.
Top with shredded lettuce, fresh chopped broccoli, fresh mushrooms, diced tomatoes, diced cucumbers and cauliflower.
Then top with Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese.

title: dilly green beans
directions: Combine the salad dressing, green beans and celery in a nonstick skillet.
Cover and cook until the beans are fully thawed, separating them with a fork as they cook.
Add onions and dill; continue cooking for about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, just until the vegetables are tender, but still crisp.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sausage dip
directions: In a double boiler, melt cheese.
Meanwhile, brown onion and sausage.
Drain and crumble.
To melted Velveeta cheese, add vanilla and soup.
When mixed well, add meat and jalapeno relish. Serve warm.

title: spinach roll
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients.
Spread
on flour tortillas and roll.
Refrigerate overnight in a covered container.
Slice in 1-inch pieces and serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar, margarine, pudding mix and eggs.
Then add bananas, then flour and flavoring.
Beat together.
Fold in nuts. Put in 2 (9 1/2 x 5 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Bake 45 minutes or until done in 350° oven.
You can keep this bread up to 6 months in your freezer.
If your kids love raisins, why not add a cup for them. They'll love you for it.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Adjust oven racks to divide oven into thirds.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray 5-cup loaf pan, Bundt or tube pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In small bowl, whisk together flour, baking powder, soda and salt; sift together and set aside.
Whisk together egg and egg whites; set aside.
Combine buttermilk and vanilla; set aside.
Cut margarine and butter into 1/4-inch chunks and place in large bowl.
With electric mixer, mix at medium speed until softened, about 1 minute.
Add sugar gradually, beating constantly until smooth, about 3 minutes.
Gradually dribble in beaten eggs, beating at medium-high speed for 2 to 3 minutes.
On low speed, beat in 1/3 of reserved flour mixture, scraping sides of bowl.
On medium-high speed, gradually dribble in 1/2 buttermilk mixture scraping sides of bowl.
On low speed, beat in half the remaining flour mixture scraping sides of bowl.

On low speed, beat in remaining flour mixture until well combined (batter may look slightly curdled). Pour into prepared pan and bake for 35 to 40 minutes in Bundt or tube pan or 65 to 70 minutes in loaf pan or until cake starts to pull away from sides of pan, top is golden brown and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on rack 10 to 15 minutes; invert pan and unmold on rack to cool completely.
Cut into 12 slices.

title: cranberry upside-down cake
directions: Grease a 9-inch round 1 1/2-inch deep pan.
Sprinkle first 1/2 cup sugar in bottom of pan.
Pour cranberries in next.
Cream butter and remaining 1/2 cup sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and orange rind.
Mix in salt, baking powder and flour alternately with milk. Pour over cranberries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool for 20 minutes.
Run knife around edges.
Invert.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together meal, onion, corn, peppers, eggs and oil.
Mix well.
Pour half of mixture in greased skillet.
Put cheese over it, then pour remaining over cheese.
Cook in 425° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pear honey
directions: Mix coarse ground pears and sugar; cook in a large kettle until thick.
Add crushed pineapple; cook until thick.
Add 1 can coconut and mix well.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes 10 pints.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Boil macaroni and drain.
In a separate pan, melt and mix butter with flour and Lawry's salt.
Add milk and stir until it boils.
Let boil one minute, then add shredded Cheddar cheese and Lawry's salt.
Mix well with macaroni in a casserole dish.
Top with seasoned bread crumbs, cover completely. Bake uncovered for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Lay
one
layer
in bottom of punch bowl; if it doesn't fit, cut
to fit and save the rest of layer to fill in as bowl widens. Drain
pineapple and lay half of can over layer.
Fix vanilla pudding
according to directions on package and cover pineapple. Layer
bananas and strawberries (if not available, may
substitute 1
can
fruit
cocktail),
layer pie filling, coconut,
pecans and top with Cool Whip.
Put next cake layer and
repeat
the process,
except
I cover the Cool Whip with pecans on the top.

title: sauerkraut
directions: Cut up bacon and fry.
Add chopped onion to bacon and brown. Rinse and drain sauerkraut.
Add to browned bacon and onion mix. Keep turning sauerkraut until brown.
Add wine, water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Slowly simmer over low heat for 3/4 hours.
Cut up kielbasi and add to sauerkraut mix.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over mashed potatoes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine salmon, drained and flaked, with all other ingredients.
Pack into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix
boiling
water
and oatmeal; let stand 20 minutes. Mix shortening, brown sugar, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon,
salt
and
oatmeal
mixture.
Mix
well.
Bake
30 minutes in 350° oven
in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan lightly sprayed with Pam.

title: jansson's temptation(janssons frestelse)
directions: Saute the onions in 1 tablespoon butter until soft.
Peel potatoes and slice lengthwise thinly, as for shoestring potatoes. Butter baking dish, layer potatoes, onions and anchovies, finishing with a layer of potatoes.
Dot with remaining butter. Bake at 400°, adding half of the cream after 10 minutes.
Add the remainder of the cream after another 10 minutes.
After 30 minutes, reduce the heat to 300° and bake for another 30 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix altogether; put into pie shell and chill.

title: white sauce icing
directions: Stir milk and flour over heat until thick.
Let cool.
Put all other ingredients in mixer and blend.
Add cooled cream sauce and beat until fluffy.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook noodles. In saucepan over low heat, melt butter; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk until thickened.
Remove from heat, add cheese and stir until melted. Add remaining ingredients, except butter and crumbs.
Put into casserole.
Top with butter and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crumbs are brown.

title: icee delights
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and sugar.
Add water and stir thoroughly. Add ginger
ale
and
stir
again.
Pour
into	blender.
Add crushed ice and blend on high until ice is thoroughly blended. Enjoy!

title: last garden supper
directions: Mix all ingredients in one large skillet.
Fry until potatoes are done.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake potatoes 45 minutes or until fork-tender.
With sharp knife, holding potato in clean potholder, slice lengthwise the top fourth from each potato. With spoon, carefully spoon out potatoes to form six shells.
Scrape potato from top quarters and discard tops.
In a large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat potatoes, butter, salt and pepper until fluffy. Slowly add milk, beating until smooth.
Pile mashed potato mixture back into shells.
Sprinkle generously with a topping.
Place potatoes on cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 6 servings.

title: wild wild rice
directions: In a small skillet, saute green pepper and onion in 1 tablespoon butter until crisp-tender; set aside.
In a large saucepan, bring the water, rice and remaining butter to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir in the chicken, soup, green beans, water chestnuts, carrot, mayonnaise and green pepper mixture.
Transfer to a greased 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese if desired. Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until heated through.
Yield: 6 to 8 minutes.

title: party mints
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Combine with sugar and peppermint extract in food processor, using steel blade.
Batter will be very stiff.
Divide batter and beat the desired color into each half. Pinch off enough dough to make marble size balls.
Roll in your hand and place balls in a single layer on a tray.
Air dry 30 minutes.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat thoroughly after each addition.
Add salt, soda and spices to the flour and sift again.
Add alternately with applesauce to egg mixture.
Beat well.
Add a sprinkling of flour to the fruit, raisins and nuts; blend in.
Fold into batter.
Bake in tube pan for 2 hours at 300°.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Grease and flour 15 x 10-inch pan.
In a large bowl combine cake mix, pie filling, almond extract and beaten eggs.
Stir by hand until well mixed; pour in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Cool.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate.
May use a couple of slices of beef to wrap cheese ball, if desired.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into small pieces.
Add to water the ham seasoning, margarine/butter, sugar and salt and pepper.
Then add potatoes and chopped onions.
Bring to boil.
Simmer until potatoes are tender.
Slightly mash potatoes with potato masher.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Dissolve soup mix in the warm water.
Mix meat, eggs, ketchup, soup mix and Accent well.
Put in a loaf pan, and cover with bacon.
Top with tomato sauce, and bake in a 350° oven for approximately 1 3/4 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze dry.
Mix with other ingredients. Refrigerate.
Tastes better if mixed several hours before needed.

title: potato salad
directions: In a large pot, cover the potatoes with water and add the salt. Boil until potatoes are tender when pierced with a fork, but do not overcook. Chop the potatoes into cubes. Put the chopped potatoes, eggs, onions, pimentos, sweet pickles, celery and celery seed in a large bowl. Mix together mayonnaise, mustard and vinegar; stir until smooth. Pour mixture over the chopped vegetables and gently fold to coat. Chill several hours or overnight before serving.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute
onions in margarine in skillet, add salt.
Layer cracker
crumbs,
onions
and
cheese in greased 8-inch baking dish.
Pour evaporated milk over top.
Sprinkle with remaining cracker
crumbs.
Bake
at	350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: strawberry trifle by billie childs
directions: Put fruit in sugar overnight.
Slice cake 3 times in a large bowl.
Alternate layers of cake, pudding, cake, pudding, cake, pudding.
Let pudding and cake set in refrigerator overnight so pudding can set up good, then strawberries on top when ready to serve.

title: chinese eggrolls
directions: Heat sesame oil in large skillet.
Quickly cook bean sprout over high heat, stirring constantly.
Add 4 fresh mushrooms chopped, water chestnuts, and cook approximately 2 minutes.
Add meat, onions, salt, pepper, soy sauce and sugar. Set aside to cool.

title: chicken casserole #1
directions: Boil chicken breast for one hour.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook chicken.
Cut up and pull from bone.
Place chicken in bottom of casserole.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Mix crackers with butter and spread over top.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine flour, soda, sugar and oil. Add yeast to warm water. Add to flour mixture and mix well.
May be kept in refrigerator and used when needed for two weeks.

title: korean barbecued  beef
directions: Mix all ingredients but rump roast to make sauce. Marinate beef for several hours or longer in the sauce. Barbecue or broil in oven and serve immediately.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 1 cup hot water.
Cool until jelly-like.
Beat cream cheese and pineapple.
Fold cream and sugar in just before folding in Jell-O.
Let set a few hours.

title: aunt ruth's oyster crackers
directions: Mix dill weed, garlic powder and lemon pepper together in a plastic bag. Add package of Hidden Valley ranch salad dressing mix. Shake bag several times. Add bag of oyster crackers. Shake and coat. Add salad oil. Shake. Let stand 2 hours, shaking occasionally.

title: dazzling dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Place cabbage in greased baking dish. Add onion. Mix soup, mayonnaise, salt and pepper. Spread mixture on top of cabbage and onions. Add cracker crumbs and cheese. Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes.

title: oreo pie
directions: Crumble 12 Oreos in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cook chips and butter slowly in saucepan to melt chips.
Add eggs and cook 1 minute. Remove from heat, beat in sugar with a mixer.
Pour mixture over cookies.
Freeze until hard.
Remove, spread softened ice cream on top.
Sprinkle Oreos on top.
Re-freeze.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a large glass bowl, layer lettuce, celery, onion, pepper and peas.
Spread mayonnaise to the edges of the bowl, covering peas.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Top with crumbled bacon and cheese. Cover tightly and refrigerate at least 6 hours before serving.

title: brussels sprouts with hazelnuts
directions: Place hazelnuts in a small baking pan and toast in a 350° oven 10 minutes.
Cool slightly and place in a kitchen towel.
Rub together to remove the skins and chop finely.
Set aside.

title: spinach pecan salad
directions: Toss mushrooms with salad dressing.
Set aside.
Remove stems from spinach; wash leaves thoroughly and pat dry.
Tear into bite size pieces.
Combine spinach, mushrooms, raisins and pecans in a bowl.
Toss gently.
Grate egg over salad.
Serves 4.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Split loaf of bread lengthwise.
Cut or scoop out bread from center of each piece.

title: chicken-broccoli bake
directions: Prepare in one 9 x 13-inch baking dish or two 8 x 8-inch dishes.
Melt margarine in a large pan and stir in crumbs until well mixed.
Divide into 2 portions (4 for two 8 x 8-inch pans). Spread one portion in bottom of baking dish, cover with chicken and broccoli which has been tossed together.
Sprinkle with pepper and parsley.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Put milk and lemon juice in bowl.
Mix well.
Then put rest of ingredients and mix good.
Then put in ready-baked or graham cracker pie crust.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Makes 2 pies; delicious.

title: beans and beef
directions: Soak the beans in enough water to cover overnight.
Simmer the beans in the water in which they soaked for about 20 minutes. Drain the beans, reserving the water.
Heat the oil in a large saucepan and salt the onions.
Add the meat and cook until the meat is browned.
Mix the honey, salt, pepper and mustard with the reserved bean water.
Add beans to meat.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender.

title: biscuits supreme
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder, cream of tartar and sugar. Cut in shortening.
Add milk and mix.
Pat 1/2 inch thick and cut. Bake on ungreased baking sheet in hot oven at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican stack-ups
directions: Brown ground beef.
Spoon off fat.
Add onion, soups, enchilada sauce mix and water; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Cut tortillas in half and line bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan with them, then add 1/3 of meat mixture.
Layer more tortillas and meat mixture, ending with meat on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Add cheese and heat until melted.

title: cold oven cake
directions: Place in a cold oven.
(Be sure not to turn oven on until after cake is placed in oven.)
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Cook 5
minutes.
Take
off stove and add 4 tablespoons butter.
Pour
over
sweet potatoes and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Baste while cooking.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in blender.
Slowly add oil, blending until thick.
Stir in poppy seed.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
(Let set at least 3 days.
The longer it sets, the better it is!)

title: easy cake
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and butter and press into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Top with chocolate chips and nuts. Mix powdered sugar, remaining 3 eggs and cream cheese. Pour over cake mix base. Bake at 350° until bubbly and golden, about 30 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Drop by tablespoonful onto wax paper.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13 dish, mix all ingredients except 1/2 of the onions. Bake at 375° until asparagus is tender.
Stir and top with remaining onions.
For extra crisp.
Bake 5 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and canned milk in a saucepan on medium heat.
When it starts to boil, time 5 minutes.
Take it off heat. Put in the rest of ingredients.
Grease pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Pour fudge into pan.

title: easy chicken and noodles
directions: Mix soup and water. Pour over chicken and bake until done. Cook egg noodles; drain.
Arrange chicken and soup over noodles.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cream 2 sticks butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Heat milk to very hot and let cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in milk (mix) and add to the creamed butter, sugar and egg.
With spoon, gradually add flour.
Set aside and let rise.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and 1/2 stick butter; melt, stirring to combine.
Spread on bottom of pan.
Arrange peaches over brown sugar in circles.

title: puppy chow
directions: Mix Crispix and peanuts; set aside.
Melt together chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter.
Pour the chocolate mixture over the Crispix and peanuts; mix well.
Measure powdered sugar and pour into a large brown grocery bag.
Add cereal and shake well until all sugar coats cereal.
Spread out on cookie sheet to cool and dry.
Makes enough to fill 5-quart
ice cream pail.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add flour, vanilla and pecans; mix well.
Shape into crescents.
If can't shape, add a little more flour.
Bake on ungreased sheet at 325° for 15 or 20 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: benne wafers(cookies)
directions: Cream together butter and sugar in large bowl. Add egg and vanilla and mix well. Add flour and benne seed, mixing well after each addition. Divide dough into 6 equal parts. Roll each into a cylinder 1 inch in diameter. Wrap in aluminum foil. Freeze until ready to bake. Preheat oven to 325°. Line baking sheets with foil. Slice the frozen dough thin and bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes. Let the wafers cool thoroughly before removing them from the foil. Makes 4 dozen.

title: beet jelly
directions: Bring to boil all ingredients, except sugar.
Add the sugar; boil for 6 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Slice cookie dough and lay on a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Press dough evenly in pan using floured fingers. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg together until light and fluffy. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add this to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Beat until smooth.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour gradually and mix well.
Stir in potato chips.
Drop by tablespoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Sort through beans, picking out and throwing away the bad ones. Put beans in pressure cooker pot and cover with water 2 inches above beans.
Bring to a boil.
Shut off burner and let beans sit for an hour.
Drain water and add fresh water to an inch above beans.
Add garlic, onion, seasonings, meat and 3 tablespoons Crisco shortening.
Cover with lid and cook on 15 pounds of pressure for 20 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.
Add some cornbread for a delicious Southern meal.

title: olive dip
directions: Cream cheese.
Add garlic and chopped olives.
Mix well. Gradually add enough milk for consistency.
Add dash of salt and pepper.
Best made a day in advance.
Remove from refrigerator about 1 hour before serving.
Also good as filling for tea sandwiches.

title: drop cookies
directions: Mix together fructose, melted butter, oats and peanut butter; stir to a boil. Add rest of ingredients; stirring to keep from sticking. Blend well. Spoon small drops on wax paper and press. Let cool before serving.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Melt butter and let cool.
Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, milk and salt to eggs.
Add butter and pineapple. Cut bread into cubes with steak knife.
Toss into pineapple mixture lightly. Butter bottom of casserole dish.
Pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Broil lightly, if needed.
This dish is especially good served with a baked ham.

title: deviled green beans
directions: Combine seasoning mix and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil; stir until sauce is thickened.
Add tomato paste.
Drain beans; add to seasoning mixture.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Press crescent rolls in sheet cake pan. Bake according to directions on roll packaging. Cool completely. Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise, onion, dill and garlic powder.
Spread on cooled rolls. Chop desired vegetables (broccoli, cauliflower, radishes, celery, green onion with tops, etc.). Put on top of cream cheese mixture. Top with grated cheese.

title: noodles
directions: Beat egg yolks, whip until fluffy.
Stir in Crisco, cream, salt, baking powder and flour.
Usually have to add more milk until soft dough, but not sticky.
Roll out very thin, roll up like jelly roll and slice very thin.
Cook for 20 minutes.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Use cherry juice in making the jello.
When cooled, pour over the drained cherries.
Add halved pecans (as many as you wish). Also, add small Philadelphia cream cheese balls (if you wish).

title: corn chowder
directions: Mix potatoes, celery, onion and water.
Bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Panfry and drain bacon.
Add remaining ingredients to cooked vegetables.
Heat for a minute and put bacon pieces on top.
Serve while hot.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning with water; bring to a boil.
Turn down heat.
Add refried beans; simmer.
Mix soup, sour cream and chilies in a bowl.
Spread thin layer in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place small spoonful of meat mixture and one of sour cream mixture on tortilla; fold and place in pan, seam side down.
Repeat until pan is full.
Usually 20 to 24 tortillas will fit.
Place remaining meat and sour cream mixtures on top.
Bake at 375° with foil on top for 30 to 45 minutes, or until bubbly.
Sprinkle with cheese last 5 minutes to melt.

title: blackberry jam
directions: Mix Sure-Jell with berries in saucepan.
Bring mixture to boil, stirring occasionally.
Add sugar and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Cool and serve on slice of bread.
MMM!!

title: shrimp salad
directions: If shrimp are large, cut into bite size pieces. Add remaining ingredients and toss lightly.

title: old-fashion beef stew
directions: Cook meat until tender.
Cut up in small pieces.
Put meat back in liquid.
Then add cooked vegetables and rest of ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix crackers with 1/2 cup sugar and pecans.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla; mix with cracker mixture.
Put into a 9-inch greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with whipped cream and shaved chocolate or chocolate bits.

title: dirgie's pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. In a large bowl, beat the eggs well by hand. Add the remaining ingredients one at a time, stirring well after each addition.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake approximately 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until mixture is set in the middle.

title: greatest fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine well.
Add all other ingredients gradually.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Preheat oven to 300°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in preheated oven. Makes 7 to 8 dozen cookies.

title: miss ida's cranberry salad
directions: Put cranberries and apple (plus skin, minus core) in a blender. Add sugar.
Let stand while preparing remainder of ingredients. Put gelatin in 1/2 cup water and set over boiling water to dissolve.
Drain juice from pulp of orange and pineapple.
Measure juice and add enough water to make 1 cup.
Pour into gelatin mix. Add fruit and nuts.
Pour into an 8 x 10-inch cake pan or mold. Refrigerate until firm.
Freezes well.
Serve with turkey or ham.

title: holubby casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Cut up cabbage. Brown meat; drain.
Mix with rice, egg, onion and salt.
Mix tomato sauce and brown sugar.
Place meat, cabbage and sauce in alternating layers in a casserole.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer.
Uncover and brown top about 10 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound flour into cube steaks until very flat.
Fry quickly in hot oil; brown on both sides.
Put in small roaster; add tomato juice and chopped onion.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Wash, pare and slice potatoes.
Cook with carrots in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Saute bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Saute onion and celery in 2 tablespoons of bacon fat. Combine all ingredients, except cheese and parsley.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Garnish with Cheddar cheese and parsley.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Combine cake mix and eggs in mixer bowl; beat well.
Add cherry pie filling; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until cake tests done. Cool in pan for several minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 16 servings.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in a large casserole dish as listed.
Cover casserole and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: confetti cake
directions: Slice cake into 3 layers.
Cream cheese and sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Add Hershey bars, cherries and pecans. Fold in Cool Whip.
Frost each layer and sides.
Refrigerate.
May be frozen.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid per package instructions.
Add juice and Sweet 'N Low or sugar to taste.
Makes almost a gallon of punch.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10-inch quiche or pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inches.
Cook and stir beef and onion over medium heat until beef is brown; drain, stir in taco season mix.
Spread in plate. Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand mixer.
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife
inserted between center and edge comes out clean, 8 to 10 minutes longer.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serve with sour cream, chopped tomatoes, lettuce and shredded cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sticky buns
directions: Put rolls in pan. Sprinkle pudding over and a little cinnamon over them. Melt margarine and brown sugar and cook until blended well. Pour over rolls and let stand until morning. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Take out and let sit for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: italian pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Trim chops of excess fat.
Sprinkle with seasoning salt and pepper.
Saute until brown in pan, draining fat as it collects.
Place chops in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Arrange mushrooms around chops.
Set aside.
In another skillet, saute in salad oil the onions, garlic and pepper strips until golden brown.
Add tomato sauce, salt, pepper, bay leaf, lemon juice and sage.
Simmer covered until vegetables are fork-tender. Pour sauce over chops and bake 1 hour covered.

title: glazed kielbasa
directions: Cut kielbasa on bias 1/4-inch.
Place in a large saute pan. Mix other ingredients except wine.
Pour over kielbasa; at high heat, simmer close to 10 minutes, until glaze forms.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Splash in wine during last few minutes.
Serve in a large bowl.
Can be served with party dark rye bread.

title: my favorite corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Arrange buttered bread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan or dish. Layer with sausage and cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients in bowl and pour over cheese.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Freeze for later.)

title: peppy popcorn
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir together butter and seasonings.
Pour over popcorn mixture.
Toss to coat.
Makes 11 cups.

title: farmhouse cabbage slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, raisins, apple, celery and onion.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and melted butter.
Add beaten eggs and pecans to mixture.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken auq vin
directions: Brown chicken pieces.
Mix cream of mushroom soup with cooking sherry.
Put chicken on bottom of pan.
Put uncooked noodles on top of the chicken.
Pour soup and sherry over all.
If cooked in oven, cook at 300° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
If cooked in crock-pot, cook for 1 hour at medium heat and 5 hours at low setting.
This makes the chicken so tender that the bones will "melt" in the crock-pot, so take care when serving.

title: sauce for cole slaw
directions: Mix well.
Keeps up to 8 days in refrigerator.

title: haystack
directions: 1st Layer:
Beans, taco seasoning and taco sauce to taste.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs together.
Stir in flour until smooth and add vanilla.
Stir.
Pour into a tube pan and bake at 300° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: onion-smothered steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Pound into meat.
Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Brown meat in hot oil.
Top with onion slices; stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour or longer.
Remove bay leaf.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip ingredients together, using hand mixer, adding sweetened condensed milk until desired consistency.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Saute garlic until brown in medium saucepan.
Add onion, chicken, vinegar, soy sauce and oyster sauce.
Cover; cook until tender.
Sauce will thicken.
Halfway between cooking, taste mixture.
Add additional vinegar, soy sauce or oyster sauce as needed to own liking.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Clean peppers and remove stems.
Cut a little off nose so they will stand on end.
Steam for 10 minutes.

title: kangaroo pancakes
directions: Mix meat, onion and sauted mushrooms together with sour cream and Worcestershire sauce.
Make pancake batter.
Follow directions on the box, but use enough milk to make it thin enough for crepes. The batter should look like thin cream.
Use about 1/4 cup for each pancake.
Fry in medium skillet.
Turn each cooked pancake out onto plate and fill with about 2 to 3 tablespoons of meat mixture.
Roll up crepe style and serve garnished with lettuce.

title: taco bake
directions: Place biscuits in casserole dish with sides touching.
In a skillet, brown ground beef, add taco seasoning and 3/4 cup water. Simmer.
Spread taco meat over biscuits.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Melt 1/4 cup butter in heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour.
Stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk and half and half.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Add cheese and herbs, stirring until cheese melts.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Mix soda and boiling water and cool in a large bowl.
Add buttermilk.
Cream together shortening, sugar, eggs and salt.
Add flour alternately with the liquid.
Then add cereals and dates, raisins or nuts.
Keep batter covered in refrigerator.
Bake as needed. Keeps for 3 weeks.
Put in muffin tins, greased, 3/4 full. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: *lime fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 1 1/4 cups cold water or ice cubes and vinegar.
Chill until thickened.
Fold fruits into 1 1/2 cups thickened gelatin; spoon into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Chill until set, but not firm (about 15 minutes).

title: copper penny salad
directions: Combine condensed tomato soup, sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and dry mustard.
In saucepan, bring to a boil.
Pour the hot dressing over vegetables in large bowl; marinate 24 hours before serving. Serve hot or cold.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 12 to 20 people.

title: french pancakes
directions: Add sugar and salt to the slightly beaten eggs.
Alternately add the flour and milk and then beat thoroughly with beater.
Heat medium size frying pan with about a tablespoon of shortening. When very hot, take a tablespoon of batter to thinly coat the pan. Fry until golden brown, about 2 minutes, then turn over.
Serve rolled up with blueberries, strawberries, preserves, etc.

title: party chicken a-la-aunt jean
directions: Use enough chipped beef to cover bottom of casserole dish. (I usually scald half of beef to remove salt, otherwise dish will be too salty.
This can be done by pouring boiling water over beef, then alternate layers of scalded and not scalded beef in casserole.)
Wrap each half chicken breast in 1 slice of bacon and place on beef.
Mix equal parts sour cream and soup and cover chicken.
You may wish to use 1/2 slice bacon due to its saltiness.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
This can be made ahead and saved to reheat for the last 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Combine first four ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and let cool.
Then add beaten egg and remaining ingredients.
Beat with a spoon.
Spread on jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool and frost.
Sprinkle with nuts and cut into squares.

title: sparkling fruit slush punch (non-alcoholic drink)
directions: Mix ingredients and freeze overnight.
Remove from freezer just before serving.
Stir well.
(Keeps in freezer.)

title: perfect pancakes
directions: Mix all together.
For camping, use powdered buttermilk.
Put all ingredients together then add 1 cup water and oil when ready to make.

title: red-eye gravy
directions: After frying a slice of country ham, drain off excess fat.
Add water to the drippings and strong coffee for color.
Bring to a boil and serve with the ham.

title: seafoam cookies
directions: Beat on high egg whites, vanilla, and cream of tartar until stiff.
Gradually add sugar and salt.
Stir in chips gently.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: berry meringue pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine egg whites, almond extract and baking powder.
Let mixture stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.

title: cajun beans
directions: Brown vegetables in oil; add remaining ingredients.
Let simmer in crock-pot 2 to 4 hours.
This is a spicy hot dish.
But excellent for those who want to brave it.

title: apple butter bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.	Combine eggs, apple butter, margarine and apple juice.
Add to flour mixture. Blend well.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: enchiladas acapulco
directions: Brown meat, drain if needed.
Add tomato sauce and 1/2 cup peppers.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add beans and 1/4 pound cheese, continue cooking until melted.
Fill tortillas with 1/4 cup meat mixture, roll up, placing seam side down in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining meat mixture, cover, bake 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and bake uncovered 5 to 8 minutes.
Top with remaining peppers and tomatoes.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Put zucchini, onions and peppers in a large container and sprinkle with 1/2 cup coarse salt.
Cover with 4 trays of ice cubes and let stand 3 to 4 hours.

title: layered crab dip(servings:  8)
directions: In shallow 2-quart dish, spread cream cheese over bottom. Cover with green pepper, green onions and olives.
Spread chili sauce over this.
Sprinkle cheeses on top and mix slightly with chili sauce on top.
Sprinkle crab meat over all.
Serve with crackers.

title: quick bread sticks
directions: Cut each biscuit into thirds.
Roll each piece into a 4-inch stick.
Combine cereal and salt.
Roll each stick in milk and then in cereal.
Place on baking sheet and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: cheese danish
directions: Cream the cheese and sugar.
Add egg yolk, vanilla and lemon juice.
Spread one package of rolls on bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan. Spread cheese mixture over rolls and layer the next package of rolls on top of cheese mixture.
Brush rolls with egg white and one tablespoon of water.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: won ton
directions: Cook bean sprouts in boiling water until tender; drain and chop.
Add to raw ground beef.
Add to mixture the onions, egg, salt, pepper and Accent.
Sprinkle mixture lightly with soy sauce and mix well.
Place about a level teaspoonful in won ton skin. Fold in half like a triangle, wetting sides of skin with water to hold them closed.
Fold sides toward center like a diaper.
Pinch together to seal.
Dip in flour and deep fry until each side is a light brown.
Place on Scott towel to drain.
Serve warm with soy sauce or sweet and sour.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cube bread in bottom of a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Spread grated cheese over bread.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and melted butter.
Use mixer or blender.
Pour mixture over bread and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
You may add chipped ham or bacon before putting on the cheese, if you wish.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add syrup, sugar, salt and softened margarine.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell and bake at 325° for one hour.

title: italian sausage sauce(for quick spinach and sausage lasagna)
directions: In large saucepan, heat oil.
Add sausage and cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring to break up meat, until lightly browned.
Pour off and discard fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Use in Quick Spinach and Sausage Lasagna.
Makes 8 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender, save broth and remove skin and bones.
Cut chicken into small pieces and arrange in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over chicken.
Then fill soup can with milk and add to chicken.
Take Stove Top stuffing and mix well with chicken broth until moist.
Put Stove Top over top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: hallingdals cream bread(hallingdals romme brod)
directions: Mix flour and butter as for a pie crust.
Add sugar and cream and mix well.
More flour may be needed to make a stiff dough. Take a tablespoon of dough and roll as you do lefse (thin pancake shape).
Sprinkle with sugar while rolling.
Bake on lefse grill on medium heat until light brown.
A pancake grill may be used in place of lefse grill.

title: giant raisin bran cookies
directions: Stir together Raisin Bran cereal, flours and baking soda.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat margarine, sugar and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add flour mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by level 1/4 cup measure onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 14 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: corn taco shells(tortillas)
directions: Combine the Masa Harina and warm water, mixing until dough forms ball.
If dough is dry, add a little water.
Wet hands; shape into approximately 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place 1 ball between 2 sandwich size plastic bags or 2 sheets of plastic wrap in a tortilla/taco press; press to form a 6-inch circle.
Carefully peel off bags.
Place into hot grease-filled pan.
Poke holes in tortillas (3 hits with a fork) as they are frying.
Turn and continue cooking 30 seconds.
Makes six 6-inch tortillas.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain.
Then in a casserole dish, layer ground beef, Cheddar cheese and powdered gravy mix.
Top with Tater Tots and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: super bowl sandwich
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Slice a loaf of French bread longways.
Put filling on bread; top with the top of bread over the filling mixture. Wrap in aluminum foil. Bake for one half hour.
Cut into slices and serve.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add onion and tomato (chopped); saute. Drain grease.
Add spaghetti spices.
Follow directions to make sauce.
Prepare noodles; drain water.
Lightly grease a baking dish; place a layer of at least 2 deep noodles.
Cook spinach according to package directions; drain water.
Mix with the Ricotta cheese.
Spread this mixture over layer of noodles; top with another layer.
Pour on spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle generous layer of Cheddar cheese.
After Cheddar cheese, put the final layer of noodles. Top with layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes, until lightly browned on top.
Let stand for about 10 minutes before serving.

title: dried beef spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Chop dried beef fine. Moisten onion flakes. Chop bell pepper fine. Mix all ingredients. Place in baking dish to be served in. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve warm with mixed crackers.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix together sugar, oleo, syrup and salt; cook, stirring constantly at medium heat until it spins a thread.
Add peanuts and cook again until light golden brown.
Remove from heat.
Add the soda and stir thoroughly.
It will be bubbly and airy.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet, spread out and cool.
Break and enjoy.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients and beat until fluffy.
Add egg and beat.
Add flour, soda, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Drop cookies in ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: grilled hawaiian chicken
directions: Overnight, marinate chicken in teriyaki sauce. Spread a little mayonnaise on each side of each piece of chicken.
Grill chicken and pineapple for about 20 minutes (medium to low heat).
Serve with any other desirable dishes.

title: corned beef barbecue
directions: Simmer the first 4 ingredients until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until desired thickness.
Serve on buns.

title: italian skillet chicken
directions: Mix flour and cheese together in plastic bag. Take chicken and put in bag; coat chicken with mixer. Put olive oil in frypan and brown the chicken and then add onions and can of tomatoes; simmer for about 20 minutes. Can serve with pasta. While simmering, make pasta.

title: chinese egg drop soup
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together chicken broth and cornstarch.
Stir in frozen vegetables.
Cook, covered, on High in the microwave for 4 minutes, stirring once.
Cook, covered again, for about 4 minutes or until bubbly.
Stir; cook, covered, for 2 minutes more.
Pour egg into hot soup; stir once.
Serve immediately.
Ladle soup into soup bowls.
Makes 4 side-dish servings.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Place flour in large plastic food storage bag. Add a few pieces of chicken; shake to coat. Remove chicken from bag and repeat with remaining chicken. Heat vegetable oil in a large skillet. Add chicken. Brown over medium high heat. Remove chicken from skillet; set aside. Add onion, green pepper and garlic to skillet. Saute over moderate heat until tender. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, mushrooms, salt, oregano and pepper, stirring to break apart tomatoes. Place chicken pieces on top of tomato mixture. Cover. Reduce heat. Simmer 40 to 50 minutes or until chicken is tender and meat near bone in no longer pink. Serve with noodles.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Seal and put in 175 degree oven for 1 hour. Last 10 minutes turn oven off.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix
sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat.
Add dry ingredients and
vanilla.
Blend well.	Add apples and nuts.
Pour into
a greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Top with caramel frosting.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt margarine; add flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture boils and thickens.
Makes 1 cup.

title: mexican turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in oiled loaf pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: heavenly pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour in pie shells.
Chill until firm.

title: cooked raisin cookies
directions: Boil the water and raisins for 5 minutes; let cool.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Pour boiling water over jello. Cool and add fruits and nuts. Refrigerate to jell.
Sour cream or Cool Whip may be spread over jello after jelling if desired.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Fry bacon (chopped) in skillet; remove and drain.
To bacon fat, add onion, potatoes, salt and boiling water.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes.
Add broccoli that was cooked in 1 cup water until well done and mashed fine or has been pureed in blender.
Simmer for 5 minutes.

title: festive christmas punch
directions: Put ice in punch bowl.
Pour apricot brandy and rum over it. Boil orange juice, lemon juice and sugar together; mix well.
Pour over ice. Add the soda, 7-Up, grenadine and lime juice.
Slice the lemon, lime and orange very thin and add to punch.
Let sit several hours to ripen.
Just before serving, pour in champagne. Makes about 2 gallons.

title: beef goulash(makes 4 large servings)
directions: Brown beef; add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is yellow. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, mushrooms, basil, oregano, parsley, pepper and instant beef bouillon.
At this time, you can cut the tomatoes in the pan with the spatula.
Boil macaroni; drain and add to meat mixture; stir in cheeses, saving thin slices for top layer as it is a good idea to stir once during baking.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 325°, the last 10 minutes uncovered with cheese slices and topping.

title: chocolate frogs
directions: Melt chips in double boiler.
Add peanuts and Rice Krispies and mix well.
Put on cookie sheet covered with wax paper.
Spoon as large as you wish.
Put in refrigerator to chill, about 1/2 hour.

title: string bean dressing
directions: Push egg yolks through sieve.
Add mayonnaise and oil; stir. Add other ingredients.
Last, put egg whites through sieve.
Mix it all together.
Refrigerate.

title: not edible play dough
directions: Mix in saucepan.
Cook for 3 minutes or until mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
Knead until smooth.
Store in airtight container.

title: baked cauliflower
directions: Wash and trim cauliflower.
Smear margarine all over cauliflower and dip it into cracker crumbs.
Bake whole in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: beef roll-ups(appetizer)
directions: Combine and cream the mayo, cream cheese, garlic powder, onions and horseradish.
Spread mixture on dried beef slices and roll up.
Chill and serve.

title: thank you mix cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well. Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 60 minutes at 350°.
While cake is hot, pour on filling.

title: squash hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and add enough flour to meal to make batter thick enough to drop by teaspoons into hot grease.
Cook until golden brown.
These are very good and do not taste at all like squash!

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain and rinse artichokes.
Cut into pieces.
Mix with cheese, pepper and mayonnaise.
Pour into small crock and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Brown top.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: chicken legs teriyaki
directions: Place chicken in a shallow glass bowl.
Pour in mixture of soy sauce, honey, ginger, garlic and sherry.
Turn chicken to coat well with soy marinade.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Remove chicken from marinade.
Place on grill about 6-inches above glowing coals.
Cook until well browned on both sides, turning once, for approximately 30 to 40 minutes.
Garnish chicken with green onions and watercress or parsley.

title: mrs. murphy's soda bread
directions: Beat milk, eggs and soda together; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Add milk mixture and stir.
Dough will be very sticky.
Split between 2 buttered and floured round casserole dishes (1 1/2-quart size).
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool in pan 1/2 hour, then on rack.

title: cheese stuffed chicken
directions: Bone the chicken breasts.
Flatten each breast out using a meat hammer.
In a medium bowl, mix the cream cheese, chives and Cheddar cheese.
Place a blob of cheese on each breast (a little less than a tablespoon).
Fold the chicken breast over the cheese and wrap the bacon around it (forming a little package).
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.

title: stuffed bell pepper
directions: Cut bell peppers in half.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Place peppers in baking dish.
Mix in bowl the hamburger, onion, tomato sauce and rice.
Fill peppers.
Pour tomato sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with margarine over low heat.
Stir until blended.
Remove from heat.
Blend in milk.
Mix in sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Blend into chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie shell(s).
Combine coconut and nuts.
Sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Filling will set as it cools.
Cut after 4 hours.
(Cover loosely with foil the last 15 minutes in oven.)

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on package.
Let cool.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 1 cup of the croutons.
Saute mushrooms in small amount of butter.
Add celery, green peppers and onions; saute until slightly tender.
Add salt, pepper, soup and mayonnaise.
Stir and pour on top of croutons.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13 ungreased pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Spread with Cream Cheese Frosting (I use black walnuts).

title: daniel boulud's stuffed sweet onions
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Remove stems from spinach and chard; wash leaves well and blanch in boiling water for 1 minute.
Drain, plunge into cold water and drain again.
Squeeze out excess water or use a salad spinner.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Put the pie filling in a buttered 8-inch pan.
Combine dry ingredients and cut in butter.
Sprinkle over filling and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in a pan, add brown sugar and scatter it.
Lay sliced pineapples over brown sugar.
Mix cake mix and pour over the pineapples.
Bake at 350°.
Cool.

title: ronda's boiled chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa for 1 1/2 minutes after it reaches a full, rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add oats, vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until blended.
Drop on wax paper until cool.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups, 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch, or line with paper baking cups.
Mix flour, 1/2 cup sugar, the baking powder, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Stir in milk, butter, vanilla and egg just until blended.
Fold in blueberries (batter will be lumpy).
Divide batter evenly among muffin cups.
Sprinkle each muffin with 1/4 teaspoon sugar.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg yolks with sugar until nice and fluffy.
Add vanilla and other extracts.
Fold into beaten egg whites.
Beat whipping cream until whipped; fold in.
Add milk, stirring, until it's drinking consistency.

title: lobster newburg
directions: Heat lobster by frying slowly in butter for 3 minutes.
Add seasonings and heat 1 minute.
Add cream and slightly beaten egg yolks;
simmer 3 minutes more.
Add sherry and serve.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: confederate's old fashioned stack cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Add eggs and molasses.

Mix well. Add soda to buttermilk. Mix dry ingredients together. Add alternately with milk to batter, beginning and ending with the dry ingredients. Bake in thin layers (about 1/2 inch thick) in either 9-inch cake pans or the old-fashioned "black griddle" for about 12 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix and pat into a cake pan.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Melt jelly in chili sauce.
Combine remaining ingredients. Shape into small balls and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Place meatballs in crock-pot.
Cover with sauce and leave on low until serving.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Heat applesauce and soda together.
Set aside to cool.
Toss dates and raisins with 2 tablespoons of flour.
In a large bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
Add cooled applesauce and soda.
Mix at medium speed. Add raisins, nuts and dates.
Bake for 1 hour.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: chicken-broccoli-mushroom dish
directions: *May be made with asparagus in place of broccoli.

title: corn pudding
directions: First plant 3 rows of peas: 1 of perseverance, 2 of politeness and 3 of prayer.
Next plant 3 rows of squash: 1 squash gossip, 2 squash selfishness and 3 squash indifference, then plant 3 rows of lettuce: 1 let us be loyal, 2 let us be truthful and 3 let us love one another.
No garden is complete without turnips: 1 turn up for work, 2 turn up for church and 3 turn up with a smile.

title: apple squares
directions: Put into greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crisp cucumber pickles
directions: Soak cucumber in 2 gallons of water with lime for 24 hours. Remove from lime water and soak in clear water for 4 hours. Change water every hour.

title: doodle cake recipe
directions: Mix ingredients and bake at 350° for 25 minutes in an oblong pan.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef, celery and onion.
Drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up cabbage and steam for 12 minutes; drain well.
Mix cheese with milk and flour; add to cabbage.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Cream butter; add other ingredients.
Form into small finger shape cookies on cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 hour at 250° to 275°. Remove from oven and shake in bag containing enough powdered sugar to coat them.

title: basil carrots
directions: Simmer carrots just until tender.
Drain.
Add other ingredients to coat carrots.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: Melt morsels in a heavy pan over low heat with condensed milk, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients and spread in a wax paper-lined ;8-inch square pan. Chill 2 to 3 hours until firm.
Turn fudge out onto cutting board.
Peel off paper and cut into squares.
Cover tightly and store at room temperature.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients; work in shortening.
Add milk; knead 5 or 6 times.
Roll out.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes or until brown.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients; store in airtight jar.
Use 1 to 2 teaspoons for each cup of hot water.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients the day before serving and refrigerate. Serve with crackers or raw vegetables.

title: uncle brownie's rice dish
directions: Braise pork.
Add carrots and onions.
Cook until almost done. Add cabbage and cook until done.
Add 3 ounces soy sauce or to taste.
Add salt, m.s.g. and black pepper to taste.
Cook enough rice for 4 people.
Serve mixture over rice or mix with rice.

title: old-fashion bread pudding
directions: Scald milk with butter.
Heat oven to 350°.
Put bread crumbs in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Blend in remaining ingredients and stir.
Place baking dish in pan of hot water about 1-inch deep and bake for 45 to 50 minutes until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: filled meat loaf
directions: Mix bread, 1/2 of the diced up onion and 1 egg.
Sprinkle salt and pepper.
Add a little of milk to keep it together.
Mix hamburger, 1/2 onion (diced up) and other egg.
Mix well.
Put hamburger in pan and flatten out.
Put bread mixture in middle of pan, then cover with hamburger to make a meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until brown.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Put over very low heat and stir as cheese starts to melt.
Mix well and heat.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: lasagna
directions: Boil lasagna noodles (10 to 12) in 4-quart pan.
Brown ground chuck in large skillet.
After browning, add spaghetti sauce and tomato sauce.
When noodles are tender, drain and let cool.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 3 layers of sauce, cheese and noodles.
For cheese layer, add 1 egg to large carton of cottage cheese.
Also, stir in 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top of cottage cheese.
Layer sauce, cheese and noodles.
Bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Mix oleo, brown sugar and dates together and bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Add nuts, coconut, Rice Krispies and vanilla. Allow
to
cool.
Roll into 1 inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: lemonade (trinity's ice cream festival- 1971)
directions: Mix together.
Stir well until sugar is dissolved.
Makes about 5 gallons.

title: hot chocolate chip pie
directions: Cream cooled butter and sugar until light.
Blend in vanilla and eggs.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and add to creamed mixture.
Beat for several minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips in prebaked shell and work some up the sides.
Pour batter on top and spread carefully to cover entire surface.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35-45 minutes until golden and tester comes out clean.
Serve hot ala mode with vanilla ice cream on top.
If it is cooled, just heat up in microwave and then serve.
Also very good served at room temperature.
