title: asparagus casserole
directions: Make layer of each, except cracker crumbs, and put them on top.
Bake in moderate oven until bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Put directly into jars while boiling.
Can pressure up to 5 pounds.

title: buttermilk congealed salad
directions: Pour pineapple with juice and jello in boiler; mix well. Bring mixture to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Refrigerate until it starts to thicken.
Stir in buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts.
Mix well.

title: linda's hawaiian kolbassi
directions: Cut up Kolbassi into
1/2 inch slices.
Put in crock pot. Add smokies and wieners.
Add the crushed or cubed pineapple (juice and all).
Pour BBQ sauce over.
Cook about 4 hours.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugars until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: carrot leek soup
directions: Cut carrots and leek into coins.
Saute carrots and leek in butter until soft.
Add chicken broth and water.
Boil until very soft and mushy.
Put in blender.
Add nutmeg, salt and pepper.
If you wish to add potato, do so at the beginning.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Crumble ground beef into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover loosely and microwave on High (100%) until very little pink remains, 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes; stir and drain.

title: banana cake
directions: Beat egg; add shortening.
Add sugar.
Add crushed ripe bananas.
Dissolve soda in sweet milk.
Add salt and flour.
Bake in loaf pans 45 minutes at 350°.

title: irish cabbage-sausage dinner
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven. Add onion, apples and caraway seed. Cook and stir 3 minutes. Add cabbage, beer, sugar, salt and pepper. Add water to cover cabbage.
Heat to boil.
Reduce heat. Simmer, covered, until cabbage is tender, about 20 to 30 minutes. Add sausage. Cook until heated through. Remove sausage to serving platter.
Keep warm.
Drain off cooking liquid. Add melted butter and vinegar.
Toss well. Put cabbage in center of serving platter surrounded with sausage.

title: holiday ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Immediately remove from pan.
Serve warm.
Makes about 7 dozen appetizers.

title: onion board
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In 9-inch nonstick skillet, combine margarine and oil and heat until margarine is melted; add onions and saute over high heat until golden, about 2 minutes.
Set aside.
Line 15 x 10 x 1/4-inch nonstick jellyroll pan with pizza crust dough, pressing dough to edges of pan.
Spread onion mixture evenly over surface of dough, leaving 1/2-inch edge on all four sides of dough; sprinkle poppy seed over onion mixture.
Bake until dough is golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Cut into 20 equal pieces.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and spices.
Add chopped nuts and raisins. Cream shortening and add sugar gradually and continue to beat until light.
Stir soda into applesauce.
Add well beaten egg. Drop by teaspoon onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: jello fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and mix in all ingredients (except sour cream).
Put half in a mold and put in refrigerator and keep half on the counter.
After the jello in the refrigerator has jelled, cover with 2 cups of sour cream and cover with the remaining jello mixture and return to refrigerator.

title: easy chicken-n-dressing
directions: Boil chicken over medium heat until done, saving the broth. Allow chicken to cool, then remove all meat in small pieces, discarding the skin and fat.

title: savory chops
directions: Pour mixture over chops.
Place in a casserole.
Cover and bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: scripture fruitcake
directions: Follow King Solomon's advice for making good children and you will have a good cake (Proverbs 23:14).

title: mollie's shrimp and scallops
directions: Bring water to boil.
Cook noodles.
Spray bottom of 11 x 13-inch pan or large baking dish.
Sprinkle small amount of cheese in dish.
Heat olive oil in skillet.
Saute 1/3 shrimp in oil until done.
Put in baking dish with small amount of oil.
Saute 1/3 scallops in oil.
Add to dish.
Saute half of mushrooms.
Add to dish.
Cover with 1/4 of mixture of cheese.
Should wash skillet before proceeding.
Repeat.
After second part of mushrooms are put in baking dish, cover with drained noodles.
Saute remaining shrimp.
Put on noodles.
Saute remaining scallops.
Put on noodles.
Cover with remaining cheese.
Put in oven for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Enjoy.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add other ingredients and make out like small marbles.
Make dent in center.
Cook at 350° for about 10 minutes and while warm sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Makes 300 or more according to size.

title: spiced tea
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients slowly for 10 minutes; add tea bags and steep for 10 minutes.
Add orange juice and lemon juice.

title: sausage pepper bread
directions: 1. Brown Italian sausage in skillet.
Remove & leave drippings. 2. Saute green and red onions, onions, and mushrooms in sausage drippings.
Mix together with sausage and cool. 3. Make bread dough by mixing flour, yeast, and sugar with 1 c. hot water and oil.
Mix well. 4. Add enough flour to make dough that is not sticky (appx 2 more cups).
Roll up in a greased bowl and let set 1/2 hour. 5. Roll out on floured board into rectangle.
On 2/3 of dough spread mozzarella cheese.
On top put sausage mix.

title: chocolate wonder icing
directions: Soften cream cheese with cream. Add sugar, one cup at a time, blending after each addition.
Add melted chocolate and salt. Beat until smooth.
You may double the recipe if needed. This frosting may be kept in the refrigerator for several days.

title: creamy taco recipe(makes a pot full!)
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in crock-pot on high until thoroughly hot.
Add Velveeta.
Turn on low until melted.
Stir and serve with chips, taco shells or wrap in tortillas.

title: italian macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni until done; drain with cold water.
Cool.
Cut up salami, cheese, green pepper and onion.
Mix together; salt and pepper to taste.
Marinate overnight with 2 packages Good Seasons Italian dressing.
Stir once in awhile.

title: picante sauce
directions: Blend unpeeled tomatoes; blend in remaining ingredients.
Cook 25 minutes.
Process 15 minutes.

title: eye of the round roast
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Chop onion and green pepper.
Add ketchup until thick like a paste.
Spread the paste on top and ends of roast.
Bake 1 hour at 250°, then all day at 150°.
This roast is always perfect any time it is served that evening.

title: horseradish and beets (hrin)
directions: Cook beets, cool and grind.
Mix with all other ingredients.

title: grandma's molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add molasses.
To the warm water, add the baking soda.
Then add this mixture to shortening mixture.
Stir in flour, ginger and cinnamon.
Add raisins.
Drop by teaspoonful onto baking sheet.
Cook for 8 to 10 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: pizza bread
directions: Slice bread in half lengthwise.
Brown and crumble hamburger. Spoon sauce over bread; add cheese and then layer hamburger.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: goop
directions: Is it a liquid or a solid?
Put this on a cookie sheet or waxed paper and have fun!

title: light lemon cheese pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, sugar, juice and rind with electric mixer until
well
blended.
Fold in walnuts and whipped topping.
Pour in	pie
shell
and chill for several hours until firm.

title: cheese, bread and tomato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 2-quart baking or souffle dish. Layer bread, cheese and tomatoes in that order (2 layers).
Beat together eggs, milk, wine, thyme and mustard.
Pour over cheese, bread and tomatoes.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes or until puffed and browned.

title: haddock delight
directions: Barely cover haddock with water.
Simmer until flaky.
Drain. Break into chunks; set aside.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Drain. Saute onion in butter until tender.
Combine all other ingredients except cheese.
Pour into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese around edges of dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kolacky
directions: Combine butter and cream cheese in large bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Blend in vanilla.
Combine flour and salt; gradually add to butter mixture, mixing until mixture forms soft dough.
Divide dough in half; wrap each half in plastic wrap. Refrigerate until firm.

title: e. t.'s favorite cookies
directions: Mix in order given and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut chicken into pieces.
Mix flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Coat chicken with flour mixture.
Heat butter and Crisco in oblong pan in 425° oven until melted.
Place coated chicken (skin side down) in pan.
Cook uncovered 30 minutes.
Turn chicken over.
Cook uncovered about 30 minutes longer.

title: napolias (cactus)
directions: Cube the pork; fry in a skillet with onion and garlic.
In a large Dutch oven, add all ingredients, salt and pepper to taste and 1/4 teaspoon cumin and seasoned salt.
Heat for 1 hour.
Serve with crusty bread.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a bowl combine the cracker crumbs, pecans, and cinnamon.
Then stir in the butter.
Press the crust mixture into the bottom and about 2 inches up the sides of a 9-inch spring form pan.
Bake about 8 minutes; remove from oven and set aside.

title: cherry cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately to creamed mixture with milk.
Add vanilla and then stir in cherries and coconut. Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl, chill before serving. Serves 4 people.

title: cheesy vegetable soup
directions: Simmer vegetables in water, onion and bouillon.
Start with those that need more cooking.
Add other veggies until all are tender.
Add soup, then cheese.
Simmer until cheese melts.

title: orange-glazed carrots(makes 4 servings)
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients. Cook until butter is melted and sauce is hot. Discard cloves. Add basil and pour mixture over carrots.

title: bonbons
directions: Blend margarine, cream cheese, Eagle Brand milk, powdered sugar, vanilla, chopped walnuts and coconut.
Chill overnight in freezer. Form into balls and dip in chocolate.
Make chocolate chips in double boiler and add paraffin.
Store in cool place. Yields 80 to 100 pieces.

title: double duty dish
directions: Pour jello over cottage cheese, but do not dissolve jello in water.
Pour directly from package.
Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges, then mix in Cool Whip.
This can be made a day ahead and keeps for several days.
If a little moisture appears, simply stir.
Makes 6 servings.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Roll into 1-inch balls and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
Roll in powdered sugar when cooled.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Stir ingredients all together; add chicken wings.
Marinate at least 1 day, stirring occasionally.
Put in oven for 1 1/2 hours at 350°; cover with foil for 1 hour.
The last 1/2 hour take off foil.

title: recipe for preserving children
directions: Mix the children with the dogs and empty into the field, stirring continuously.
Sprinkle the field with the flowers.
Add the deep blue sky.
Bake in hot sun.
When children are well browned, they may be removed.
They will be found right for setting away in a cool bath tub.
Serves two loving parents.

title: one dish chicken and dressing
directions: Stew chicken in salted water until very tender.
Reserve broth for dressing mixture.
Bone chicken and cut into large chunks.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Let poppy seed and warm water set while mixing the rest of the ingredients.
After mixing the rest of the ingredients, add poppy seed to it.
Grease and flour 1 loaf pan or 2 small loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: silver cloud
directions: Mix in blender with crushed ice and top with whipped cream, then lace with Kahlua.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Stir sugar, vinegar and salt thoroughly and pour over sliced vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Stir occasionally. Put into pint containers and freeze!
Will keep several months. Thaw before serving and refrigerate any not used.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Lightly grease baking sheet. Mix all ingredients; knead for 1 minute. Shape into 1 1/2 inch balls. Bake 25 to 30 minutes; drain.

title: creamy spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.
Serve with assorted vegetables.

title: surprise shortcake
directions: Slice fresh or frozen strawberries, reserving a few for garnish.
Crush about half.
Drain, if using frozen, reserving juice.
Make 5 cups of whipped topping.
Butter one side of 8 to 12 trimmed slices of white bread; sprinkle with sugar.
Measure 1/2 cup juice from berries.
Set aside.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix together.
Grease and flour tube pan. Put 1/3 of batter in.
Lay in apples.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Put in rest of batter.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Then bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Test with cake tester.
May need to bake longer.

title: banana bread
directions: Soften margarine.
Add sugar and eggs.
Gradually mix in flour, soda and powder.
Fold in mashed bananas.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry jello food cake
directions: Cut cake into bite-size pieces.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Dissolve Jell-O according to package.
Pour over cake.
Place in refrigerator until jelled.
Pour over strawberries and serve with light Cool Whip.

title: four soup hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Stir in soups, water and rice or barley.
Place in large casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs in large mixing bowl with electric mixer until frothy
Gradually beat in sugar, then the oil.
Combine all dry ingredients by sifting together in small bowl.
Add 1/2 the zucchini, then 1/2 the flour mixture.
Repeat.
Stir in nuts and vanilla.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes in pan and then remove to cooling rack to completely cool before slicing.

title: chili
directions: Cook beef and onion until beef is browned. Drain grease and add remaining ingredients. Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: bubble and squeak
directions: * May be used instead of cabbage.

title: easy no fat pound cake
directions: Desserts are one of the easiest parts of our diet to make low-fat.
All you need to know are the tricks of substitution and modification.
When you learn to make some easy changes, the possibilities are unlimited.
Plain yogurt, buttermilk, low-fat cottage cheese, cream cheese spread, Egg Beaters, Butter Buds, Grape-Nuts cereal, etc.
The list could go on and on.
You can even use cocoa as a substitute for chocolate.
Experiment with low-fat substitutions and you will be in for a "sweet" surprise!

title: nutty peach crisp
directions: Just layer a 9 x 12-inch baking pan with peaches (chop up a little).
Spread cake mix on top, dry.
Pour margarine on cake mix.
Spread coconut and pecans on top of margarine.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: arkansas swamp rabbit stew
directions: Put rabbit pieces in a large Dutch oven and cover with the water.
Add salt and bring to a boil.
Skim off any scum that rises to top.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Add onion, garlic, bay leaf, thyme and any leaves off celery and green parts of leeks. Simmer for 1 hour longer.
Remove rabbit pieces from water and set aside.
Remove bay leaf, leek greens and celery leaves and discard. Add potatoes, slice white parts of leek and add them.
Put turnips, carrots and celery in pot.
Remove rabbit meat from bones and return to pot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer for 20 minutes.
Add chopped parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Hold chocolate chips aside for topping.
Mix sugars together. Add margarine, then peanut butter. Add beaten eggs and water.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add liquid mixture, then add 1 bag of chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes in greased jelly roll pan.

title: shrimp creole
directions: First, you make a roux! Heat oil in a large heavy pot. Stir in flour. Stir constantly over low heat for about 20 to 30 minutes until roux is a medium brown color. Add onion, celery, bell pepper and green onion. Saut until limp. Add garlic, tomato sauce, tomatoes, bay leaves, black pepper, thyme, basil, salt and cayenne. Cook 15 minutes. Add Worcestershire and water; bring to a boil. Add shrimp and simmer about 30 minutes. Serve over rice. This dish improves upon resting several hours.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
Skin and debone.
Cut up in small chunks.
Heat all this together.
Put crushed tortillas in bottom of pan.
Layer chicken on top, then heated soups and top with cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: monterey jack cheese soup
directions: Put onion, tomato, chilies and garlic in pot with chicken stock; cook until tender. Remove from heat; slowly stir in white sauce, then milk, stirring constantly. Add salt, pepper and cheese. Simmer slowly over low heat until cheese melts. Serve immediately. Makes 6 servings.

title: hard candy
directions: Combine sugar, Karo syrup and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir often over medium heat.
Boil until 310° on candy thermometer or until candy crackles in cold water.
Add flavoring and food coloring.
Put in buttered cookie sheet.
When it starts to harden, cut with kitchen scissors.
Or, for a fast and easy way, use a pizza cutter and snap pieces apart.
For the finishing touch, put candy in powdered sugar.
It will also keep it from sticking together.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans well, then add pecans and vanilla.
Pour mixture in pie shell.
Bake at 375° until center is set when gently shaken, approximately 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spaghetti marinara sauce
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, heat oil; saute garlic until golden brown.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over pasta, meatballs or chicken.

title: pizza sandwich
directions: Cut the Italian bread lengthwise.
Spread a thin layer of mustard on the bread.
Cover the mustard with pizza sauce.
Layer the ham, sandwich pepperoni and Mozzarella cheese.
Top with pepper slices.
Spread pizza sauce on bread top.
Place bread top on bottom and wrap with aluminum foil (tightly).
Bake in preheated 350° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: creamed vegetable cheese soup
directions: Place vegetables and broth in food processor until pureed. Turn into saucepan.

title: cranberry mold
directions: In saucepan, combine Jell-O and cranberry sauce.
Heat and stir until almost boiling.
Stir in pineapple and ginger ale. When fizz stops, pour into mold and chill.

title: yummy cheese hors d'oeuvres
directions: 1. Shave off top of the brie cheese.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix well and form into small meatballs.
Brown in vegetable oil.
Add 2 jars La Choy sweet and sour sauce.
Simmer 1/2 hour. Best when done a day ahead.

title: no bake rice pudding
directions: Cook rice until done and rinse.
Whip the cream until stiff. Mix rice, crushed pineapple and cream.
Add sugar to taste.
(This has been in the family for many generations.)

title: delicious cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients in order except egg whites.
Beat egg whites and add last.
Bake in a shallow pan, never a loaf pan, at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Test at 25 minutes.
Cut in squares when cool.
Cake requires no frosting.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken until done. Remove bones and skin.
Place chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Save broth.
Mix soup and milk and pour on top of chicken mixture.
Mix dressing with broth.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes until brown and bubbly.
A small amount of sage may be added.

title: company omelet
directions: Butter or grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Put 1/2 of bread in bottom of pan. Put cheese, onion and ham on top. Use remainder of bread. Beat eggs, milk and salt. Add mushrooms to mixture. Pour over top. Refrigerate for 12 hours. Bake 45 minutes at 350°, covered. Remove cover. Bake 15 minutes more.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Mix powdered sugar, whipped cream and vanilla.
Add pineapple and marshmallows, nuts and cherries.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.

Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Immediately after removing from oven, pour 1 cup sugar, 1/2 cup water and 1 teaspoon coconut flavoring that has been boiled for 1 minute while cake is still in the oven.

title: sandy's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Saute bacon, bell pepper, onion and celery until soft.
Remove from heat.
Add 3 ounce package cream cheese and mix together well.
Stuff into mushroom caps.
Place on cookie sheet and add 1/4 cup water to pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sour stew
directions: Brown meat and onion in oil in large pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until beef is tender.
Slightly thicken sauce if necessary when cooked.
Serve over noodles.

title: jello salad
directions: Add lemon Jell-O, lime Jell-O and 2 cups boiling water together.
Blend well and let set.
Refrigerate.
Cream the cream cheese, Eagle Brand milk, pineapple and juice, nuts and oranges. Mix well and let set.
Add to top of Jell-O.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: chile egg puff
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients except chilies, then add the chilies.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake 35 minutes or until lightly brown on top and firm.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Mush green tomatoes, sugar, onions and peppers.
Put in enameled saucepan.
Put in ground vegetables and remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.
While still steaming hot, spoon into sterile pint jars and seal.
Makes 6 to 8 pints.

title: fruit slush mix
directions: *The can of orange juice should be the 6 ounce size of the concentrate.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Lay half of chilies on bottom of greased square baking pan. Cover with half of the tortilla strips, half of the cheese and all of the tomatoes.
Repeat layers with remainder of chilies, tortillas and cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk and seasonings. Pour evenly over casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until puffy and set in center.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: festive chicken
directions: Wrap two bacon strips around each chicken breast and place in baking dish. In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken, coating all of the chicken.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Drain and keep marinade.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes, basting with marinade.

title: easy and yummy spicy dip
directions: In food processor, blend first 2 ingredients.
Serve with veggies or chips.
Makes a delicious low-fat, no cholesterol appetizer or dressing.

title: nutty green bean salad
directions: Grate 2 teaspoons zest and squeeze 2 tablespoons from lemon; reserve. Over high heat, bring large pot of water to boil. Add beans; cook until tender, 6 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place in 9 x 13 greased pan and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: delicious corn soup
directions: Put meat in a Dutch oven, fill with water, and let boil.
Skim off foam; add tomatoes, onion and celery.
Let simmer as you do for vegetable soup.
In a Dutch oven, smother cut corn in margarine until tender.
After soup has simmered about 1 hour, and meat is tender, add corn and simmer another half hour.
Serves 6.

title: hot fudge topping
directions: Mix ingredients in top of double boiler. Heat and stir until melted and smooth, then cook for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes. Makes 2 1/2 pints.

title: dry marshmallow salad
directions: Beat cottage cheese; add dry jello,
Cool Whip, pineapple, marshmallows and drained mandarin oranges.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish and chill.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Soften butter. Cream butter, oil and sugar. Beat well. Add eggs one at a time. Beat well after each. In separate bowl, add flour and salt. Mix milk with 1/4 cup water in measuring cup. Add flour and milk, alternating each to creamed mixture; blend well. Add flavoring. Bake in greased and floured tube pan. Put in cold oven. Turn to 325°. Bake 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: rosy peach upside-down cake
directions: Arrange peaches in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine strawberry and peach jello and cinnamon in a small bowl.
Sprinkle about 3/4 of the mixture evenly over peaches and dot with butter. Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour 3/4 of the batter into pan.
Stir remaining jello mixture into remaining cake batter.
Blend well and pour into pan.
Zigzag spatula through batter to marble.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes in pan, then invert onto serving platter and cool.

title: hot ham and cheese rolls
directions: Melt butter, mustard, poppy seed and Worcestershire sauce. Split rolls and spread with butter mixture.
Put desired slices of ham and cheese on each roll.
Wrap each roll in foil and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Cool.
Mix vanilla pudding, milk and cream cheese until thickened. Spread over cake. Spoon pineapple on top. Cover with Cool Whip and top with crushed nuts.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cook in crock-pot on low heat, 14 to 15 hours.

title: spiced beets
directions: Combine beets and onion.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in beets and onion; simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: virginia spoonbread
directions: Scald milk.
Sift in cornmeal slowly while stirring and cook until thickened.
Add salt, sugar, shortening and beaten egg yolks.
When thoroughly blended, add the baking powder and fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Turn into a well-greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish and bake in hot oven (400°) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with a spoon from the dish in which it was cooked. Serves 6.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Beat oil, sugar and eggs.
Add coconut, apples, pecans and vanilla; beat.
Add flour and soda; mix.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: cheesy potato skins
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise; scoop out center, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Deep-fry shells in 375° oil for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown; drain.
Place on cookie sheet.
Top with cheese; broil until cheese melts.
Top with remaining ingredients.

title: chicken in the sack
directions: Mix, stir and heat sauce until butter is melted.
Grease inside of brown paper bag.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Dip chicken in sauce and place in paper bag, folding tightly and place bag in roaster.
Cook for 15 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook 1 1/2 hours.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Place ingredients in oiled casserole in order listed.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes. Serves 4-6.

title: rich peanut butter bars(so easy)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt peanut
butter
and
oleo over hot water.
Add remaining ingredients and
stir
until
blended.
Bake for 25 or 30 minutes. Cool and cut in squares.
Delicious.

title: chocolate cream cake
directions: Dissolve German chocolate in hot water. Mix first 5 ingredients. Take out half of it for icing. Add remaining ingredients. Mix good and bake in 3 layers in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Cool and cover with icing.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, cocoa and sugar together.
Add milk.
Stir and cook until it begins to thicken.
Add butter.
Take 3/4 cup mixture out and mix in egg yolks, then add this back to mixture.
Cook 2 more minutes.
Take off heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour in baked pie shell.

title: zesty italian spaghetti sauce
directions: First wash and cut up tomatoes.
Let stand in a colander 15 to 20 minutes to drain.
In a 10-quart Dutch oven, combine tomatoes, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
When cooked, puree through a food mill.
Return puree to pan.
Add onions, parsley, thyme, oregano, basil, garlic and bay leaves.
Boil gently uncovered for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until thick.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Cook cranberries and water until skins pop.
Add sugar; boil 5 minutes.
Add jello; stir and chill.
Cut apple, celery, nuts, pineapple and orange juice.
Add to cranberry mixture and chill.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and spices; bring to a boil.
Add cucumbers, pepper and onions.
Boil for 2 minutes, then can and seal.

title: rubber devils
directions: Dissolve yeast and 2 tablespoons sugar in lukewarm milk.
Add 3 cups flour.
Beat smooth and let rise.
Cream shortening, rest of sugar and eggs.
Add to yeast.
Add salt and rest of flour to make soft dough.
Let rise.

title: sheep herder's pie
directions: Brown
ground
beef
with
taco
seasoning
mix.
Drain excess fat,
if
needed.
Add
corn, about 1/3 cup if desired, and mix it with ground beef.
Put meat in a small Dutch oven. Prepare enough mashed potatoes to cover meat (1 to 2-inches). Bake at
350° until
it
bubbles and potatoes start to brown. Scoop out portions and sprinkle with cheese.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Add sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely before serving.

title: potato salad for 1,000 people
directions: Make sure potatoes are well chilled, then toss with remaining ingredients.
Add salt and pepper.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: kooky good
directions: Mix flour, sugar, oleo and nuts; bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate butter pecan ice cream
directions: In a small skillet, saute pecans in butter 2 minutes.
Cool. In a saucepan combine cocoa and water; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in Eagle Brand condensed milk and vanilla.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan and freeze until mushy.
In a large bowl, beat cream until stiff.
In a small bowl whip chocolate mixture and fold into whipped cream.
Blend in pecans.
Return to square pan; cover and return to freezer.
Stir frequently during first hour; freeze until firm.

title: chocolate nut drops
directions: Stir flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder together. Cream shortening; add brown sugar gradually, beating well after each addition.
Add well beaten eggs, milk, melted chocolate and vanilla; mix well.
Blend in dry ingredients; fold in nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet and bake in a moderate oven (375°) for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ham and broccoli strata
directions: Place 4 bread slices on bottom of greased 8-inch square baking dish; top with broccoli, ham, onion and remaining bread. Gradually add eggs and milk to 2/3 cup of cheese spread, mixing well until blended.
Pour mixture evenly over bread.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese spread.
Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: tight jeans cookie bars
directions: Mix margarine, flour, and sugar.
Spread in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake at 350° F for 10 minutes (not until completely done).

title: deviled macaroni
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
In a mixing bowl, blend soup, cheese, pimentos, salt and mustard.
Add macaroni; mix well.
Pour half of the macaroni mixture into casserole; cover with eggs.
Top with remaining macaroni mixture. In small bowl, mix butter and crumbs or use "Italian bread crumbs."
Sprinkle on macaroni mixture.
Bake in preheated oven for 40 minutes.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle evenly over 3 cups blackberries.
Melt butter and pour over flour mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: oven stew
directions: This is so easy.
Do not brown meat.
Put all ingredients in a covered Dutch oven.
Bake for 3 hours at 325°.
Stir occasionally. Serve over mashed potatoes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Put butter and 3/4 cup sugar into a mixing bowl.
Blend them thoroughly with a wooden spoon.
Stir in egg, cream of tartar, baking soda and flour.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Put the cinnamon and tablespoon sugar into a separate saucer, and mix together; set aside.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumble Oreo cookies in blender.
Prepare packages of vanilla pudding and blend into Cool Whip.
Mix together cream cheese (softened), margarine (softened) and sugar.
Fold everything together except Oreo cookies.
Then layer pudding, Oreos, pudding, etc.
Should be 4 to 5 layers.
Layer into plastic flowerpot, top with silk flowers, gummy worms and serve with trowel.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ground meat, pork sausage, eggs, soup mix, bread crumbs nutmeg and cream. Form into balls. Fry until golden brown.
Pour off excess fat.

title: eggplant hoagie
directions: Grill sliced eggplant, sliced yellow squash, zucchini, red onion, yellow pepper, red pepper and sliced tomatoes.
When almost cooked through, add a little Italian seasoning, thyme and curry powder.

title: cool whip delight
directions: Put sweet milk in small bowl and dip 2 or 3 cookies at a time in milk.
Place in pan or dish as if you were making banana pudding.
Put a layer of cookies and a layer of Cool Whip until all is used up.
Refrigerate for several hours.
This will keep well several days in the refrigerator.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook meat until well done (meat leaves the bone).
Grind meat; set aside.
Put onions and potatoes through food grinder; add to the broth.
Cook until well done.
Add meat and other ingredients. Cook over low heat until done and thick, about 2 or 3 hours.

title: whole meal in frying pan
directions: Brown as many pork chops as needed (season lightly with salt as soup is salted).
When browned, place
a large slice of onion on each chop and 1 tablespoon rice (uncooked) on onion.
Pour soup over all.
Place potatoes on top and let simmer until rice and potatoes are done.

title: short ribs of beef casserole
directions: Heat oil in frying pan.
Add onions and meat; brown well.
Put into casserole.
Mix tomatoes, carrots, rice and seasonings.
Pour over beef and onions.
Add hot water to cover all ingredients. Cover and cook in slow oven at 275° for 3 hours.
Add more water, if necessary.

title: tom's onions
directions: Wrap onions in tinfoil with a pat of margarine and salt and pepper.
Place on grill for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes, until tender.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Mix in mixer. Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Add to pumpkin mixture and mix well.
Add pecans and raisins.
Pour into greased large Bundt pan or four 1 pound greased coffee cans.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Cool 15 or 20 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and put into 9 x 13-inch greased casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator one hour before cooking.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: winter vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions on package.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Cover with water chestnuts, onions and celery.
Mix mayonnaise and cheese; spread on top.
Crush crackers; mix with melted margarine.
Place this on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: angels and devils on a ferris wheel
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wrap each oyster or scallop, prune or mushroom in half-slice bacon.
Secure with wooden picks.
Arrange in shallow baking pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with or without wooden picks and garnish with leaf lettuce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Saute onions in butter until clear.
Chop mushrooms and add to onions.
Add the flour, broth, garlic and rice.
Cook approximately 20 minutes and enjoy.

title: pumpkin spice cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, spices and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Combine egg yolks, pumpkin, cooking oil, sweetener and orange peel.
Beat until smooth.
Wash beaters.

title: "different" fruit salad
directions: Peel, section and slice fruit. Peel and dice avocado. Dice onions and drain olives. Mix all together and enjoy.

title: out of this world pie
directions: Mix cherries, pineapple, juices, sugar and flour together and cook until thick.
Dissolve jello in hot water and add to mixture. Allow to cool.
Add vanilla, bananas and pecans and pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Top with cool whip and chill.

title: tortilla crisps
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder together in bowl.
Next add oil and water to dry ingredients.
Knead 5 minutes, forming a round ball.
Make small balls of dough to roll out like tortilla rounds. With knife, cut 4 wedges out of each ball of dough.
Deep fry in skillet both sides until brown.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Eat!
Very delicious!!

title: one gallon refrigerator pickles
directions: Make a mixture of first 5 ingredients.
Slice onions and cucumbers.
Mix real good and then fill jar.
Heat mixture until dissolved and pour over onions and cucumbers in jar and seal.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: crab and shrimp bake
directions: Mix all ingredients with your hands and place gently, do not pack, in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add beaten eggs and mix well.
Clean sides and bottom of the bowl with spatula.

title: rice mingle
directions: Wash wild rice and add to 2 cups salted boiling water.
Cover and reduce heat.
Cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
(This may take as long as 1 1/2 hours; start checking after one hour.)

title: huevos rancheros
directions: Heat oil in skillet; fry each tortilla until crisp.
Drain. Have the shelled eggs ready to slip in pan.
Cook until whites are set.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place one egg on each tortilla.
Heat salsa; pour over eggs and top with cheese.
Serve with refried beans and a mound of chorizo.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: yellow rice with chicken
directions: Cook the chicken slowly for 15 minutes with all the ingredients; afterward, add the rice.

title: freezer pecan pies
directions: Mix everything, except pecans, and pour into pie shells. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake 8 minutes at 425°, then 20 minutes at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: beef tenderloin in mushroom sauce
directions: In a skillet, heat oil and 2 tablespoons of butter over medium heat. Cook steaks for 6-7 minutes on each side or until done as desired. Remove beef to a serving platter and keep warm. To pan juices, add mushrooms, onions and remaining butter. Saute until tender. Add flour, salt and pepper. Gradually stir in broth until smooth. Bring to a boil and stir for 2 minutes. Spoon over the steaks. Serve immediately.

title: chili dip
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Spread cream cheese in bottom of cake pan.
Smooth chili over cream cheese.
Chop green pepper and onion stems.
Sprinkle over chili to taste.
Cover with Velveeta cheese. Bake at 250° until cheese is melted.

title: kraut salad
directions: Fluff kraut.
Mix peppers, celery, onion and pimentos. Sprinkle sugar over all ingredients.
Do not stir.
Cover tight and leave out overnight.
One hour before serving, stir well.

title: apple cake
directions: Slice apples and put in bottom of pie plate.
Mix remainder of ingredients in a small bowl.
Pour mixture over apples; distribute mixture to edges evenly.
Dot with butter and cinnamon.
Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Chill if cake sits for more than 12 hours.
Can be served with milk or ice cream.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Put in buttered dish; add 2 tablespoons butter cut in pieces. Sprinkle Stove-Top on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a large saucepan and cover with water. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and cook for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain; mash potatoes.
Beat in the cream cheese, sour cream, milk, garlic, salt and chives; beat until well blended.
Transfer to a greased shallow 3-quart baking dish. Drizzle potatoes with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until edges are bubbly and potatoes are heated through. Yield: 8 servings.

title: black walnut cream fudge
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients together in a large pan until mixed. Set on hot fire (medium heat) and stir constantly with a wooden spoon.
Boil until it will form a medium soft ball in cold water. Remove from fire and stir until cool.
Add nuts and vanilla and continue stirring until almost cold.
Pour into a buttered pan. Makes 5 lb. fudge.

title: old-fashioned cookies
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Beat until light.
Stir in all dry ingredients.
Blend thoroughly.
Shape into small balls. Place on a cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into cubes.
Cook in boiling, salted water until tender (15 to 20 minutes).
Drain; mash with fork. Brown meat in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Add onion and pepper and cook until tender.
Stir in eggplant, rice, salt and pepper. Spoon into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Saute bread crumbs in remaining 2 tablespoons margarine.
Sprinkle over eggplant mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: el's flan
directions: To caramelize sugar, in small heavy skillet, heat 3/4 cup sugar on medium heat until sugar begins to melt; do not stir. Cook and stir 4 or 5 minutes more, or until sugar turns a rich brown.

Remove from heat; immediately pour caramelized sugar into an oval 3-quart shallow casserole (9 x 13-inch oval dish). Holding dish with pot holders, quickly rotate dish so sugar coats the bottom and sides evenly.
Cool.

title: pineapple lemon pie
directions: Mix together and pour into Ritz cracker crust.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water and cool.
In a large bowl, mix the remaining ingredients together.
Add to sugar-water mixture.
Put in cups and freeze.
Serves 20 to 30.

title: zucchini nut chip cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Beat in zucchini, then dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: belvie's dumplin's
directions: Cook chicken until tender. Remove from broth and debone.
Mix flour, egg yolks and enough broth from chicken to form stiff dough.
Roll out and cut into strips and drop into boiling broth. Cook 20 minutes.
Stir chicken meat into dumplings and serve.

title: tennessee taters
directions: Allow 1 large potato per serving.
Cut individual size aluminum foil squares (size depends on servings).
Cut potatoes in bite size squares.
Take each square of aluminum foil and spray Pam cooking spray.
Place potatoes on squares.
Season with the ingredients for flavor.
Heavy on onions/garlic for "long lasting" flavor!
Grill for 45 minutes to an hour or you can bake in oven at 350° for
1 hour.
Add optional toppings for flavor and zest.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, shortening and oleo.
Add eggs and water.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; add dry ingredients to creamed mixture; stir well.
Add chips, vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese over low heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over sugar and cocoa mixture.
Mix well.
Mix in nuts.
Spread in 2 buttered 9 x 13-inch pans.
Let stand until set.

title: brown sweet potatoes
directions: Cut sweet potatoes into thin slices.
Melt butter in medium skillet; add potatoes and brown over medium heat.
Season to taste.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cherry streusel coffee cake
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups dry cake mix (reserve rest for streusel), yeast, flour, eggs and water.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Spread dough in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Set aside.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl, then add milk and egg. Bake in an 8 x 8-inch, well-greased pan at 425° for 20 minutes. Beware as ovens vary.
Keep in an airtight container.

title: potato supreme
directions: Combine in pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Garnish with paprika.

title: mixed vegetable salad
directions: Cook vegetables as stated on package, omitting salt.
Add celery and onion.
Boil vinegar, oil and sugar for 5 minutes. Pour over vegetable mix while hot.
Refrigerate 3 days; stir occasionally.

title: apricot chicken
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Place chicken in roasting pan. Pour sauce over.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: eva's maple charolette
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Dissolve it in hot maple syrup. Chill the jelly until it falls in heavy sheets from a spoon.
Whip cream until stiff, fold in gelatin until well blended.
Add chopped nuts.
Line a bowl with pieces of sponge cake, pour in gelatin.

title: cream cheese walnut brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed.
Add nuts.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until blended.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Reserve 1/2 cup brownie mix.
Spread rest on bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining brownie batter.
Swirl mixture to marbleize.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake; cool.

title: spicy shredded chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer 15 minutes or more.

title: tuna hot dish
directions: Boil egg noodles and drain.
Place in baking dish.
Drain tuna and add to noodles.
Drain peas and carrots and add to mixture. Mix in soup and milk, mix together and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Crumble potato chips and place on top.
Bake for 5 minutes more.
Serve hot.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Combine and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix well and eat!

title: hawaiian baked beans
directions: Mix all but pineapple slices.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes; top with pineapple slices and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: southern cornbread
directions: For healthier recipe, substitute vegetable oil or margarine for bacon drippings.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in water for 5 minutes; drain.
Stir soup and sour cream together.
Toss together with squash.
Mix stuffing mix with melted oleo.
Spread half of mix in 11 x 7 x 2-inch pan.
Pour squash mixture over.
Top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Line or spray muffin tins.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift flour with salt, baking powder, soda and spices.
Set aside.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a small bowl beat together cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add peanut butter and milk.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Fold in Cool Whip to mixture.
Turn into pie shell and chill 5 to 6 hours.
Garnish with Hershey chocolate fudge and peanuts.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Place vegetables in large pot with tomatoes and broth.
Bring to a boil and simmer covered until thick, about 45 minutes.

title: caramel pie
directions: Mix in a mixing bowl, blend cream cheese and milk; fold in the whipped topping.
Spread half into pie crust.
Drizzle with half of the caramel topping.
Combine coconut and pecans; sprinkle half over the caramel.
Repeat layers.
Chill or freeze until serving. This is a convenient recipe for serving a crowd.
The recipe can be doubled as well as made ahead of time and stored in the freezer.

title: 7 layer jello
directions: Dissolve red jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
When cool, pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Bring 2 cups milk to slow boil.
Add 1 cup sugar.
Remove from heat. Dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water.
Add to milk and sugar. Mix well.
Add 1 pint sour cream and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Mix and set aside.
When jello sets, add 1 1/2 cups white mixture.
Chill until set.
Add remaining layers, alternating colors and white filling.

title: marie's vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until potatoes are tender.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mash artichokes.
Mix with mayonnaise, cheese and garlic salt. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries in food grinder or food processor.
Stir in sugar to blend; set aside.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Cool until starts to thicken.
Add to cranberry mixture.
Add oranges, nuts and pineapple; stir well.
Pour into lightly oiled 8-cup mold or glass dish.
Chill overnight.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheeses.
Shred cheeses.
Combine cheeses and add about 2/3 to other ingredients.
Sprinkle remaining 1/3 of cheese mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips or Fritos.

title: dad's soup
directions: Bring 6 cups of water to boil with six bouillon cubes and tomatoes, while you are cooking your noodles in a different pot. Strain the noodles when they are done to your individual taste. Mix the strained noodles into the bouillon water.

title: fried bologna sandwich
directions: Fry in an iron skillet or fryer until golden brown. Place on toasted bread.
Very good.

title: low-fat yogurt pie
directions: With whisk, combine yogurt and Cool Whip until well blended. Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze.
A half hour before serving, place in refrigerator.
Garnish with fruit and Cool Whip if desired.
Serves 6 to 8. Great low-fat summertime treat.

title: creamed chicken (or turkey) in toast cups
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan; mix well and heat thoroughly. Spoon into toast cups.
A little chopped parsley may be sprinkled over the top, if desired.

title: spaghetti sauce and meat ball
directions: In large skillet brown onion and sausage in butter; add sauce, paste and water. Then add the salt, pepper, garlic, bay leaf, Italian seasoning, sweet basil, parsley and mushrooms; simmer for four hours.
Mix the remaining ingredients in a mixing bowl and shape into balls, brown lightly in skillet. Then add meatballs to sauce and simmer for 2 hours.	Serve over your favorite pasta or spaghetti.

title: easy sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix together ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until thick and bubbly, about 1 hour.
(Mixture will be even thicker when cool.)
Makes about 2 cups.
Sauce keeps indefinitely in the refrigerator.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Place potatoes, carrots, celery and onion in a large kettle. Cover with water.
Cook until tender.
Meanwhile, in a mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, oleo and soup; stir well.
Add milk, salt, pepper and bacon.
Add to vegetables and heat thoroughly. For a thicker soup, drain vegetables before adding cream cheese mixture.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir first 5 ingredients until well blended. Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Cool.
Serves 8.

title: rice casserole
directions: Cook rice; cook bacon until crisp and break into crumbs.
Cook the onion, celery and green pepper in the bacon fat until celery is tender; drain.
Mix all the ingredients in a casserole dish. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: pink cloud
directions: Mix Cool Whip and sweet milk together and let sit for 1 hour. Add remaining ingredients to Cool Whip mixture and serve.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat first three ingredients to boiling or oleo is melted. Remove from heat.
Add flour to mixture in saucepan.
Stir until mixture leaves sides of pan.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, hand beating each time until egg loses gloss.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until completely dry and browned. Cool and cut in half and fill with filling.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add cocoa and remaining ingredients, except powdered sugar.
Blend well.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar (coat heavily).
Place onto cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Bake for 15 to 18 minutes, or until edges are set.
Cool thoroughly before storing.

title: corned beef and vegetables
directions: Rinse corned beef with cold water and place in large pot, cover with water and season with whole peppercorns, bay leaf and garlic.
Bring to a boil for 10 minutes, then reduce heat and slow cook for 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
Drain meat.
Save some broth to cook vegetables in.

title: out-of-this-world fruit salad
directions: *Such as strawberries, blueberries, cantaloupe, seedless grapes, peaches, bananas, etc.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar, Wesson oil and eggs.
Beat well. (In cup, mix coloring, cocoa, and vinegar.)
Pour into sugar mixture.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add alternately with buttermilk. Add vanilla.
Pour into two 9 inch or three 8 inch layer pans. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and
onion for 5 minutes in salted water. Mix stuffing as
directed
on
package.
Add
soup and stir in zucchini and
onions.
Pour
into
casserole
and add 4 tablespoons melted butter.	Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fanny mae fudge
directions: Melt the oleo.
Add sugar and stir. Add milk.
Heat until warm.
Add marshmallows. Bring to a boil and lower heat.
Add all 3 chocolates and melt.
Add nuts, if desired.
Pour into large jelly roll pan that has been lightly buttered.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: amplified rice krispie bars
directions: Melt 4 cups of mini marshmallows and 1/4 cup of butter (margarine) in microwave.
Mix in 4 cups of Rice Krispies.
Pat in pan.

title: mock lobster
directions: Cover frozen fillets with cold water and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer for 10 minutes; drain again.
Cover fillets with cold water and add vinegar.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Dip in melted butter.
Wow lobster!

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and cube potatoes; boil until they are almost done. Drain.
Dice the onion; add to potatoes.
Remove the majority of fat from the bacon.
Dispose of fat.
Fry the bacon.
Remove the bacon; add to potatoes.
Using the grease from the bacon, create a roux with the 1/4 cup of flour.
Add 4 cups of milk.
Allow to thicken.
Pour into potatoes.
Add remainder of milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: house dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oil and vinegar.
While beating with mixer, gradually add salad oil and vinegar.
Serve over salad greens.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 1/2 cup sugar and softened margarine.
Bake in a greased oblong (9 x 13-inch) baking dish at 350° for 10 minutes. Set aside to cool.

title: quick cherry cobbler
directions: Combine lemon juice and cherry pie filling.
Pour into shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over filling.
Cut margarine into thin slices over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix soups, water and uncooked rice.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Season chicken and then layer over rice. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is done.

title: oat waffles(serves 4)
directions: Blend all ingredients except almonds or pecans.
Spray hot waffle iron with Pam.
Pour mixture onto iron and bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with almonds or pecans or both.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti and return to large pot.
Add canned ingredients.
Warm and serve.

title: meat loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Place in loaves in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: "diabetic cake"
directions: Cream eggs, oleo, sweetener and vanilla together in bowl.
Add spices, flour and soda.
Mix well; pour in dates, pecans and applesauce.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: maw's egg custard(nellie starnes)
directions: Mix well and pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle nutmeg onto the top.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean, about 30 minutes.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Sugar can burn easily, so use a heavy-based pot; preferable one that doesn't have a dark interior so that you can monitor the sugar once it begins to color.
Set a small dish of water and a pastry brush by the stove.
Pour 1 cup water into a heavy-based 8 quart saucepan or dutch oven.
Add the sugar and corn syrup. Cook over high heat, stirring often with a wooden spoon, until the mixture is clear and comes to a boil.
If sugar crystals form on the sides of the pan, wash them down with a wet pastry brush.

title: donald's favorite barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together, baste chicken, pork chops and steak that you have grilling.
You may leave out the hot sauce and vinegar.
It is very good either way when grilling.
Take the meat up when done and use the extra sauce for dipping at the table.
It is also good to use when baking in the oven.

title: paella
directions: Boil clams.
Set aside 1 cup broth.
Boil crab and set aside. Devein shrimp; saute with garlic.
Set aside.
Heat olive oil in heavy pan.
Fry chicken and sausage.
Cover until half done and push to one side.
Saute onion in garlic, then add tomato sauce. Add broth, clams, chicken and rice.
Mix everything together. When rice is half done, add red pepper and green beans.
Cover without stirring for 20 minutes or until broth is absorbed by the rice.
Paella may be baked in oven and kept covered.
During last 5 minutes of cooking, add shrimp, crab and peas on top.
Garnish with sliced hard-boiled eggs, parsley and lemon slices.

title: dream cake
directions: Bake cake as to package directions in 13 x 9-inch pan and let cool.
Mix pudding as directed and let settle.
Add softened cream cheese.
Spread mixture over cake.
Top with crushed drained pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: south-of-the-border dip(microwave)
directions: Place tomato in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pierce with a fork. Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap and vent.
Microwave on High 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until tomato skin splits, rotating tomato after 1 minute.
Peel, seed and dice tomato. Set aside.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Beat eggs and oil; add brown and white sugar.
Add flavorings. Mix flour and rest of ingredients; add to first mixture.
Mix this in a large pan by hand.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
(Don't overcook.)

title: hidden valley snack
directions: Mix seasoning and pour over the oyster crackers.
Stir occasionally for 1 hour, until oil is absorbed.

title: raspberry jam(low-fat topping for pancakes and waffles)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring often.
Cool 20 minutes.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Has 0 g fat.

title: caramels
directions: Pour 1 bottle white Karo in a heavy pan; stir with pancake turner.
Add 3 cups sugar and pinch of salt and bring to a rolling boil.
Boil about 2 or 3 minutes.
Add 1 stick of butter.
Turn burner to medium before adding butter.
Keep boiling.
Add 1 can milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook until right consistency, about firm ball stage (245°).
Will burn easily.
Pour into buttered pan or cookie sheet.
Cut into pieces and wrap in waxed paper.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with taco chips.

title: 4 bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: whistling marinated chicken
directions: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine the first 7 ingredients; mix well.
Add chicken; seal bag and refrigerate for at least 8 hours. Drain and reserve marinade.

title: microwave bacon stix
directions: Cover one side of bacon strips with cheese.
Roll bacon strip diagonally around each bread stick.
Line a microwave-safe baking sheet with paper towels and place bacon wrapped bread sticks on the baking sheet.
Microwave on High power for 4 1/2 to 6 minutes. Remove and roll bread sticks in cheese once again.
Ready to serve.

title: boyd's shrimp saute
directions: Remove shell from shrimp.
Wash in cold water.
Combine all ingredients.
In large mixing bowl, let set for 45 minutes.
In a shallow pan or saucepan, cook on medium heat until shrimp are a pretty orange color.
Broccoli should still be crisp.
Serve with pasta, rice or broiled plantain.

title: man style meat and potatoes
directions: Place beef and onions in saucepan.
Add margarine and cook until onions are tender and meat is brown.
Blend in soup, milk or cream and 3/4 cup cheese.
Arrange alternate layers of potatoes, meat, onions and sauce in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and paprika.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Yields 6 servings.
Good to prepare early and cook just before needed.

title: butter brickle cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions; let cool for 5 minutes. Poke holes in the cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk in the holes.
Let cool.
Top with Cool Whip and butter brickle almond chips.

title: sausage stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and snap off stems.
Set aside and allow to dry on paper towel.
Brown sausage in microwave, stirring until crumbles and is no longer pink.
Drain grease.
Place cream cheese in mixing bowl and pour sausage over it.
Using hand mixer, mix well.
Generously spoon sausage mixture into mushroom caps.
Place mushrooms on ungreased broiler pan with slats so juice can drain off.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 10 minutes.
Broil 5 1/2-inches from heat for 3 minutes or until tops are lightly browned. Servings:
36 mushrooms.

title: pepper steak and rice
directions: Sprinkle steak with meat tenderizer and let stand about 4 hours.
About 30 minutes before serving, melt Crisco in a heavy skillet.
Cut steak in 1/2-inch strips.
Add to hot shortening. Put vegetables on top.
Cover and cook until steak is done and vegetables are tender.
Add soy sauce, cornstarch and water.
Cook about 1 minute, until gravy is thick.
Serve over hot rice with cole slaw and rolls.
Makes a meal.
Serves 4.

title: chicken ball
directions: Mix all together and shape into a ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and take off the bone.
Melt Velveeta; add pimentos, garlic salt and onion.
Place a layer of chicken and a layer of the mixture; keep repeating until all used up.
Crush Tostitos and place on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: chicken or turkey dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased pans.
This makes a lot.

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: Combine berries and sugar; mix well.
Bring to a full boil.

title: chewy chocolate cookies(makes 5 dozen)
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, salt and soda and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
(Do not overbake; cookies will be soft.
They will puff while baking and flatten while cooling.)

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture.
Add apples and chopped nuts.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mock crawfish dip
directions: Saute in butter the onions (bottom of green onions), bell pepper and garlic.
Add drained tuna, soup and lemon juice and cook for 10 minutes.
Add parsley, green onion tops and cayenne. Cook for 5 minutes more.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: tuna and chips casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk.
Drain oil from tuna; add tuna, potato chips and peas.
Mix all ingredients gently.
Sprinkle top with 1/4 cup chips, bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar.
Mix pudding according to package, but using the 1 1/2 cups milk and let stand 5 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip.
Combine with cream cheese mixture and beat on low speed.
Crush cookies into fine mix.
Layer pudding mixture into a clay flower pot, ending with cookie mixture on top.
You can insert a silk flower in center of pot.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Cream sour cream, eggs and sugar together.
Bring oleo, cocoa and water to a boil; add.
Sift flour, soda and salt together; add.
Beat well.
Will be real soupy!
Bake in a greased 16 x 11-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Frost while hot.

title: margarita balls
directions: Mix vanilla wafers with almonds.
Melt chocolate according to package directions.
In a blender, process tequila, orange marmalade, lime juice and corn syrup until smooth and stir along with melted crumb and chocolate mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls and coat with sugar.
Store in fridge.

title: jelly jewel cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Add well beaten egg yolk.
Stir in flour.
Chill dough.

title: zucchini lasagne
directions: Wash zucchini and slice in 1/4-inch strips lengthwise.

When ready to assemble, place zucchini in boiling water for 2 minutes; drain and layer (using zucchini strips in place of pasta noodles). In large skillet, brown ground meat, chopped onion and pepper. When meat is done, add 2 cups of spaghetti sauce.
In separate bowl, beat 2 eggs and combine with Ricotta.
In large baking dish, layer zucchini on generous layer of sauce with Ricotta mix and meat.
Mix, then 1/2 Parmesan and 1/2 Mozzarella.
Repeat layers. Top with sauce and cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix well and boil all ingredients together until thick.
Serve hot with a pat of butter and a biscuit.

title: dirt(serve in flower pot and serve with a small spade.)
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add soft cream cheese.
Crush 18 Oreo cookies and line bottom of bowl.
Crush 12 Oreos and add to cheese mix.
Pour mix into bowl.
Crush 18 Oreos and put on top of pudding mixture.

title: sesame potatoes
directions: Mix all but potatoes together.
Put potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture over potatoes, then sprinkle 2 ounces sesame seed on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until sesame seed are golden brown.

title: hurry-up yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a
large
mixing
bowl. Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine biscuit mix and sugar.
Gradually add to yeast mixture; stir well.
Turn
dough
onto floured surface and knead until smooth (about 10
minutes).
Roll into a
12-inch circle.
Cut in 12 wedges.
Roll
up
each
wedge, beginning at wide end.
Place rolls on
greased
sheet,
point side down. Cover and let rise in warm place 1
hour.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes.

title: broccoli-beef squares
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Cook and stir beef in 10-inch skillet until brown; drain.
Stir in mushrooms, 1 1/2 cups Cheddar cheese and onion.
Mix baking mix, water and remaining Cheddar cheese until soft dough forms; beat 20 strokes.
Put dough in dish with floured hands, pressing 1/2-inch up sides.
Spread beef mixture over dough; sprinkle with broccoli. Mix remaining ingredients; pour over broccoli.
Bake until knife inserted near center comes out clean, 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Mix sugar, salt, and cocoa together.
Add eggs and mix well. Stir in vanilla and milk.
Add melted margarine.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° for 40-50 minutes.

title: white wine punch
directions: Mix lemonade, pineapple juice and water.
(Can do this step ahead of time).
Then when ready to serve, add ginger ale, club soda and wine.
An ice ring can be made from equal parts water and pineapple juice.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In large casserole dish, pour rice, then add mushroom soup and milk (save a little to pour over chicken). Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over rice and soup mixture. Lay chicken breasts over this. Add remaining soup and milk. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Add 1 pudding to cake mix and make as directed on box.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute garlic and onion in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Add tomato sauce, oregano, sugar, marjoram and thyme.
Layer sauce, noodles, cottage cheese and cheese in casserole, finishing with shredded cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: one layer cake
directions: Mix flour, milk and sugar together.
Place in cake pan.
Pour prepared pie filling over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet muffins
directions: Grease bottom of muffin tins.
In a mixing bowl, beat egg lightly with a fork.
Measure and stir milk and melted butter. Measure and sift flour.
Measure sugar, baking powder and salt; add all at once to the liquid mixture.
Stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Remember, no extra strokes, to avoid toughness and tunnels.

title: mom's salad dressing
directions: Cut fish in strips. Place in baking dish.
Pour 1 teaspoon real lemon on each piece and sprinkle with Greek seasoning and hickory smoke salt.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all together;
place 4 strips of bacon on top.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: rhubarb kuchen
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cut in butter until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine egg, milk and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until moist.
Pat dough into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine gelatin, 1/3 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons flour.
Add rhubarb and mix well.
Pour onto crust.

title: belgian waffles
directions: Sprinkle yeast over milk; stir to dissolve.
Beat egg yolks; add to yeast mixture with vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in melted butter.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Let mixture stand in warm place until mixture doubles in bulk.
Use 3/4 to 1 cup batter per waffle.
Batter keeps well in refrigerator for a week.
Good with strawberries and whipped cream.

title: hot dogs and bacon wraps
directions: Cut bacon and hot dogs in 3 equal pieces.
Wrap each 1/3 piece of bacon around each 1/3 hot dog.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Place in oblong cake pan.
Mix brown sugar, water and A-1 sauce and pour over hot dogs.
Bake at 325° for 1-1/2 hours.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package.
Pour 1/2 of batter in 9 x 13-inch cake pan, greased and floured.
Bake for 15 minutes, then cool.

title: all-purpose crepe batter
directions: Combine ingredients in blender; blend for 1 minute.
Scrape down sides with rubber spatula and blend for another 15 seconds or until smooth.
Refrigerate batter at least 1 hour.
Cook on upside-down crepe griddle.
Makes about 32 to 36 crepes.

title: sunflower beef spread
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk together. Add other ingredients and refrigerate.
When ready to serve, warm in oven or microwave. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or microwave 1 1/2 minutes. Serve on wheat crackers and sprinkle with sunflower kernels.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Put 1/2 of cheese in 11 x 7-inch pan.
Mix eggs and sauce; spread over cheese.
Cover with remaining cheese and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly before cutting into squares.

title: cherry delight salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight in a 13 x 9-inch dish or bowl.

title: crawfish or shrimp fettucini
directions: Melt butter and saute onions, bell peppers and celery; add garlic, parsley and crawfish or shrimp.
Cook 10 minutes.
After add flour, cream and jalapeno cheese.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes. Add cooked egg noodles to mixture.
Put in casserole dish and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple cinnamon muffins(low-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Empty mix into a large bowl.
In a separate bowl, combine applesauce and cinnamon and mix well.
Form a well in the center of cake mix and pour applesauce mixture and egg whites into the well.
Put mixer on low and blend all ingredients.
Increase mixer speed and beat for 2 minutes.

title: candy apple salad
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Combine next 3 ingredients and cook over medium heat until thickened.
Chill.
When chilled, add apples. Fold in whipped cream.
Garnish with peanuts.
Refrigerate until served.

title: sour cream oven doughnuts
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix baking mix, 1/4 cup sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon, sour cream and egg until soft dough forms.
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured cloth covered board.
Knead 10 times.
Roll dough 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with floured 2 1/2-inch doughnut cutter.
Lift doughnuts carefully with spatula and place about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Immediately brush entire doughnut with melted butter; dip in sugar mixture, coating all sides.
Or, if desired, spread with Creamy Glaze.
Serve warm.
Makes 10 to 12 doughnuts.

title: honey baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Cook slowly all day in crock.

title: holy land soup
directions: Brown Quaker oats in butter in a big pot.
Add grated vegetables; cook about 2 minutes.
Add chicken broth.
Bring to a boil.
Add 3 more cups of water.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add parsley and dill.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: rice krispie deluxe
directions: Heat peanut butter, Karo and sugar just throughly.
Then add Rice Krispies and spread into buttered pan.
Frost with melted chocolate chips and butterscotch chips mixed.
Delicious.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions.
Cool slightly and prick all over with a fork.
Bring the following mixture to a boil and pour ove warm cake:
sugar and milk.
When cool, frost with: 8 ounces Cool Whip and 2 cups coconut.
Reserve some coconut to sprinkle on top or use extra.

title: fruit on a stick
directions: Mix cream cheese, Marshmallow Creme and milk until smooth. Thread fruit on wooden skewers or insert toothpicks into each piece.
Serve with dip.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Warm in oven until bubbly. Sprinkle with paprika for color.
Serve with wafers.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Combine granulated sugar, cream, white corn syrup, butter. Cook until it will spin a thread or 234°.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour over 12 cups popcorn at once.
Pack into ungreased tube pan.
After this sets, turn out and decorate as desired with candy corn, nutmeats, gumdrops and other candy.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add ingredients by layers as listed.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool in pan. Cut in squares.
This is very rich.
Serve in small servings.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off top of peppers, remove seeds and wash.
Bring salted water to boil, add peppers and cook 5 minutes.
Cook ground beef, garlic and onion in pan until onion is tender.
Do not brown. Drain fat, add salt, rice and half of tomato sauce.
Heat mixture, remove from heat and add cheese.

title: quick and yummy angel food cake
directions: Slice angel food cake in 2 or 3 layers, depending on the height of the cake.
Mix remaining ingredients, folding in the whipped topping last.
Allow to sit in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Ice the cake between layers, on top and sides.

title: coleslaw
directions: Combine vegetables in large mixing bowl.
In small bowl, beat together the cream, sour cream, mustard, lemon juice, sugar, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables, tossing well. Refrigerate one hour before serving.

title: streusel coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Measure 2/3 cup of cake mix (dry mix) into small bowl.
Cut in the butter.
Mix in brown sugar and set aside.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and add seasoning mix.
Drain and cool. Toss with other ingredients except dressing and chips.
Add dressing and chips just before serving.

title: red, white and green salad
directions: Wash cauliflower and broccoli good.
Cut in bite size pieces (cut broccoli flowerets only).
Mix all ingredients and pour Wish-Bone dressing over all.
Shake bottle of dressing good.
I put my salad in a 13 x 9-inch plastic pan with top.
Stir once or twice during refrigeration.
It is much better if you let this marinate for about 4 hours before serving.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fast family fajitas
directions: Cut bell peppers into 1/2-inch strips using Utility Knife. Cut chicken crosswise into thin strips.

title: apple snack squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease a 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Combine sugar, eggs, and oil.
Mix well.
Stir in self-rising flour and cinnamon (batter will be thick).
Stir in apples and walnuts. Sprinkle butterscotch chips on top of cake.
Bake 35 - 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool before cutting.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put in pot and cook until vegetables are tender.
Can use bouillon cubes in broth.

title: veal schnitzels - sznycle cielece
directions: Have veal cut into cutlets; pound well so meat is
not more than 1/4-inch thick.
Season and dredge in flour.
Brown quickly in hot butter.
Reduce heat and fry slowly until tender.
Arrange on hot platter and garnish each piece with a lemon slice and chive butter.
Add soup stock to the bottom of the frying pan; allow to boil up and pour over the meat.
Serves 6.

title: cowboy chili
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towel.
Drain fat from skillet.
Cook and stir beef in same skillet until light brown. Drain.
Add all remaining ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: perfect fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cream and margarine. Bring to boil; lower heat to medium and cook 15 minutes. Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour in buttered baking dish (or two). Refrigerate until set.

title: sausage-rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage in a heavy skillet or Dutch oven; stir in remaining ingredients and simmer until vegetables are tender. Spoon into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: ritz cracker dessert
directions: Mix together crackers and butter. Save some for top.
In a bowl, mix pudding and milk, then add ice cream; mix well.
