Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan or container. Store in refrigerator.

title: black-eyed peas
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add to rest of ingredients.
Cook until peas are tender.

title: ice cream caramel rolls
directions: Stretch and roll thawed dough into 8 x 12-inch rectangle. Spread softened butter over dough.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle mixture over dough.
Roll up tightly, starting with long edge.
Seal edge by pinching dough together.
Cut into 12 slices.
Thread works great for cutting slices.
Place into a well-greased 9 x 13 cake pan.

title: over seas fudge
directions: Mix Fluff and peanut butter together thoroughly.
Bring brown and white sugar and milk to a rolling boil and boil 3 minutes. Take off stove and fold in Fluff mixture.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine baking mix, milk and cheese to soft dough.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix butter with garlic powder and brush over warm biscuits.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Gently mix in fruits and nuts. Fold in frozen whipped topping.
Put into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and freeze.
Smaller pans or ice trays may be used.
Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: strawberry marbled cheesecake
directions: In blender container, combine strawberries and cornstarch. Blend until smooth.
In heavy saucepan, over medium heat, cook and stir until thickened.
Reserve 1/3 cup of sauce; cool.
Chill remaining sauce to use for topping.
Preheat oven to 300°. Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press onto bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: stuffed eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise; remove yolks and combine with other ingredients.
Mix well.
Refill egg whites.
Chill.

title: banana split cake
directions: Use 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt 1 stick margarine; add crumbs, mixing well.
Press into pan.
Cream other
stick margarine and powdered sugar.
Add softened cream cheese and beat until smooth. Spread cream cheese mixture over crust.
Cover cream cheese layer with bananas.
Layer with drained pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: mexican chicken chalupas
directions: Boil fryer, seasoned with salt, pepper and poultry seasoning. Boil until chicken falls from bones.
Debone and shred.

title: finnish summer vegetable soup
directions: Add water, carrots, potato, peas, beans and cauliflower in a 3-quart pan.
Bring to a boil for 2 minutes.
Reduce heat to simmer; simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add spinach.
Cook, uncovered, for 2 minutes.
Combine milk, cream, flour, salt and pepper.
Stir into vegetables; bring back to a boil for 1 minute. Reduce to a simmer and serve hot.
Garnish each serving with dill. Serve with rye bread.
Makes 10 (3/4-cup) servings.

title: thanksgiving turkey gravy
directions: Combine first 6 listed ingredients and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and cover, then simmer 1 hour.
Cool a little, then strain, keeping liquid, neck and giblets.
Discard vegies.
(At this point you may freeze liquid and neck separately for up to 1 week.)
Cut butter into flour and make four balls; put into freezer.
Thaw liquid and neck day of dinner; add in salt, pepper and herbs to taste.
Adding neck, giblets and drippings to liquid, bring to boil, then reduce to medium heat.
Remove flour and butter balls from freezer.
Place one at a time, in center of wire whisk.
Stir whisk with ball into the liquid until dissolved.
Repeat with each ball until desired thickness is achieved.
Bring to low boil for 3 minutes to remove any flour taste.

title: crabmeat stuffing
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in large bowl; set aside.
Combine eggs and next 4 ingredients.
Stir them into crabmeat mixture.

title: breakfast bread
directions: Pull biscuits apart; cut into small pieces.
Chop bell pepper and onion until fine pieces.
Knead together all ingredients until well mixed.
Bake in Bundt pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve warm.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potpourri hot dish
directions: Cube bacon; saute and add onion.
Brown hamburger until done; add drained bacon and onion, then other ingredients.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Continue cooking on top of stove until hot dish is heated through and flavors are blended.
Can also be made in electric frying pan.
Serves 6.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice firm, green tomatoes into quarters or half-inch thick slices.
Dip slices in corn meal mixture.
Fry in bacon fat until brown, turning once during cooking.

title: spicy apple cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix together well.
You can either make drop cookies or flour surface and roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: diet delight
directions: In a large container, crumble half the angel food cake.
Mix pudding as directed on box.
Spread half over the cake.
Put half of the drained pineapple and half sliced strawberries over the pudding.
Top with Cool Whip, then crushed pecans.
Repeat, refrigerate and enjoy.

title: cream cheese drops
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients.
Add flour.
Roll in balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press half of maraschino cherries in middle.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: rice krispies caramel bars
directions: Melt 1/4 cup margarine and 4 cups mini marshmallows or 40 large.
Stir in 5 cups Rice Krispies. Pat in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan or use a jelly roll pan and spread Krispies layer thinner.

title: taffy apple pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove 1/2 cup of cookie dough and reserve for another use.
Add flour to remaining dough and knead with hands to combine.
Use either round or square baking stone (or a greased cookie sheet or pizza pan) and press cookie dough on it.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes or until cookie is lightly browned. Let cool for 10 minutes, then loosen cookie from pan.
Cool completely.

title: cheddar potato bake
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix soups and sour cream in saucepan.
Add cheese and 1 can of milk.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and onion flakes over potato and cheese mixture.
Stir well and put into 9 x 13 baking pan and top with shredded Cheddar.
Bake until golden brown and bubbly at 350°, about 30 minutes.

title: beef roll-ups
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, butter and salt.
Top each steak with stuffing.
Roll up as for jelly roll, then fasten with skewer or toothpick.
Brown in oil.
Add gravy; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until steaks are tender.
Serve with rice or noodles. Makes 6 roll-ups.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Cover with boiling water and let stand five minutes.
Drain.
Add
sugar, vinegar and salt. Bring the mixture to a
boil
and boil for five minutes.
Pour into hot, sterile jars and seal.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Pour over broccoli, onion and cheese and mix.
Cook bacon, drain and crumble on top.

title: old fashioned coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order and pour into uncooked pie shell. Dust nutmeg over top, if desired.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: millionaires
directions: Put in top of double boiler, caramels and milk and melt.
Add chopped pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto buttered wax paper.
Cool 1 hour.
In double boiler, put paraffin and chocolate chips. Dissolve.
Dip each nut cluster.
Cool on wax paper.

title: german potato salad
directions: Wash, cook and peel potatoes.
Cool and then slice into large bowl.
Add onions to potatoes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Whip cream; add sugar and softened cream cheese.
Add fruit and nuts and freeze in small greased molds.
To serve, set in hot water for a second and arrange on top of a leaf of lettuce with a cherry on top.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and cocoa.
Beat egg yolks.
Add eggs and gradually stir in milk.
Stir constantly over medium-low heat.
Add vanilla and margarine.

title: celery stick treats(appetizer)
directions: Clean and separate the celery stalk into sticks.
Be sure to string the celery sticks.
Cut celery sticks into pieces about 3 inches long.
With a knife or spoon, fill 1/13 of the celery sticks with cream cheese, 1/3 with American cheese spread and 1/3 with peanut butter.
Arrange sticks on a plate.
Place in the refrigerator and let chill one hour before serving.

title: taco pie
directions: Combine taco sauce and refried beans, spread in bottom of baking dish.
Brown and drain ground beef.
Combine all other ingredients.
Add enough water to separate.
Cook on low to medium heat for 1 hour until mixture is thick.
Spread over beans.
Top with cheese and put in 400° oven until cheese is melted and mixture is bubbling.
Let cool 15 minutes.
Then top with lettuce, tomatoes, black olives or anything else you might like.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: no cook fondant
directions: Mix cream cheese and flavoring.
Add coloring.
If more than one color is desired, separate batch at this time.
Mix in sugar, kneading with hands, until consistency of stiff pie dough.
You may need more sugar.
Wrap in plastic to prevent drying.

title: cheese grits
directions: Beat eggs with fork and add enough milk to make 1 cup.
Then add all ingredients to cooked grits and mix together.
Place in buttered casserole dish and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Casserole should be firm, if it moves cook a little longer, but no longer than 50 minutes.
Serves 6 people.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Flatten chicken to 1/4-inch thickness. In a shallow bowl, combine bread crumbs, cheese and basil. In another bowl, beat the egg. Dip chicken in egg and then crumb mixture. In a large skillet, brown chicken in butter and oil over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes on each side or until juices run clear.

title: dump it cake
directions: Add ingredients as listed in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip if desired.

title: friendship cake
directions: Cream greetings and smiles thoroughly.
Add hand shake separately.
Slowly stir in hospitality.
Sift sympathy and love together.
Fold carefully.
Bake in a warm heart.
Serve often.

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Grind cranberries and combine with marshmallows and sugar. Chill overnight.

title: crab meat pizza
directions: Mix together cream cheese, lemon juice, onion, garlic powder, Worcestershire sauce and mayonnaise with fork until well mixed. Spread into a 12-inch glass round serving tray. Spread cocktail sauce on cheese mixture.
Crumble crab meat on cocktail sauce. Use like a dip with crackers.

title: orange balls
directions: Combine crushed wafers, sugar, butter and orange juice concentrate. Mix well. Shape dough into one inch balls. Roll balls in pecans. Chill until firm.

title: fried chicken batter coating
directions: For fried chicken, remove skin.
Salt and pepper and flour chicken pieces.
Dip in buttermilk and repeat by dipping in flour. Place in electric skillet which has 1-inch hot oil.
Cover with lid.
Brown on one side and turn.
Brown other side.
For last few minutes, leave lid off pan while frying to make chicken crisp. Lid on makes chicken tender and cooks through.
To test for doneness, press fork tines next to bone in center.
If no red rises to top, chicken is done.

title: irish potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients together and shape into small balls.
Roll in cinnamon.
Eat and enjoy.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Add eggs and oil and stir until dry ingredients are moist. Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, bananas and pecans. Spoon batter into a greased and floured cake pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes and let cool. Makes a 10 x 13 oblong pan or 3 round cake pans.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Cook cake like recipe on box.
Let it cool completely, then add your Eagle Brand milk.
Let it soak into the cake.
Then put your can of pineapple on top of cake.
Top with Cool Whip and coconut.

title: sante fe soup
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add chopped onion, salt and pepper to taste. Add remaining ingredients and simmer until hot through and through.
Good with grated cheese and Fritos.

title: million dollar dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo; add to flour and nuts.
Mix well and line bottom of dish (9 x 13-inch) with mixture.
Bake 15 minutes, or until lightly brown.
Cool.
Blend together powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over the baked crust and refrigerate.
Beat instant pudding mix and milk until slightly thickened.
Spread over the cheese layer.
Top with Cool Whip.
(The most popular flavors are lemon, chocolate, pistachio and butterscotch.)

title: spring garden dressing
directions: Combine yogurt, mayonnaise, salt and pepper; stir well.
Stir in the remaining ingredients and chill dressing thoroughly.
Serve over salad greens.
Yields 2 cups.

title: linda poor's breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until brown; drain.
Separate dough and put in ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.
Press over bottom and up sides. Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle over hash browns.
Top with cheese.

title: all-in-one dinner
directions: Fry ground beef until brown and pour off excess fat.
Place alternate layers of ground beef and fresh vegetables in casserole dish.
Pour canned tomatoes over top.
Place cheese and butter on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken pie
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Make cream sauce and cook 1 minute. Add chicken, sausage, peas and carrots and heat thoroughly.
Place in an 11 x 7-inch casserole and top with Savory Pastry.
Bake at 425° for about 30 minutes.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Cut bacon into thirds.
Wrap bacon around water chestnuts; secure with a toothpick.
For easy clean-up, bake on an aluminum foil covered cookie sheet at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix ketchup, sugar and soy sauce; dip water chestnuts in sauce.
Bake another 20 minutes at 350°.
You can bake water chestnuts the first time, dip ahead of time and bake the second time just before serving.

title: snickerdoodlesceres, california
directions: In a large bowl, beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.

title: fruit tarts
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, sugar, eggs and dash of vanilla.
Place vanilla wafers, flat side down, in 1-inch high cupcake papers.
Fill cups 3/4 way full.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Before serving, put fruit filling on top, such as blueberries, cherries or strawberries.
Makes 28.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Blend all ingredients.

Divide mixture and place on tortillas, spreading evenly. Roll tortillas and wrap tightly in plastic wrap, twisting ends. Refrigerate several hours or overnight. Cut into 1/2 to 3/4-inch slices (electric knife works best). Throw away ends. Makes about 50 pinwheels. Arrange on platter with salsa in middle.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, bananas and vanilla, beating well.
Combine the dry ingredients, blending well.
Stir into banana mixture.
Mix in milk and pecans.
Spoon batter into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Grease lightly a 13-inch pizza pan.
Cream together oleo, Crisco, 1/2 cup sugar and egg.
Add flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Dough will be sticky.
Spread until it covers pan.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 400°.
Let crust cool.
Clean strawberries and have bananas ready to slice.
Beat until smooth and spread over cooled crust the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons reserved juice.
Slice bananas, strawberries, pineapple and oranges in bite-sized pieces.
Arrange in pretty design on top of cream cheese filling.
Thicken remaining fruit juice with cornstarch over medium heat.
Stir continuously.
Cool slightly and spread over fruit. Chill at least 2 hours.

title: layered overnight salad
directions: Put all ingredients in a bowl in the order listed.
Tightly cover with plastic or a lid and leave overnight.
Mix well before serving.
(May need more mayo!)

title: pride of iowa cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs, then dry ingredients and mix.
Drop on cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Dip each piece of bread into the batter and deep fat fry at 370°. Drain and roll in granulated sugar.

title: wild goose
directions: Rub inside of bird with salt and pepper.
Stuff loosely with sliced onions, apples and celery.
Truss bird if large.
Brush bacon drippings lightly over entire body.
Sprinkle pepper generously over breast and body.
Place 3 or 4 bacon strips over the breast.
Cover exposed part of bird with aluminum foil.
Pour 2 cups of water in roaster.
Roast at 300° to 325° for 15 minutes per pound until tender.
Baste frequently.
Remove foil when ready to brown.
Remove stuffing and serve.
Allow 1 to 1 1/2 pounds per person.

title: vidalia onion casserole 2
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
In casserole dish, put layer of crackers, onions and 1/2 can of each kind of soup; repeat layers. Top with crackers.
Mix together the eggs and milk; pour over the top.
Top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed in a 9 x 13-inch or 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch pan.
Blend cream cheese, pudding and milk until spreadable.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cooled cake.
Then spread pineapple over that.
Cover entire cake with Cool Whip (will need 12 ounce container for larger pan).
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Freezes well also.

title: crisp-fried catfish
directions: Combine water, vinegar and salt in a large bowl.

Soak catfish in vinegar mixture 4 to 5 hours in the refrigerator. Combine cornmeal, flour, salt, onion powder and seasoned salt in a plastic bag, shaking to mix. Add catfish, one at a time, and shake until completely coated.
Pour oil to depth of 2 to 3-inches into a Dutch oven.
Heat to 375°. Fry catfish 4 minutes on each side or until golden brown. Drain well.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and slice tomatoes 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Beat egg and milk in bowl.
In another bowl, combine corn meal and flour.
Dip each slice individually in the milk and egg mixture and then in the flour and corn meal mixture.
Have shortening about 1/2-inch deep in heavy skillet.
When shortening is hot, place tomatoes in and fry (not too fast) until brown on both sides.
Salt to taste.

title: pumpkin-raisin-nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Using medium speed of mixer, cream sugar and oil until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Sift flour and spices several times and add.
Mix until smooth.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Mix raisins and nuts with 1/4 cup flour and 1/4 cup oil.
Add to batter.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: lemonade pie #1
directions: Blend ice cream and lemonade together.
Put into pie crust. Place in freezer until ready to serve.

title: tangy cabbage
directions: Heat butter in skillet.
Add cabbage, garlic and water; simmer for 10 minutes.
Cover tightly; steam 10 minutes longer.
Add carrot, sour cream, sugar, lemon, salt and caraway seed.
Heat thoroughly before serving.
Serve with pork roast or sausage.

title: pork chops with apple gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a well heated skillet brown pork chops on both sides well (coat pan with 2 to 3 tablespoons oil). Arrange browned chops in a baking dish.
Saute garlic in fat left in skillet chops were browned in.
Add flour, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Add water; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils and is thick.
Add applesauce and lemon juice.
Mix.
Pour over chops.
Bake for 1 hour or until tender.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Chop onion and green pepper.
Cook in small amount of oil in large frying pan until tender.
Add ground beef and brown.
Season beef.
Drain excess grease.
Add all other ingredients to beef and simmer very slowly at least 1 hour, stirring often.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: featherweight chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Cover large baking sheet with foil and
set
aside.
Beat
egg
whites
in medium bowl until foamy. Add
sugar	gradually and beat until stiff peaks form. Add vanilla
and
salt.
Fold
in
chocolate pieces and nuts. Drop
by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart.
Put in preheated oven. Turn off heat.
Leave
cookies at least 5 hours or overnight, without opening the door.
Cookies will be light brown.
Store in airtight container.	Makes 45 cookies.

title: astoria cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Make a paste of cocoa, coloring and water; add to the creamed mixture.
Add salt and flour alternately with the buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla last, then mix soda with vinegar and add to the mixture.
Do not beat at this stage; just fold gently until blended.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Bake 1 pie crust according to package directions.
Reserve remaining pie crust for garnish.
Set aside in large saucepan. Combine gelatin, cornstarch, cinnamon, nutmeg, ginger and salt. Stir in pumpkin and evaporated skim milk.
Let stand 5 minutes to soften gelatin.
Cook and stir using medium heat until mixture bubbles.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir 1 cup hot mixture into eggs.
Return all egg mixture to saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat for 2 minutes.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Equal.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Cover and chill 6 hours or overnight.
Makes 8 servings. Contains 237 calories.
Food Exchange:
1/2 Milk, 1 1/2 Bread, 2 Fat.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots until they are tender.
Cool.
Mix all ingredients together and add carrots.
Let set overnight.

title: home fries
directions: Heat oil in skillet, saute onions until limp.
Add potatoes and continue cooking, flip in sections until done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Separate eggs. Add the yolks to the mixture; blend well. Add flour and baking powder alternating with milk. Add flavor. Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into batter. Pour into 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 375° until done. Use your favorite frosting.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, place chopped onions and mushroom stems.
Cover and microwave on High for 4 minutes.
To this mixture, add cream cheese, mixing well; then add crumbs of bread and bacon.
Stir and mix well, then stuff each mushroom cap with mixture.
Place each cap on plate and put into microwave for 3 to 4 minutes, rotating after 2 minutes.

title: sunday chicken dinner
directions: Saute vegetables in butter until tender.
Combine vegetables, chicken, soups and rice.
Put in buttered baking dish.
Grate cheese on top.
Bake until cheese melts at 400°.

title: shrimp casserole "easy"
directions: Saute celery, onion, bell pepper and shrimp in butter. Add cream of shrimp soup and rice.
Mix and pour in buttered 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with herb
stuffing. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cottage cheese nut loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Form a loaf and bake in a generously greased bread pan in a 375° to 400° oven for about 45 minutes or until top and sides are well-browned.

title: pastry
directions: Mix with pastry blender.
Add
water and stir until all sticks together lightly.
Roll out for pie crust.

title: microwave chinese chicken and mushroom soup
directions: Shred the cooked chicken finely; cut off and discard the ends of the mushroom stalks and slice the caps finely.

Pur the chicken, sliced mushrooms and bean sprouts in a 3-quart ovenproof glass bowl and stir in the stock; three-quarters cover with Saran Wrap and microwave on High 15 minutes, stirring 2 to 3 times during cooking.

title: deep-dish pizza
directions: Lightly brown hamburger; drain.
Mix tomato sauce, onions, oregano and garlic powder.
Press dough evenly on bottom and halfway up sides of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread the tomato sauce on bottom of dough.
Add hamburger and spread evenly. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 425° until cheese is light brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: rommegrot
directions: Boil cream slowly about 20 minutes or a little longer. Gradually stir in flour.
Let butter come to top and spoon off. Add hot milk to thin. Beat with electric mixer on low speed and keep on low heat. When about done, add salt and sugar.

title: tia's flan
directions: In a saucepan over medium-high heat, melt 2/3 cup of sugar. Have patience and keep stirring.
All lumps will dissolve with time.
Coat a pan of your choice (could be a Pyrex in an interesting shape or a smooth Bundt pan.
I use a simple stainless steel mixing bowl so that is comes out round) with the melted sugar.
Coat the pan well!!
In a small bowl, whisk 6 egg yolks and 2 whole eggs.
In a large bowl, combine 2 cans of condensed sweetened milk with 2 cans of the evaporated milk.
Add the eggs. At this time, add vanilla.
Pour mixture into prepared pan.
Take a roasting pan.
Pour 2-inches of water into it and set the flan in the middle.
Bake your flan in an oven that has been preheated to 350°.
This can take anywhere from 1 to 2 hours depending on your oven.
Test your flan for doneness with a toothpick inserted into the middle.
It's ready when it comes clean.
Carefully remove your flan by lifting the bowl out of the pan.
Chill well (6 hours minimum, you can make it the night before).
To remove slide a butter knife around the edge.
Invert the pan onto your serving plate (a large plate or a plate with a lip).
Remember the caramel runs off.
Get all of it on the plate.
Yields 12 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish and top with more cracker crumbs and grated cheese.
Place "pats" of butter or margarine on top.
Bake until golden brown.

title: mexican hamburger
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix Ro-Tel, beans and soup with hamburger in saucepan.
Heat; place in dish.
Layer tortilla, layer sauce, layer tortillas, layer bean sauce and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: gentlemen's favorite cake squares
directions: Stir baking soda into buttermilk.
Cream shortening.
Add sugars.
Cream together; beat in eggs.
Alternately add buttermilk (with added soda) and flour.
Add nuts, vanilla and cinnamon. Spread in greased oblong baking dish.
Prepare topping.
Place topping on batter before baking.
Bake slowly in 300° oven until done.
Cut into squares.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Make Jell-O according to package.
Cream the cheese and stir cheese into Jell-O, then add small can crushed pineapple.
This is for a double package of Jell-O.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cake:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate in boiling water. Cream butter and sugar.
Add yolks one at a time, beating in between.
Add vanilla and chocolate.
Sift flour, soda and salt. Add dry items alternately with buttermilk to the butter mixture. Fold in stiff egg whites and pour batter into three 9-inch pans lined with wax paper.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost when cool.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Place ribs in large baking pan.
Cover with onion and lemon juice.
Bake in 450° oven for 30 minutes.
Combine ketchup and remaining ingredients. Pour over ribs and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix according to list. Spray 1 loaf pan or 2 small loaf pans with Pam. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: emil's stew
directions: Sprinkle a little salt in the bottom of a pot.
Heat pot and then add meat.
Brown a little, if possible.
Add onions and peppers; saute until limp.
Then add water to cover meat and chopped canned tomatoes.
When the mixture begins to boil, turn to a simmer and cook until meat is close to tender.
Then add carrots and corn.
Add all seasoning, a little at a time if you wish to suit your taste.
Add green beans and potatoes.
Continue cooking. About 15 minutes later, add chopped fresh tomatoes.
When potatoes are done, you are ready to eat.
Serve with cornbread. Makes enough for 20.
If you wish to freeze, omit potatoes.
When you wish to serve, boil potatoes until done and then add frozen stew.

title: french toast
directions: Dip any bread, preferably sourdough rolls, split or dry bread, in mixture and brown on both sides in hot buttered skillet. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: party turnovers
directions: In medium skillet, combine Lipton onion soup mix and meat; brown well and blend in cheese.
Separate crescent dough according to package directions; then cut in half.
Place spoonful of meat mixture in center of each triangle; fold over and seal edges. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 48 turnovers.

title: caesar salad
directions: Rub garlic in wooden bowl with salt.
Add rest of ingredients and toss.
Add egg after lettuce.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook vegies in 1/4 cup water quickly (bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and cook 3 to 4 minutes or until vegies are just barely tender).
Do not drain.
Combine cornstarch, cream, pepper and bouillon cube.
Add to vegies.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly, then cook 2 minutes more.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix cake and pudding mixes together.
Add remaining ingredients one at a time.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 large or 3 small loaves.

title: french dip sandwich
directions: Mix au jus as package directs.
After it comes to a boil, add the roast beef and simmer until well heated.
Split hoagie rolls and butter lightly and place under broiler of oven until heated. Divide beef onto the rolls.
Serve the au jus in small dish for dipping the sandwiches.

title: sweet potato pies
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until tender; drain water off potatoes and whip potatoes.
Add beaten eggs, sugar, milk, vanilla and nutmeg to potatoes.
Mix in margarine and beat well.
Pour into pie crusts. Bake at 350° until done.

title: deb's way good oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugars, egg, water and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Boil whole tomatoes and 1/2 teaspoon oregano.
When it comes to a boil, take off stove.
Add seasoning packet and potatoes. Put in
half of the Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni and mix thoroughly.
Put in casserole dish and put remaining cheese and pepperoni on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown onion and ground chuck.
Mix with other ingredients. Bake in casserole for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 5 or 6.
Never any leftovers.

title: soup bean pie
directions: Cream the sugar and butter; add eggs.
Add syrup and mix well. Stir vanilla into mixture and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Pour beans into mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 40 to 50 minutes; when knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean, pie is done.
Tastes like pecan pie.

title: mikado goulash
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir turkey burger, onion and vegetable oil; brown well and drain.
Add other ingredients; simmer 1/2 hour.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, whip cheese at low speed until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter at medium speed.
Slowly add milk while beating.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Turn into pie shell.
Sprinkle peanuts over top.
Cover with Saran Wrap and freeze until firm.
To serve, remove from freezer 1/2 hour before cutting.

title: nappa cabbage salad
directions: Finely chop cabbage and onions.
Saute butter, sesame seed, almonds and Ramen noodles until brown.
Drain on paper towel. Shake oil, sugar, soy sauce and vinegar in covered jar.
Toss cabbage, onions, sauteed ingredients and dressing just before serving.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat the yolks of 4 eggs and the white of 1 egg until thick. Add condensed milk and beat again.
Add lime juice and beat until thick.
In a separate bowl, beat 3 egg whites until dry and fold in the lime, milk and egg mixture.
Pour into a baked pie crust. Separate 2 eggs.
Beat the whites with the sugar until stiff peaks form.
Spread evenly on top of pie.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or until meringue is brown, then garnish with thinly sliced limes.
(Do not overbeat egg whites.
Do not use a food processor; use a mixer instead.)

title: texas brisket
directions: Season brisket with salt and pepper; top brisket with onion and green pepper.
Place brisket in 2 layers of heavy-duty foil, wrapping tightly.
Cook at 250° for 4 hours.
Serve natural juices and vegetables as sauce.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: rio grande chilli
directions: Prepare chili as directed on package.
Top with cheese, sour cream, onions or green peppers.
Makes 8 servings.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oatmeal with boiling water; let stand 20 minutes. Add sugars, butter and eggs, beating well after each addition. Add sifted dry ingredients to mixture, beating well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti squash with anchovy and capers
directions: Cut squash in half, remove seeds.
Place cut side down in pot with 2-inches water or in microwave.
Cook until tender, 20 to 30 minutes.
Take fork when squash cools and remove squash from shell. Looks like spaghetti.

title: marshmallow delight
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Chill for at least 1 hour. For a salad, serve on crisp salad greens.
For a dessert, serve in a bowl.

title: savory cheese bundles
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine 2 cups of flour, sugar and salt in a large bowl.
Add margarine, milk, 3 of the eggs and yeast mixture; beat until blended, about 2 minutes.
Stir in enough additional flour to make stiff dough. Place on lightly floured surface and knead 8 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Place dough in greased bowl; turn to coat. Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours. Punch down.
Knead dough a few times to release air.
Divide into 16 portions.
Roll each into a 6-inch circle.
Place 2 tablespoons of filling in center of each circle.
Draw dough up around filling to form bundle.
Pinch dough firmly above filling, letting top of dough flare loosely.
Place 2 inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Cover; let rise 30 minutes.
To seal firmly, lightly pinch bundle together again.
Combine remaining egg and water; brush over bundles.

title: sugared pecans
directions: Boil first three ingredients until soft ball stage. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour out on wax paper and quickly separate with a fork.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel, slice or coarsely chop potatoes while the sugar, water and butter is simmering, 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour over mixture of potatoes in baking dish.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook, peel and slice salad potatoes.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain.
Add chopped onions, salt and pepper.

title: simple tea cakes
directions: Mix together the vanilla, egg and sugar in small bowl.
In a large bowl, pour flour, making a depression in center.
Spoon in shortening or butter and the sugar mixture.
Work into a stiff dough.
Roll out really thin and bake 7 to 8 minutes at 400°.

title: vegetable rotini
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, gradually stir soup into cream cheese. Add milk, mustard and pepper.
Over low heat, heat through, stirring often.
Add macaroni, vegetables and Parmesan cheese. Heat through, stirring often.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese omelet
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place 8 slices of bread on bottom. Cover each slice with slice of American cheese.
Top with remaining bread slices.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour over bread.
Cover with grated cheese.
Chill overnight before baking.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels and add 1/3 cup sugar and margarine. Bake at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes. Set aside to cool. Cream together cream cheese (room temperature) and 1/2 cup sugar until sugar is not grainy. Stir in pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip and pretzels.

title: sauce for chicken
directions: Saute chicken in butter 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove chicken and set aside.
Mix cornstarch and juice.
Stir in 57 sauce and marmalade.
Pour into skillet and heat; stir until thickened. Place chicken in sauce until heated.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil in a double boiler 2 sticks margarine, water, and 4 Tbsp. cocoa.
Remove from heat and add 2 c. sugar, flour and salt; mix well.
Beat together eggs, sour cream and soda and add to cocoa mixture.
Pour batter into jelly roll pan and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
While cake is baking, prepare frosting. Melt together in double boiler 1 stick margarine, cocoa and milk. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and quickly add walnuts, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread frosting on hot cake as soon as it comes out of the oven.

title: barbecue slaw piedmont style
directions: Grate cabbage. Combine all other ingredients and pour over cabbage. Mix well. Chill before serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs and beat about 1 minute on high.
Add bananas and beat until no lumps remain.
Add flour and soda and beat until thoroughly mixed.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in loaf pan, which has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Wrap and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: mango sherbet
directions: Up To Two Weeks In Advance:
In a 3-quart saucepan, sprinkle gelatin evenly over milk.
Let stand 1 minute.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring until gelatin dissolves.
Remove pan from heat.
Stir in sugar until dissolved.
Cut mangoes into bite size bits; remove seeds and peel.
In food processor, blend mangoes until they are smooth.
Pour mangoes into gelatin mixture with orange juice.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Let vegetables thaw, then drain.
Drain pimentos.
Combine vegetables, soup, 2 ounces cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimento and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into 1-quart casserole dish. Bake, covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out of oven and top with remaining cheese and onion.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together in a large mixing bowl.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator before serving.

title: caroline's heavenly chicken
directions: Lightly spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam cooking spray.
Line dish with dried beef.
Wrap each chicken breast with 1/2 slice bacon (do not use extra thick bacon).
Mix together sour cream and cream of mushroom soup and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
This recipe is easy and great for company!
Serves 12.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake sugar cookie in pizza pan, until browned.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip with electric mixer until smooth. Spread over cookie.
Arrange fruit as desired.
Refrigerate until served.
Makes two pizzas.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Cook lasagna according to package directions.
Mash potatoes. Add cheese to potatoes and beat with hand mixer.
Saute onions in margarine until soft.
Add 1/3 of onion and margarine to potato mixture.
Salt to taste.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: In iron skillet, cook sausage, onions and green peppers until lightly browned.
Stir together corn meal, baking powder, salt, Cheddar cheese, corn, egg, oil and milk.
Stir in sausage, onion and peppers.
Also add the oil from the sausage.
Turn back into iron skillet.
Bake in a 400° oven for 35 minutes or until done.

title: french fried squash
directions: Wash squash.
Cut them up lengthwise.
Let them drain on paper towels.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Roll in dry flour real good. Fry in real hot grease or oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
They are real good.
You should try them.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Place peaches in crust.
Combine sugar, water, cornstarch and syrup in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Cook, stirring until thickened.
Add the Jell-O granules and stir until dissolved. Cool.
Pour cooled gelatin mixture over peaches.
Chill until firm.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Combine water, vinegar and salt in a large pot and bring to a boil.
Put cucumbers, dill and garlic into hot jars.
Pour boiling liquid in to fill jars almost to the top.
Seal jars.
Yields 8 quarts or 16 pints.

title: banana bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Mash bananas and put on side.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Beat again.
Add oil and bananas.
Beat.
Add vanilla and almond.
Mix dry ingredients in small bowl.
Add gradually to banana mixture. Add nuts last.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: maple-almond ice cream
directions: Advance preparation:
Beat egg yolks well; stir in syrup. Cook and stir over low heat until mixture thickens.
Cool well. Whip evaporated milk to soft peaks; fold into syrup mixture.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Fold into syrup mixture along with almonds.
Pour into two 3-cup refrigerator trays; freeze firm.
Makes 6 cups.

title: breakfast crescent rolls
directions: Unroll and separate crescent rolls.
Place 1/8 of the shaved ham on each roll; sprinkle with grated cheese.
Roll up dough as directed on package and place on nonstick cookie sheet or baking sheet.
Bake according to package directions, or until rolls are brown.
Makes 8 breakfast rolls.

title: chicken breast edan isle
directions: Rinse dried beef, pat dry and line bottom of oblong glass casserole dish with beef.
Wrap each chicken breast with a slice of bacon.
Place on top of dried beef.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken breast.
Cook, uncovered, for 3 hours at 275°.

title: almond tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve chilled.

title: oatmeal waffles
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together flour, oats, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
In a small mixing bowl, stir together eggs, milk, butter and brown sugar.
Add to flour mixture; stir until blended.
Pour batter onto lightly greased waffle baker.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Chop celery and onion medium fine.
Melt butter in a skillet and saute celery and onion until tender, about 5 minutes.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well.

title: oatmeal patties
directions: Mix together all ingredients with 1/2 cup water or milk.
Let stand a few minutes.
Form into patties or balls.
Brown slightly in oil.
Cover with can of tomato sauce and simmer a few minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all but last two ingredients in large pot.
Put cloves and allspice in tea ball while heating all for about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot, but do not boil.
Yields one gallon.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Set aside.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased) or hot iron skillet.
Spoon meat mixture into center of batter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: deep pan pizza
directions: Mix crust; pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Saute vegetables; mix with soup and hamburger.
Spread over crust.
Top with pizza sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and bubbling.

title: pineapple jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add egg and beat until smooth.
Add juice and cook in heavy pan until thick.
Add to jello mixture and drained pineapple.
Sprinkle marshmallows over top and chill until firm.
Spread on Cool Whip and grated cheese on top.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Combine fat, onions, potatoes and dried beef (broken up) in pan and saute until potatoes get browned.
Add soup and water to mixture and blend.
Place all in casserole and top with buttered crumbs.
Heat in 350° oven and place casserole in for about 20 minutes.
(This is for 2, but I found it does feed 3.)

title: crab or salmon mousse
directions: Put water into saucepan.
Sprinkle gelatin on top and let stand 5 minutes.
Add soup, cheese and mayonnaise.
Heat and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat; add celery.
Drain meat and add Worcestershire sauce and onion flakes.
Pour into ring mold and chill at least several hours or overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Beat the ingredients together with an egg beater and serve with cucumber or cabbage.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine milk and eggs; pour over bread crumbs.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour over bread crumbs.
Pour into 1-quart baking dish; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in a slow oven, about 325°, for 1 hour, or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Serve warm with hard sauce.

title: old timey pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar together.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: pancakes the night before
directions: Add vinegar to milk.
The next morning, mix baking powder, salt, flour, baking soda and sugar.
Add cooking oil and eggs to flour mixture.
Add milk mixture; stir together.
Cook as pancakes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
(It will be sticky.)
Make into balls and bake at 350° for 20 minutes, until brown.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: chicken and sausage gumbo
directions: In a large stockpot, bring the chicken broth and water to boil. Add the chicken neck, back, wingtips, heart and gizzard, if desired; the parsley stalks and yellow onion.
Return to a boil; skim, reduce heat and simmer while preparing the other ingredients.

title: venison steak
directions: Brown meat thoroughly in oil and melted margarine in heavy skillet.
Add salt, pepper and garlic to taste while browning. Place steak in deep oven roasting pan; cover with thick slices of onion, mushrooms and mushroom juice.
Cover with tight lid or aluminum foil wrapped tightly around roaster.
Bake at 350° until tender enough to cut with fork.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: In saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar; bring to a boil and boil 8 minutes.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese; stir until mixture is thoroughly combined.
Cool.
Fold in apples, nuts, celery and whipped topping.
Pour in 9-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: strawberry-pineapple nut jello
directions: Combine strawberry Jell-O, boiling water and drained pineapple juice.
Add pineapple, strawberries and walnuts.
Pour 1/2 mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan; put it and other half in refrigerator to harden.
When semi-hard, spread 1 pint sour cream over mixture in pan.
Spread remaining Jell-O mixture on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Toss raisins, carrots and pineapple together; set aside.
Stir together mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and sweetener; add to carrot mixture.
Keep refrigerated.
Serves 8.

title: nanakiss' sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until very thick and lemony colored.
Gradually add sugar, beating constantly.
Add sifted flour, baking powder and salt alternately with water, flavorings and rind, blending lightly.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff, but not dry.
Gradually and gently fold egg yolk mixture into beaten whites.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in slow oven (325°) about 1 hour.
Turn pan upside down with tube over neck of funnel or bottle.
Cook and remove from pan.

Put on serving plate and dust top with confectioners sugar or top with whipped cream slightly sweetened and sliced peaches or strawberries or bananas. (Tastes better if refrigerated overnight with cream and fruit.)

title: o' henry bars
directions: Boil sugar and syrup to a soft ball stage, then add peanut butter.
Mix well; add cereal.
Put in greased cake pan.
Melt chips, (nuts optional) and 1/2 stick butter together; pour on top.

title: pineapple-carrot bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, butter, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in carrots and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins and pecans. Pour into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: winnipeg warmth
directions: Place dried mandarin peel, cardamom, cinnamon and cloves in a cheesecloth bag and simmer slowly in the Port and Claret.
Remove from the stove and place a wire grill over the top of the pan.
Put the sugar cubes on the grill and slowly pour the brandy over the sugar.
Carefully light sugar cubes, warm brandy will flame.
When the sugar is melted, remove the grill and extinguish the flame by covering the kettle.
Remove the bag of spices.
Serve hot.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chris' chicken
directions: Melt the margarine over medium heat and saute mushrooms until tender.
Remove with slotted spoon and reserve for later.
Pound chicken breasts between waxed paper until even and thin.
Saute in remaining margarine (add more if necessary) until cooked through. It is not important for the chicken to brown.
When chicken is done, remove from pan and pour off any remaining juices (do not scrape the pan).
Pour in enough cream to cover bottom of pan (at least 1/4 cup) and bring to a light boil.
Cut the cooked chicken into bite size pieces and add to pan with mushrooms.
Warm all, covering with the "gravy."
This recipe is quick and easy and everyone will think you are a gourmet cook!

title: spaghetti
directions: Cook onion with ground beef and seasonings and brown.
Add soups, cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Cook spaghetti.
Drain and rinse with hot water.
Mix with hamburg mixture.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Lightly grease 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Layer noodles, cottage cheese, sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Heat
oven
to
In
large bowl, combine pumpkin, milk, eggs
and
spices.
Mix
well
and turn into pie shell. Bake for 15 minutes and reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: custard
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick.
Let cool.
Mix 1 package Dream Whip and fold into cool custard.
Spread on top of jello and fruit.

title: hazelnut plum cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

Grease and flour 8-inch spring-form pan. In food processor fitted with chopping blade or in large mixer bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt. Process or stir until just blended.
Add butter, process briefly until just blended.
Add eggs, rind and vanilla; process just until smooth batter forms.
Scrape inside of bowl as necessary.
Spread half of batter in prepared pan and bake 25 minutes.

title: orange french toast(5 servings)
directions: Combine beaten eggs and juice; quickly dip bread into egg mixture, then into crumbs.
Fry on both sides in 1 tablespoon butter until brown.
Serve with butter and warm maple syrup.

title: pennsylvania dutch red beet eggs
directions: Drain beets.
Measure juice and add water if necessary to make 1 cup.
Add vinegar, sugar, salt and spices.
Bring to a boil. Pour hot solution over beets.
When cool, add peeled eggs and let stand in sour juice 24 hours.

title: herring in cranberry sauce
directions: Drain herring thoroughly.
Onions from herring may be used. Combine all ingredients with drained herring.
Mix thoroughly. Chill well before serving.
Serve as a dip with challah, Syrian bread or bread rounds.

title: duck & sausage gumbo
directions: Make stock with consomme and water in a large, heavy iron pot and bring to a low boil.
In a separate heavy iron pot, brown duck pieces well in hot cooking oil.
(This browning will prevent excess duck fat from cooking out into the gumbo.)
When all duck pieces are browned well, place them in the pot of stock.
Drain about 3/4 cup of the oil and fat from the pot used to brown the duck and set aside for later use in making roux.
Add the chopped onions, pepper, and celery to the remaining hot oil and saute until very tender, stirring well.
When vegetables are cooked, combine them with the duck and stock.

title: gooey butter bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Press onto bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: bacon squares
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, salad seasoning and paprika.
Stir in cheese, bacon, peanuts and onions.
Spread about 3 tablespoons bacon mixture over each slice of bread.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet 10 minutes.
Cut each slice into 4 pieces.
Serve hot.
Makes 56 appetizers.

title: mahogany chiffon cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Combine boiling water, cocoa; cool.
Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt into mixing bowl.
Make a well and add in order oil, egg yolks, cocoa mixture and vanilla.
Beat with spoon until smooth.
In large bowl, beat egg whites and cream of tartar to very stiff peaks.
Do not overbeat.
A dry rubber scraper drawn through leaves a clean path.
Pour egg yolk mixture in thin stream over entire surface of egg whites, gently cutting and folding in with rubber spatula until blended.
Do not stir. Pour into 10-inch tube pan. Bake 65 to 70 minutes, or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Invert pan on funnel or bottle.
Let hang until cold.
Frost with White Mountain Frosting.

title: tuna pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Press into prepared pie shell and lay triangles of cheese slices on top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet until all red is gone, then add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
After mixing together, cook at lowest temperature on electric skillet for about 3 hours.
Serve with long thin spaghetti, Parmesan cheese and tossed salad.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook fryer in water until tender; cool.
Remove meat from bones and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Saute onion in oleo in large saucepan.
Add soups, tomatoes and broth.
Break tortillas into pieces.
Grate cheese.

title: rhubarb dessert cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on the box.
Pour into a greased 9x13-inch pan.
Mix half-and-half, sugar, and rhubarb together. Pour over cake.
Bake at 350°F. for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in crust.
Refrigerate about 2 hours.

title: broiled frosting
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar, cream, chopped nuts and coconut. Spread on baked cake.
Broil in oven 5 minutes just under flame. Best on Pillsbury white cake.

title: zesty pasta salad
directions: Heat 4 quarts water, salted if desired, to boiling in 6-quart Dutch oven.
Cook pasta in boiling water 11 minutes.
Add asparagus to boiling water; cook about 3 minutes or until asparagus is crisp-tender.
Drain pasta and asparagus.
Rinse with cold water; drain.
If using fresh basil, finely chop before preparing dressing.
Mix Italian salad dressing, basil and red pepper in a large bowl.
Add pasta, asparagus and remaining ingredients; toss.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and boil squash in salted water about 7 minutes; drain. Add cream, grated carrot, onion, pimentos and pepper.
Saute stuffing mix in melted oleo.
Use 1/2 of stuffing in casserole and put other 1/2 on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter and honey.
Add the chocolate chips, M&M's/coconut and vanilla.
Spread the Rice Krispies cereal on wax paper.
Drop by teaspoons and roll in cereal until it is covered with cereal.
Enjoy your treat!

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Crust:
Mix graham crackers, margarine and sugar.
Pat lightly into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix in large saucepan rest of ingredients except tortilla chips.
Bring to a boil, then mix in ground beef.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage in frypan.
Drain and set aside.
Spread butter on bread and cube.
Place bread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with sausage and top with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Chill at least 8 hours.
Remove from refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
For breakfast or brunch.

title: play dough
directions: Mix salt, flour and cream of tartar in a medium saucepan.
Add vegetable oil and water.
(Add several drops of food coloring to water for colored play dough.)
Cook over medium heat until thickened and play dough pulls away from the sides of the pan.

title: nutty oven fried chicken
directions: In shallow dish, combine biscuit mix, pecans and seasonings. Mix well.
Dip chicken pieces in milk; coat generously with pecan mixture.
Place in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken until tender, 25 to 30 minutes.
Skin and pull meat into chunky pieces.
Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place broccoli spears in bottom of pan in one layer.
Scatter the chicken over the broccoli.
Make a paste of the mayonnaise and soup (add some water), lemon juice and curry powder.
Spread over chicken evenly.
Sprinkle cheese (or preferred topping) on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Add beef to all other ingredients in soup pot.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 6.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Mix the graham crackers, margarine and 1/2 cup powdered sugar for crust.

title: quick rolls
directions: Mix well and spoon into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: 5 pint hot pepper relish
directions: Put together.
Bring to boil and let simmer 30 minutes.
Can! Regular size lids and rings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade chili
directions: Cook meat and onion until brown and onion is tender.
Drain. Mix chili mix, garlic powder, beans and tomato sauce together in a big saucepan.
Add the meat mixture and simmer for about 30 minutes or until chili is thick.
Makes a big pot of chili.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: In a small bowl combine mayonnaise, chili sauce, pickle relish, onion and egg.
Cover; chill.
Makes 2 servings.

title: lime pie
directions: Mix all ingredients gently.
Fill crusts and chill about 3 hours.

title: monkey cake
directions: Quarter biscuits.
Mix 3/4 cup brown sugar and cinnamon in plastic bag.
Shake biscuits in mixture until well covered. Bring butter and 1 cup brown sugar to a boil.
Layer biscuits in tube pan.
Sprinkle each layer with raisins and nuts.
Pour syrup over each layer.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tootsie rolls
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Mix together for rolls.
Add vanilla, powdered sugar, powdered milk and corn syrup.

title: ina's beaten biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together at least twice. Mix in lard until mixture is mealy. Add milk to form a dough. Place
dough on floured board and beat with a wooden rolling pin. Keep folding the dough and beating it until blisters appear on the dough (about 200 times).
Roll out about 1/3-inch thick.
Cut with small biscuit cutter and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Prick the top of each biscuit 2 to 3 times with a fork. Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Add flour and salt. Stir into creamed mixture.
Mix in nuts. Chill mixture. Roll dough into 1-inch balls and bake on an ungreased baking sheet for 10 to 12 minutes in a 400° oven.
When done, roll cookies in powdered sugar.

title: squash corn bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix together cornmeal, flour, brown sugar, baking powder, salt, cumin, herbs, parsley and cayenne pepper.
In separate bowl, blend squash, eggs, milk, oil, cheese, pimiento and green chiles.

Pour dry ingredients into squash mixture and blend. Pour squash-cornbread mixture into greased 9-inch by 13-inch pan. Arrange ripe olives on top and bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.

title: cabbage-potato-hamburg casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburg with onion, salt and pepper.
Place in bottom of casserole.
Layer potatoes over hamburg; shred cabbage and salt lightly.
Put on top of potatoes; add water and bake until tender at 350°.
Before serving, top with cheese.

title: caribbean chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients. Blend remaining ingredients and pour over first mixture. Toss lightly.
Chill.
Serve on salad greens and garnish with tomatoes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook the vegetables. Add water chestnuts. Place in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cube 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese and mix with vegetables. Slice remaining 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese and place on top. Place Ritz crackers (rolled out and crumbled) on top. Melt the oleo and drizzle over. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese and ham tortilla rolls
directions: Combine cream cheese, lemon juice, seasoning, artichokes and pimentos in mixing bowl. Layer each tortilla with cream cheese mixture, ham and Provolone. Roll tortillas tightly and wrap in plastic wrap to hold form. Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving. To serve, cut rolls into 1-inch thick slices.

title: chicken and mock dumplings
directions: Combine ingredients except tortillas and cook in a medium size pot until chicken is well done.
Remove this mixture from pot; skin and debone chicken.
Cut tortillas into strips.
Bring stockpot to a boil and add 1/4 teaspoon curry powder and tortillas strips one at a time.
Let boil about 10 minutes.
Add cut up chicken and boil 5 minutes more.

title: miniature pecan pies
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter until smooth.
Add flour, mix well.
Shape into ball.
Chill 2 hours.
Divide into 24 walnut size balls.
Mold into mini muffin pans.
Run finger around cup to make rim.
Fill each with 1 teaspoon of filling.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Take out of pan while hot.

title: fettucine carbonara
directions: In large skillet, stir-fry bacon and onion until golden brown, stirring often.
Remove from heat.
Drain excess fat from skillet; set aside.

title: roast pork
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
In large skillet, combine butter, pork lard, onion, celery, green pepper, garlic, pork and veal magic and dry mustard.
Cook and stir about 4 minutes over high heat.
Cool. Meanwhile, place roast in baking pan, fat side up.
Make several large slits in meat with knife, being careful not to cut through to bottom.
(Make the slices down the length rather than the width of the roast so all of the carved pieces will have some of the vegetable mixture stuffing).
Stuff pockets generously with vegetable mixture, then thoroughly rub vegetable mixture over entire roast by hand.
If any mixture is left, spread it evenly over top and a little on sides of roast.
Roast, uncovered, about 3 hours (or until meat thermometer inserted in meatiest part registers 160°) then at 425° until dark brown on top and meat is no longer pink in center, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand about 20 minutes, then slice as desired.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Beat eggs until creamy; add sugar.
Mix in flour, baking powder, pineapple with juice and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fancy cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower and drain.
Combine ingredients, except cheese, in a bowl.
Spread over cauliflower.
Place in baking dish; sprinkle cheese on top.
Place in hot oven until cheese melts.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy; beat in flour, butter and sugars until well blended.
Fold in chips and pour into shell and bake for 1 hour.

title: mexican corn
directions: In a medium bowl microwave butter until melted.
Stir in flour to thicken.
Add corn.
Microwave until warm.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Microwave until hot.
Serves 4.
Good, fast and easy!

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place chicken on top.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover, fluff rice and bake for 10 to 15 more minutes.

title: crusty garlic cheese bread
directions: Cut loaf lengthwise.
Melt butter and mix in Parmesan, garlic and basil.
Brush generously, using all butter mixture.
Wrap in foil and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Unwrap and place under broiler until crispy.

title: 6-week bran muffins
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add eggs, oil and buttermilk; mix well.
Store in refrigerator in airtight container 6 to 8 weeks.

title: old fashioned cream pie
directions: Stir all together until smooth.
Pour into unbaked shell; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in hot oven (400°) until thickened or about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: brenda's banana split cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Cook yellow cake mix according to box directions. Cool!

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in casserole.
Add garlic and half the parsley.
Mix well.
Arrange shrimp in single layer. Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Turn shrimp.
Sprinkle with lemon peel, lemon juice and parsley.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: pumpkin and cream cheese roll
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside. Grease and line with wax paper.
Grease and flour again a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Beat eggs and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in pumpkin.
Stir in dry ingredients all at once.
Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Invert onto a clean towel dusted with confectioners sugar.
Peel off wax paper.
Roll up cake and towel together.
Cool on wire rack . Unroll and spread with filling.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt butter.
Beat eggs and add sugar. Beat in butter, corn syrup, molasses, lemon juice, vanilla and salt.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake 20 to 30 minutes or until set.

title: oven roasted potatoes with herbs
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place all ingredients in a plastic bag; shake to coat.
Empty into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes until tender, stirring occasionally.

title: cranberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in milk, oil and egg until blended. Fold in cranberries, nuts and orange peel.
Spoon into greased muffin tin or use paper liners.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Serves 12.

title: meal in a skillet(serves 4)
directions: Combine in skillet.
Cook over low heat for 20 minutes.

title: yankee doodle salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni shells.
In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, sour cream, dill, mustard and garlic.
Add macaroni, radishes, corn and green pepper.
Toss the salad.
Add the cayenne pepper, salt and pepper to taste.
Chill the salad, covered, for at least 2 hours.
Garnish with the dill.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar and oil together.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add sour cream last and mix well. In separate bowl mix brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Place 1/2 of batter mixture in bottom of pan.
Put cinnamon mixture on, then pour in rest of batter.
Bake in Bundt or tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: date-nut cake
directions: Heat water, sugar, oleo, dates, cinnamon and cloves until oleo melts; stir.
Cool.
Add flour and soda sifted together.
Mix well. Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 2 loaf pans.

title: curried shrimp
directions: Cook
and devein shrimp according to directions.
Saute onions with
stick
oleo. Add 6 tablespoons of plain flour. Add tomatoes
and
juice.
Add 3 tablespoons curry. Serve over rice.

title: pandas
directions: Spread ingredients on the canned biscuits pressed flat.
Fold biscuits together and press edges together with a fork (like a fried pie).
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour Ranch dressing over. Serve with garlic bread.

title: refrigerator yeast rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine yeast and 2 cups flour.
In 4-cup glass measure, combine milk, sugar and shortening.
Heat, uncovered, at High in microwave for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes (until warm and shortening begins to melt).
Add to dry mixture in bowl and add egg.
Beat at low speed with mixer for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Place in oiled bowl, turning once to completely oil surface.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Let rise once; roll out and make into rolls.
Bake in a preheated oven at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown. Brush with softened butter.

title: squash with green chilies
directions: In large skillet, saute squash and onion in butter until tender. Add milk, green chilies, salt and pepper. Cover and cook over low heat 15 minutes. Pour into casserole dish; sprinkle with cheese. Cover and let stand several minutes until cheese melts.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix in heavy 2-quart saucepan the sugar, milk, marshmallows, butter or margarine and a few grains of salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat to a boil (bubbly all over). Boil and stir 5 more minutes.
Remove from heat. Stir in until completely melted the semi-sweet chocolate pieces. Stir in nuts and vanilla. Spread in an 8-inch pan.

title: english trifle
directions: In a trifle bowl (a glass bowl with tall straight sides), layer 1/2 of the cake cubes and 1/2 of the orange slices.
Pour 1/2 of the sherry over that.
In order, layer 1/2 of the jello cubes, pudding, pecans and whipped cream.
Repeat layers putting remaining pecans on top of last layer of whipped cream.
Refrigerate for 4 hours before serving.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together all but Cheddar cheese.
Put in a cake pan or casserole dish and top with cheese.
Heat in oven until hot (or great to do in the microwave).
Serve with Doritos or nacho chips.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add onion and green pepper and cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and cook until thoroughly heated (do not boil).

title: pie crust
directions: Combine liquids, pour over bread to make dough.
Mix well. Press into pie tin.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
This equals one bread.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken rice casserole(an elegant version of a hot chicken salad.)
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Mix mayo with water.
Add chicken mix.
Fold in egg slices.
Place in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with potato chips. Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery soup

title: lola stack cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Spread with thick, sweetened spiced applesauce between layers and on sides after cake is cooled.

title: fritos pie
directions: For each person:
Put 1/2 cup of Fritos in serving bowl, 3/4 cup hot chili and 1/4 cup grated cheese.
Ready to eat!

title: dirty rice
directions: Saute bell pepper, onion and celery in nonstick frypan. Remove from fryer and fry sausage until crumbly; drain on paper towels.
Combine all ingredients in a covered saucepan and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve with green and yellow vegetables.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook the potatoes and carrots in boiling water until tender. Drain. Saute bacon until crisp. Drain on paper towels and crumble. Saute onion and celery until tender.
Combine potatoes, carrots, onion/celery mixture, bacon and milk in pot. Simmer for 30 minutes.
May also add cheese as desired.
Makes about 2 quarts or 8 (1 cup) servings.

title: rice-a-roni salad
directions: Add the olives, onions, artichoke hearts, mayo and curry powder to the rice. Toss and chill.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Heat first four ingredients slowly to boiling and cook, without stirring, to 242° or until a small amount dropped from tip of spoon spins a long thread.
Pour syrup slowly into stiffly beaten egg whites, beating constantly.
Beat until cool and thick enough to spread.
Add vanilla.
Will frost one 9 x 9-inch cake.

title: dene's chicken dressing(bread dressing)
directions: In large bowl, crumble biscuits and toast.
Precook onion and celery in boiling water until softened; drain, then add to biscuits.
Add egg (beaten),
melted butter, salt and baking powder.
Slowly add broth or stock until pouring consistency.
Can add pepper, celery seed or poultry seasoning for added taste. Pour into buttered glass dishes no more than 1 1/2 inches thick. Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes until edges brown.

title: english pea bake
directions: Mix peas, soup, chestnuts and onion together. Pour into greased baking dish. Pour melted oleo, crumbs and cheese evenly over top. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: kentucky cornbread
directions: Bake at 450° for 30 minutes in an iron skillet.
May add Cheddar cheese and hot peppers for Mexican style.

title: crisp pita circles
directions: Brush the inner sides of the pita circles with the melted butter and honey.
Sprinkle with the toasted sesame seeds and broil 1 minute or until top begins to brown.
Bread should become crisp. Serve hot or cold.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Roll into medium-size balls.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: green chili snack
directions: Put chilies on the bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with eggs and then cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Set out for a few minutes.
Cut into small squares and serve on Triscuits.

title: prize supreme pie
directions: Melt margarine; stir in sugar.
Add eggs, vinegar, pecans, raisins and coconut.
Mix well by hand.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 50 minutes at 300°.

title: cherry pecan gems
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in egg, syrup and extract.
Stir together flour, soda, cream of tartar and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Stir into creamed mixture; stir in nuts.
Shape dough into 9-inch roll. Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill well.
Cut into 1/4 inch slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Lightly press a well drained red cherry half in center of each cookie.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: nut balls
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add salt, nuts and flour.
Roll into small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 15 minutes or until brown in 300° oven.
Let cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: meat sandwiches
directions: Grind one pound bologna (can add boiled eggs).
Add sweet pickle relish or pickles or olives, enough mayonnaise to make a spread for sandwiches.
Put between bread.
Cut off crust and cut into small bite size sandwiches (can stack with cheese).

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute
onion with butter and seasoning.
Add cream of chicken soup and water.
Add 1/2 cup of melted Cheddar cheese.
Cut up chicken breasts.
Put egg noodles in oven dish.
Pour sauce on top of noodles.
Add 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes.

title: easy pork parmigiana
directions: Combine egg with water; set aside.
Combine Parmesan cheese and breadcrumbs; set aside.
Place each piece of pork between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Dip pork in egg mixture and dredge in crumb mixture.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello and hot and cold water, let set until syrupy.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, yogurt and dry gelatin. Spoon into pie crust. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: zippy green beans
directions: Blend the dry onion soup mix and 1 cup hot water; simmer for 10 minutes.
Add the green beans and mushrooms and heat.
Serves 4.

title: easy punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and Kool Aid in small amount of warm water; add lemon juice and pineapple juice. Add enough water to make 2 gallon.

title: ham and apples in casserole
directions: Arrange slices of ham in buttered, flat casserole.
Peel and chop apples.
Mix with raisins and brown sugar.
Spoon over ham in casserole.
Top with second slice.
Pour apple juice over all. Bake at 400°
for 30 minutes, basting several times.

title: fruit slush
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Add rest of ingredients and freeze.
Thaw until slushy before serving.

title: spiced tea mix(diabetic)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and mix well. Store mixture in an airtight container.
Be sure to stir well before use.

title: tuna salad
directions: Chop tomatoes and potatoes into small cubes.
Toss all ingredients together.
Serve on lettuce leaves with saltine crackers.
Important to remember to tear leaves off, do not cut leaves.
If you cut leaves, they will begin to turn brown and make dish look bad.
Great for dinners or for losing weight.

title: caramel icing
directions: Let it come to a boil; take off stove and add 1/4 cup milk. Let come to a boil again; take off stove and let cool.
Add about 2 cups powdered sugar or put enough to spread good over the cake. Icing for 1 cake.

title: condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix in blender or mixer at high speed until thick.
Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Marinate with poppy seed or Parmesan peppercorn salad dressing.
Great alternative to tossed salad.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix and press graham crackers, oleo and sugar.
Mix Jell-O and water.
Set aside to cool.
Whip milk; whip the cream cheese and sugar.
Pour Jell-O into cream cheese mixture.
Whip.
Add whipped milk until well blended.
Pour over graham cracker crumbs. Sprinkle top with graham cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: breakfast delight
directions: Cook sausage according to package directions in a large skillet; drain well.
Return sausage to skillet and add apples and remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often, about 5 minutes, or until liquid is absorbed.
Serve immediately. Yields 8 servings.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter and peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies and sugar. Roll into balls and chill 3 to 4 hours.
Dip balls in melted chocolate and wax.
Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Stir milk and salad oil into egg.
Sift together and add dry ingredients.
Stir just until flour is moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Batter should be lumpy.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bring to a boil over medium heat the sugar, cornstarch and water, stirring constantly.
Boil until clear.
Remove from heat. Slowly add Jell-O to hot mixture and stir until well blended.
Set aside to cool.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Makes 16 servings.
Prep:
10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 70 to 80 minutes.

title: somalia tea
directions: Bring water to
boil.
Pour over ingredients.
