Steep for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: triple chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sour cream, pudding mix, oil, water and eggs on low speed for two minutes or until well blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake in greased and floured bundt pan at 350 degrees for 1 hour.
Leave in pan 15-20 minutes before turning out on cake plate.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Dough should be stiff, not too moist. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour in cast-iron skillet or glass pie plate or 8-inch cake pan.
All pans should be greased.
Do not underbake.
Cool before cutting.

title: easy eye of round roast
directions: Wash roast and place in a slow electric cooker.
Pour the package of onion soup over roast, then pour water over both ingredients.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or on high 3 to 5 hours. Cut and serve with meat and onion juices.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and egg yolks together.
Add sugar and cream well.
Add flour alternately with sour cream.
Whip egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Add vanilla and baking powder. Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Break
chicken	up;
mix
in soup and Veg-All.	Pour in deep dish
pie
shell; top with other pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: glazed fresh apple cookies
directions: In a mixer bowl, beat sugar and shortening until well combined.
Beat in 1 egg until fluffy.
Combine next 5 ingredients and add to creamed mixture on low speed.
Beat in apple juice.
By hand, stir in apple, nuts and raisins.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: down home butterscotch pie
directions: In a medium-size saucepan, add milk, sugar, flour and egg yolks.
Beat until smooth.
Place over medium-high heat.
Keep stirring until it boils.
Turn down heat to medium.
Keep stirring until it thickens.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter. Stir until smooth.
Pour into precooked pie crust.
Let cool for 2 hours before cutting.
You can use the egg whites to make a meringue top.

title: colonial carrot pecan cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside.
In large size mixing bowl, combine oil and sugar and mix well.
Add 1/2 flour mixture and blend.
Add remaining flour mixture, alternating with eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add carrots and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into lightly oiled 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in slow oven (about 325°) for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tests done.
Frost with Orange Glaze.

title: hurry-up chili
directions: In 2-quart casserole that can be used on top of stove put the tomatoes, kidney beans and chili seasoning.
Warm and mix.
Boil rice according to package directions.
Add to tomato bean mixture. Serve with sliced scallions.
Serves 6 to 8.
Better the second day.
Can be frozen.

title: easy corned beef and cabbage soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until cabbage is tender. Taste and adjust seasoning, if needed.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients except chip well with mixer, adding eggs one at a time.
Add chips.
Flour into greased and butter Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cushaw pie
directions: Mix well cushaw, sugar, butter, flour and eggs in mixing bowl. Blend in baking powder, cinnamon and vanilla.
Hand beat for five minutes.
Pour into two 9-inch unbaked pie shells.
Scatter nuts on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with mixture of 2 cups of crushed cornflakes and 1 stick margarine. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered, then 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: mexicali dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, and taco seasoning.
Spread in a medium serving platter.
Sprinkle olives, shrimp, and rotel on evenly.
Top with lettuce and cheddar.
Pour taco sauce over this. Serve with corn chips.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream Crisco, peanut butter and sugar until smooth.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a Pyrex measure cup (4 cup size):
Microwave on High sugar and corn syrup for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts and microwave 3 to 5 minutes on High until light brown.
Watch carefully.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir.
Microwave 1 to 2 minutes on High.
Add baking soda and stir gently.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet and cool 1/2 to 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix together and cook in 375° oven until brown.

title: squash dressing casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: pudding cookies
directions: Mix oleo, brown and white sugar together.
Mix flour, soda and chips with other mixture.
Drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package; drain well.
Combine with melted or softened cream cheese and butter (melted).
Line a 2-quart casserole with artichoke hearts, cut in half.
Pour cheese and butter mixture into spinach and stir.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.

title: delicious asparagus
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small frying pan melt butter and add the flour and the milk slowly, stirring constantly until thick.
Place 3 asparagus on each slice of ham and roll up.
Place seam-side down in a Pyrex casserole dish.
Cover with cream sauce and top with cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: nam prik shrimp
directions: Combine all ingredients except shrimp.
Mix well.
Let stand 30 minutes before adding shrimp.
Marinate shrimp for 30 minutes. Skewer shrimp, piercing at head and tail.
Grill 2 to 3 minutes per side over red hot to medium hot fire.
Baste once after first turn.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a "well" and add eggs, oil and berries.
Mix until just blended.
Pam 2 loaf pans. Bake in two 9 x 5-inch pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Bring chocolate, sugar and water to a rapid boil for 2 minutes.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Boil on low heat until thickened, about 10 minutes.
May be stored in refrigerator for 10 to 14 days.
Can be heated in microwave as needed.

title: spicy sweet and sour chicken
directions: Put soy sauce, honey, sugar, water, wine, pepper, ginger and garlic in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil and stir for a few seconds.
Lower heat to medium and add chicken (washed and dried). Cook chicken with pan, covered until liquid mixture is almost evaporated.
Remove chicken and pour remaining liquid over chicken.

title: caramel marshmallows
directions: Melt caramels, sweetened condensed milk and butter in double boiler or microwave.
Dip marshmallows in mixture.
Roll in Rice Krispies and place on wax paper.

title: uncle tommy's famous flaming cajun spice
directions: Makes enough to keep you on fire all summer!

title: peach cobbler
directions: Line pan with sliced peaches.
Make batter of oleo, milk, baking powder, vanilla, 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt.
Pour batter over peaches and spread.
Mix 1 cup sugar with water and pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If I use frozen peaches, I cut the sugar in the syrup to 1/2 cup.

title: pea pickin' cake
directions: Blend ingredients well with mixer.
Grease 2 round pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Let cake cool.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion in butter until soft and yellow.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat mix (do not boil).
Can be used for ham, pork or chicken.

title: strawberry smoothie
directions: UTENSILS:
You will need a blender (you'll need help from an adult), serving glass and measuring cups and spoons.

title: golden chicken nuggets
directions: Mix egg, water, salt, sesame seed and flour.
Dip chicken into batter.
Drain.
Pour corn oil into heavy skillet or deep fryer; heat to medium heat (375°).
Carefully add chicken one layer at a time.
Fry 3 to 5 minutes or until golden brown; drain.
Serves 6.

title: honey coated nuts
directions: Beat the egg whites and sugar together until peaks form.
Fold in nuts.
Melt the butter on cookie sheet with sides or a jelly roll pan. Pour nut mixture on pan and roast in a 350° to 375° oven for 45 minutes. Cool. Serve at any party.

title: angel food supreme
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Have ready an ungreased tube pan.
Sift and measure flour and first amount of sugar together.
Measure egg whites, cream of tartar and salt into a large mixing bowl.
Beat until foamy; gradually add second amount of sugar, a small amount at a time.
Continue beating until meringue holds stiff peaks. Fold in flavoring; sprinkle sugar and flour mixture over meringue. Fold in gently, just until flour disappears.
Push batter into tube pan.
Cut gently through batter with spatula.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Invert on a large heavy bottle and let stand for 1 hour.
Turn right side up.
Slide knife gently around sides of pan and turn out onto serving plate.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Thaw pie shell.
Bake at 425° until light brown.
Cool, reduce temperature to 350°.
Sprinkle cheese, bacon and onion into
pie shell.
Beat eggs, milk and salt until well blended. Pour
over cheese,
bacon
and
onion mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes,
until knife
comes
out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: okra and stewed tomatoes
directions: Combine okra and
tomatoes.
Simmer for 5 to 7 minutes. Add butter, salt and pepper.
Serves 6 to 8.
Serve hot.

title: blueberry sky pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, add lemonade and milk.
Fold in 3/4 of the blueberry pie filling.
Fold in 3/4 of the Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shells.
Chill.
Using 1/2 of the remaining Cool Whip, make a mound in center of pie.
Spoon on 1/2 of remaining pie fill. Repeat on second pie.
Chill.

title: wonderful fragrance
directions: Slice or quarter apple and place in saucepan.
Add cinnamon sticks and cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat to a simmer.
Let this simmer all day if you wish, making sure you add water when it boils down.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine dressing mix with melted margarine.
Place half of this mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Place large cut pieces of chicken over the dressing mix.
Cover with the chicken soup. Put remainder of dressing mix over chicken.
Pour 2 1/2 cups of chicken broth over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: grannie's peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown and white sugars; mix well. Then add vanilla, peanut butter and beaten eggs. Beat together.

title: curried fruit bake(one of our favorites.)
directions: Drain fruit well.
Put in casserole (flat).
Bake 1 hour in a 325° oven.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chinese candies
directions: Melt chips together in microwave.
Add noodles and peanuts to mixture.
Stir together with spoon.
Drop onto waxed paper with a teaspoon.
Candy will harden upon standing (hardens faster in cool temperature). Makes 3 dozen candies.

title: herbed peasant bread
directions: Form thawed dough into a ball.
Press dough into a 12-inch circle.
Place on a greased pizza pan.
Brush with 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes until lightly browned.
In a small cup, combine 2 tablespoons olive oil, sage, rosemary and garlic powder.
Brush with 1/2 sage mixture over entire crust.
Top with remaining ingredients and drizzle with remaining sage mixture.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: lemon blossom pie
directions: Mix together egg yolks, lemon rind and juice; set aside.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Gradually stir in boiling water and cook, stirring constantly, until clear and thickened (2 to 3 minutes).
Carefully stir in egg-lemon mixture; cook, stirring for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in butter.
Cool 5 minutes.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: lemon bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cake mix, pie filling, and coconut. Stir until thoroughly mixed (do not add any liquid).
Spread this mixture in a 10 by 15 inch baking pan.
Bake for 30 minutes in a preheated 350 degrees oven.
Cool.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together. Add eggs, one at a time, and add half of flour.
Beat.
Add remaining flour.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Bake in a tube pan that has been greased and floured at 310° to 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
(This recipe has no liquid in it.)

title: tetrazzini supper
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain.
Pour oil over spaghetti and toss.
In large casserole, mix the soups, milk and Cheddar.
Stir in meats and spaghetti.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top of casserole. Bake in oven at 375° for 30 minutes.
Can be prepared ahead of time.
Bake 10 minutes longer.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Beat together with fork egg, oregano and Parmesan cheese. Brush over dough (reserve some egg mixture for later).
Layer pepperoni and cheeses over dough.
(Roll 12 x 15-inch rectangle.) Roll as for jelly roll, folding in ends and pulling toward you as you roll.
This will keep the pepperoni and cheeses from slipping as you roll.
Put on lightly greased baking sheet.
Brush on remaining egg mixture.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: super rich cheese cake
directions: Blend the cream cheese, Ricotta and sugar. Add each of the remaining ingredients one at a time to cream cheese mixture.
Mix all until blended.
Pour into a greased 9-inch spring-form pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and leave cake in for another hour.
Do not open the oven door during this time!
Enjoy!

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Mix together beef, onion, soup, water and beans; pour into baking dish.
Mix muffin mix as directed on box; pour over meat mixture.
Bake at 350° until cornbread is done.

title: apple salad
directions: Boil crushed pineapple and sugar for 3 minutes. Add Jell-O and cream cheese (cubed and softened) and stir well. Leave in bowl and put in fridge to chill for about 20 minutes. Fold in pecans, apple and 6 ounces Cool Whip. Spread in serving dish and return to fridge until firm. Top with remaining 6 ounces Cool Whip.

title: make ahead salad
directions: Layer ingredients as listed in preceding order.
Cover with 1 pint Hellmann's mayonnaise and seal to edges.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated Parmesan cheese over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: chasen's chili
directions: *Add chili to taste.

title: sausage brunch bake
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Combine eggs, milk, bread, cheese, mustard and salt and add to sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set in center. Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Nice made in round dish and cut like pie.

title: beet pickles
directions: Combine liquids, sugar, salt and pepper; bring to a boil. Place cooked and peeled beets into jars.
Add cinnamon stick and pour boiling liquid over beets.
Seal.
This makes about 1 quart beets.

title: apple strudel
directions: Into buttered baking dish, put thick layers of sliced fruit. Sprinkle each layer with sugar and cinnamon. Dot with butter. Mix 1 cup sugar, salt, flour and baking powder.
Add egg. Mix until crumbly. Pour over fruit. Bake at 350° until brown. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: You will need a nonstick pan, 11 x 12-inch, etc., and ovenproof pans with lids.

title: best bean dip ever
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese in a baking dish. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake one hour at 300°.

title: glazed pineapple cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Blend cream cheese with sugar, eggs and 1/2 tsp. vanilla.
Stir in 1/2 c. pineapple.
Pour into crust.
Bake 25 minutes or until center is set; cool.
Combine reserved juice with cornstarch. Cook 3 or 4 minutes or until thickened and translucent.
Stir in remaining pineapple.
Spread to outer edges of pie.
Chill.

title: cheddar-spinach quiche
directions: Toss cheese and flour in bowl.
Add spinach, milk, eggs and mushrooms.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into crust and bake 1 hour in preheated 350° oven.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: acadiana cafe's cajun cabbage
directions: Cook bacon in large heavy pan until brown and crisp.
Add margarine and chopped onion.
Cook over medium heat until onions are translucent.
Add green pepper and cook until soft, about 5 minutes.
Add cayenne and m.s.g.; mix well.
Add chopped cabbage and mix well.
Mixture will seem dry.
Cook slowly over medium heat, about 30 minutes, or until cabbage is tender.
Do not overcook.

title: stove top baked beans
directions: Use large pot.
Fry bacon well done.
Take bacon out to use later.
Chop onions up really fine.
Place onions in bacon grease and cook for a few minutes.
Pour can of pork and beans in pot. Add brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and catsup.
Cook on medium heat for 20 minutes.
Break bacon in very small pieces and add to pot.
Add extra brown sugar, if needed.

title: coconut orange salad
directions: Mix sour cream and miniature marshmallows.
Fold in oranges and coconut.
Easy to fix and ready to serve!

title: vegetable salad
directions: Pour vinegar, oil and sugar over drained vegetables.

title: crusty beef casserole
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and garlic in a large skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble. Drain off pan drippings; stir in tomato sauce and chili powder. Spoon meat mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 baking dish. Top with cheese. Spoon beans over cheese. Prepare cornbread mix according to package directions and pour over beans. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until cornbread is golden.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Fry sausage (or other meat) and drain. If using ham, chop. Beat eggs and milk together. Add sausage, bread cubes and cheese. Stir in dry mustard and salt and pepper to taste. Pour into 13 x 9 inch pan. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Can be mixed at night and baked next morning.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and roll into a ball.
Roll in remaining 1 ounce chopped dried beef.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together until done.
Mix milk and egg together and add to squash.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: deer bologna
directions: Mix all spices together in a large bowl.
Grind meat and spread out on table.
Sprinkle spices over meat evenly until all is used. Then mix together with hands, mixing well.
Grind it again. Stuff into muslin bags.
Let hang where cool or put in the refrigerator for 24 hours.
Bake at 200° for 3 hours.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown beef, drain.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Mix well.
Combine onion, cream cheese and sour cream in bowl.
Mix well.
Layer noodles, beef mixture and sour cream mixture alternately in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: baked scrambled eggs
directions: Toast bread and cut into cubes.
Scatter over bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cube cheese and scatter cubes over toast.
Scatter ham cubes over toast and cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
Pour egg mixture over ham and cheese.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight. In the morning, preheat oven to 325°; uncover baking dish and bake for 1 hour.
Let stand a few minutes before cutting to serve. Makes 8 servings.

title: crunchy veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a greased casserole dish.
Note:
A 1 1/2-inch deep large size dish is best.
Top with your favorite cracker or crumb topping.
A thin layer is best (I like to use finely crumbled Ritz or cheese crackers.)
Bake at 350° until lightly browned and bubbly, approximately 30 minutes.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients except 1/4 cup barbecue sauce. Shape into loaf in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Microwave on High 12 to 14 minutes or until center is no longer pink, turning dish after 6 minutes.
Top with remaining barbecue sauce; let stand 5 minutes.

title: jonny bread
directions: Let dough raise in pan until ready for baking.
Break off handfuls of dough; stretch dough as far as possible.
Fry in Crisco until light or golden brown.
Serve with butter and jelly. Delicious with any meal.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except pecans), mixing very well.
Form into ball and roll in pecans.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix cornstarch, 2/3 cup sugar and salt; gradually add milk. Cook in double boiler until thick, about 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Slowly add small amount of hot mixture to egg yolks, then stir into remaining hot mixture. Cook 5 minutes. Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla. Cool.

Place alternately a layer of vanilla wafers, sliced bananas and pudding in baking dish. Spread with meringue made by beating egg whites until foamy, then add remaining sugar gradually, beating until stiff. Spread over pudding. Bake in 450° oven until browned, about 5 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: favorite lettuce dressing
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a jar and shake well.
Chill. Pour over chopped lettuce or lettuce wedges and sprinkle with chopped, hard-cooked eggs.

title: hilda's snicker cookies
directions: Cream together butter, white and brown sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Add peanut butter, baking powder, soda, salt and flour. After mixed, remove wrappers from Snickers candy.
Roll mixture around Snickers candies.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Place in greased dish.
Place peaches over mixture.

title: avocado egg salad(makes 6 first-course servings)
directions: Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice, salt and hot pepper sauce in a large bowl. Add avocados, tomatoes, onion, eggs and parsley.
Toss lightly until well combined.
Cover; refrigerate. Serve on spinach leaves.

title: tamale pie
directions: Saute beef and onions.
Place all ingredients together in large casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil noodles; drain.
Mix noodles, eggs, onion, carrots and pickles.
Set aside.
Mix together Miracle Whip, sour cream and milk.
Add dry mustard, dill weed, garlic salt, cayenne pepper, pepper and paprika to dressing.
Taste dressing.
Can add more spices to suit taste.
Pour dressing over noodle mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: oven rice
directions: Mix together and pour in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine celery, cheese, onion, frozen vegetables, mayonnaise and salt.
Stir together and place in casserole dish.
Crush crackers and sprinkle over top of casserole.
Melt butter and drizzle over crackers.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and extracts together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add the flour and mix until smooth.
Spread 3/4 of the batter over a small cookie sheet.
Spread the cherry pie filling over the batter and spoon the rest of the batter over the top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fudge truffle cheesecake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients for crust and press on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Heat oven to 300°.

title: mystery bars
directions: Cook sugar and syrup over low heat until dissolved.
Add peanut butter; remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with melted chips.

title: sweet potato and apple soup
directions: Heat a large pot over moderate-high heat until hot.
Add oil and heat until hot.
Add onions and cook over low to moderate heat, stirring frequently until they start to brown, about 5 minutes.
Add sweet potatoes, apples, broth, 1 cup apple juice, thyme, basil, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes or until potatoes are soft.
Remove from heat and let stand until cool enough to handle.
Puree in food processor or blender to a coarse texture.
Return soup to pot, add remaining 3/4 cup apple juice and heat thoroughly.
For a thinner soup, add more juice.

title: cheese soup
directions: Bring to a boil bouillon cubes, water, celery, carrots, potatoes and onion.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables. Cook until tender.
Add soup and cheese.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: herb roasted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Place roasting rack in large roasting pan.
Rinse chicken; pat dry with paper towels.
In large bowl, toss stuffing with 1 c. water.
In large skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onions, spinach, ham, garlic, sage and rosemary to skillet; saute until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add spinach mixture to stuffing.
Stir in heavy cream and lemon juice; mix well.
Spoon stuffing loosely into chicken cavity, filling about 3/4 full.
Fold skin over opening and close with metal skewers.
Tuck wings under chicken and place on roasting rack. Roast chicken until thickest part of thigh reaches 180 degrees, and chicken is golden, about 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: christmas salad
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients; bring to boil and let cool while mixing salad.
Mix remaining ingredients.
When dressing has cooled, pour over salad.
Mix well; cover and refrigerate.
Will keep several days.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine all ingredients
(except tortillas) and heat in large skillet.
Place 1
tablespoon of chicken mixture in each tortilla. Roll tortilla and	place
in
a
baking dish.
Pour remaining mixture over
tortillas.
Sprinkle shredded Monterey Jack cheese generously over
tortillas.
Bake
at
until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, raisins and sunflower seeds.
Add the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar 1 hour before serving.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all except the almonds and potato chips. Put in well-greased baking dish.
Top with almonds and potato chips. Pour 1/2 cup melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: never fail pie crust(3 crust pie mix)
directions: Mix flour and shortening together.
Using 1 cup measure, break egg into cup and add vinegar and milk to make 1 cup.
Add to flour mixture.
Makes 3 fluffy crusts.

title: reese's peanut candy cookies
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients well, then add egg, flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix with first mixture until well blended.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Drop into ungreased tassie pans.
Take 9 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Bake out of oven and put a peanut butter cup on top.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Makes about 40 cookies.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together cake mix, oil, eggs and juice at medium speed 3 to 4 minutes.
Fold in oranges.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: pecan meal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into an unbaked pie shell. Top with pecans and bake in 350° oven until firm, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: white icing
directions: Mix Crisco, salt, vanilla
and
of sugar. Add milk and remaining sugar.
Beat until smooth.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add next 6 ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes, uncovered.
Cook noodles.
Beat eggs, cottage cheese, remaining teaspoon of salt, pepper, parsley and Parmesan cheese in a separate bowl.
Grate Mozzarella.
Lay in greased pan or dish half of the noodles, half of the cottage cheese mixture and half of the meat sauce mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with the cheese on top.
Cover and bake in a 375° oven until bubbly (30 to 45 minutes).

title: strawberry-lemonade punch
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and stir well.
Add the Fresca and stir gently.

title: cole slaw(cole slaw for 50)
directions: Put cabbage in a large bowl. Sprinkle salt and sugar
over it. Let stand about one and a half hours in a cold place. Drain well. Combine sweetened condensed milk and vinegar. Pour over cabbage. Toss with a fork. Keep cold until ready to serve.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in a microwave 8-cup measuring cup. Whisk in milk until smooth; add yolks until well blended.
Stir in lemon peel and juice. Add butter. Heat in microwave until just before it boils, about 5 minutes. Remove and stir.

title: juicy grilled burgers
directions: Preparation and cooking time is 15 minutes.

title: carrot bread
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs until light. Stir in vanilla and salad oil.
Add carrots, coconut, raisins and nuts.
Mix well until blended.
Combine the flour, salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and sugar. Sift into the first mixture.
Stir just until well blended. Spoon into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan that has been well buttered and dusted with flour. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until it tests done.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Its flavor and texture improve if wrapped and refrigerated for several days.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: braised short ribs
directions: Dredge ribs with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown on all sides. Drain off fat from pan and add onion, bay leaf and beef broth. Bake about 2 to 3 hours at 350° or until fork-tender.
Discard onion and bay leaf.

title: alice's strawberry pie
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until clear and slightly thick.
Add jelly and cool.
Add berries to cooled jello mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip when served.

title: golden festal pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare a one crust pie shell. Combine eggs, sugar, salt and spices and beat well. Blend in pumpkin, add milk, beat well. Turn into shell. Bake in a hot oven 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Pie is done when knife, inserted in center comes out clean.

title: jumbles
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift baking soda with flour and add flour and milk alternately.
Blend in vanilla.
Put on greased and floured cookie sheet (1 teaspoon spaced 1/2 inch apart).
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sweet yogurt(bangladeshi dish)
directions: First put yogurt and evaporated milk in a bowl. Then add sugar and mix these ingredients very well (a blender works well). Then put the mixed evaporated milk and yogurt in an oven proof glass tray.
Keep in oven at 100-110°F (lowest termperature in your oven) for 6-7 hours until it becomes thick, delicious yogurt.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Measure salt into flour.
Cut in shortening.
Beat egg and add to vinegar and water.
Stir into flour and shortening mixture. Roll out and put in pie pan.
Prick with fork.
Bake ten minutes at 400°.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Combine milk and water; add pudding.
Mix well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Beat cream until thick.
Fold in pudding.
Layer wafers, pudding and bananas.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Saute celery and onions in oleo until tender.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer until cheese has melted.
(Protect from sticking.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender (about 15 minutes).
Drain.
Add margarine, salt, pepper and eggs.
Mix.
Add rest of ingredients. Pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: baked squash
directions: Put one or two fresh tomatoes on top.
Add 1/4 to 1/2 stick butter, 2 tablespoons water, parsley flakes and garlic powder (optional).

title: corn casserole
directions: Soften butter.
Beat eggs, then mix all ingredients in a bowl (use dry Jiffy mix).
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch square greased pan (glass preferred).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Pour boiling water over first three ingredients.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain well.

title: orange n honey pull-apart
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Remove dough from can in rolled sections.
Do not unroll.
Place sections together on greased cookie sheet, forming 1 long roll.
Cut roll into 12 slices, cutting to within 1/8-inch of bottom and being careful not to cut all the way through.
Alternating from left to right, pull slices out sideways and twist to lay flat on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 35 minutes.
Mix butter, honey, and orange peel and brush over warm loaf.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: norwegian cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into balls and place 2-inches apart on baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: deep dish tuna pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sprinkle the crust with each of the cheeses.
In a medium saucepan, parboil the potatoes and onion until just barely tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain well and place in the pie crust over the cheeses.
Beat together half and half, milk, flour and dry mustard.
Pour over the potatoes.
Distribute tuna over the top; sprinkle with olive slices and crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes.
Let sit 10 minutes before cutting into wedges.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain all ingredients; mix and cover with dressing.
Can be refrigerated up to 5 days.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Place popped corn in roasting pan.
Take the ingredients off heat and add vanilla and soda.
Pour over popcorn and bake 1 hour at 250°.

title: cabbage pepper slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: lemony chicken cutlets
directions: About 45 minutes before serving:
With meat mallet, pound chicken breasts to 1/8-inch thickness.
On waxed paper, mix flour, salt and pepper; use to coat chicken.
Reserve remaining flour mixture.
In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in 3 tablespoons hot butter or margarine, cook breasts until lightly browned on both sides, adding more butter or margarine, if necessary.
Remove chicken pieces to plate.
Reduce heat to low. Into drippings in skillet, stir reserved flour mixture.
Add water, bouillon and juice of half lemon, stirring to loosen brown bits. Return chicken to skillet.
Thinly slice remaining lemons; top chicken with lemon slices.
Cover; simmer for 5 minutes, or until chicken is fork-tender.
Arrange chicken and lemon slices on warm platter.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking dish.
Place apples in bottom of dish.
Combine flour, sugar, butter and cinnamon. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes or until apples are tender. Turn oven to broil and brown top.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1/2 cup hot water; add strawberries, bananas, nuts and pineapple.
Half mixture in two bowls; let set overnight.	Put sour cream on top of one; turn the other one on top of sour cream.	Refrigerate.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix the zucchini, onions and peppers with 1/4 cup salt; set in refrigerator overnight.
Drain and rinse well with cold water. Put the vegetables in a large kettle.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Boil for 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir to prevent sticking.
Seal in jars.
Process in boiling water bath.

title: mama's pecan cake
directions: Cream butter, add sugar and eggs, beat well.
Sift flour and salt; add to butter mixture along with milk, baking powder, soda and vanilla.
Beat until batter is of smooth consistency.
Pour into well-greased pans and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes. Makes 3 layers.
Cool for 10 minutes before icing with Seven Minute Icing.
Sprinkle each layer with chopped pecans.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix German chocolate cake as directed on package.
Put half of batter into a greased and floured 13 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 250°.

title: david's quick and easy pasta
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling water until "al dente;" drain.
Cook broccoli in boiling water until crisp-tender; drain.
In large skillet or Dutch oven, heat olive oil over medium heat.
Add minced garlic.
Heat until garlic is very aromatic.
(Do not let garlic brown or burn.)
Add drained spaghetti and broccoli.
Toss to coat with seasoned oil.
Salt to taste.
Serve immediately.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Clean and scrub vegetables.
Break into bite size pieces. Drain juice from mushrooms.
Place in shallow dish and pour mixture over vegetables.
Let stand 24 hours before serving.

title: cole slaw
directions: Boil together first 3 ingredients and set aside to cool.
When this dressing is cool, pour over other ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate at least 2 4 hours before serving.
It is good as long as you keep it.
This serves 8 people.

title: ruby red salad dressing
directions: Prepare Italian dressing and add remaining ingredients.
Blend and chill.
(Blueberries may be added before serving.)

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together, but the 7-Up.
Just before serving, add the 7-Up.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with bell pepper and onion.
Drain.
Cook macaroni.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce and taco sauce.
Add cheese, cut in thin strips (Longhorn).
Add macaroni.
Stir well.
Put 4 slices of cheese on top and let melt.
Stir in well.

title: chicken gumbo(low calorie)
directions: Stew chicken in 4 cups water the day before.
Debone and skin and cut up chicken.
Let broth set overnight in refrigerator. Skim off fat.
Bring broth to boil.
Add chopped vegetables. Bring to boil again and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add chicken and serve.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sauce for pizza
directions: Heat oil in pan.
Add onion and garlic until translucent; then add the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer 40 minutes.

title: lemonade
directions: Squeeze the lemons.
Mix lemon juice, sugar and water.
Serve over crushed ice.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Cut angel food cake in half.
Tear into bite size pieces and layer bottom of pan.
Beat egg yolks and margarine together, then add powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 mixture over cake. Crush 3 Butterfinger candy bars; sprinkle over top of Cool Whip mixture.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat strips with flour mixture.
Brown meat in hot oil in a large frying pan.
Add onion and cook until clear.
Drain off excess fat.
Add soup and mushrooms.
Simmer, covered, 10 to 15 minutes.
Blend in sour cream and remove from heat.
Serve over egg noodles.
Sprinkle with paprika and garnish with parsley.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a pan.
Cook until zucchini is soft. Put all ingredients into the blender.
Blend until smooth.
Return to pan; reheat.
Season to taste.
